              "project/ROADMAP.md"
            ],
            "summary": "Different products. ROADMAP describes generic identity-transform template; SPEC describes Visual Modeler. See F11."
          },
          {
            "docs": [
              "project/SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a710.4",
              "project/SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a718.1 FR-C013",
              "project/SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a731 DoD #15"
            ],
            "summary": "v0.3 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 v0.4 migration normatively required but lacks an FR-C identifier. See F3."
          },
          {
            "docs": [
              "project/SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a75.2",
              "project/SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a75.14"
            ],
            "summary": "iao:OntologyDesignPattern minted under OBO IAO namespace without authority. See F4."
          }
        ],
        "owl_dl_notes": [
          {
            "observation": "iao:isAbout values are permitted to be class IRIs (\u00c2\u00a75.4.1 'a class IRI from an imported ontology, e.g. cco:Person'). Using a class IRI as the value of an object property assertion requires OWL 2 punning. The Project TBox \u00c2\u00a75.14 does not declare punning intent; iao:isAbout is declared @type:@id in @context but no rdfs:range is stated. Under strict OWL DL this is non-conformant; under OWL 2 with punning it is conformant only if explicit. Recommend \u00c2\u00a75.14 add 'iao:isAbout a owl:AnnotationProperty' or explicit OWL-2-punning acknowledgement.",
            "severity": "advisory"
          },
          {
            "observation": "ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter is declared owl:Class and used as the OBJECT of iao:isAbout assertions for placeholder projects. Same punning concern as above; magnified because the placeholder is the default state and will appear in nearly every migrated v0.3 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 v0.4 document.",
            "severity": "advisory"
          },
          {
            "observation": "The project root carries rdf:type = ['ecm:Project', 'iao:OntologyDesignPattern']. ecm:Project is declared rdfs:subClassOf iao:OntologyDesignPattern, so the dual typing is redundant under entailment. Harmless for OWL DL but invites confusion; consider emitting only ecm:Project in canonical form and deriving iao:OntologyDesignPattern by entailment, or document that both are emitted for offline consumers without reasoners.",
            "severity": "informational"
          }
        ],
        "realist_anchoring_notes": [
          {
            "observation": "Realist anchoring (\u00c2\u00a75.14, NFR-014, DoD \u00c2\u00a731) is entirely dependent on iao:OntologyDesignPattern \u00e2\u20ac\u201d an IRI the spec admits it does not own (F4). The architectural claim cannot be considered honest until the IRI is either minted under ecm: or coordinated with IAO. The fallback (\u00c2\u00a75.14 'if a future IAO release adds this term natively, the spec will align rather than re-namespace') is a forward-compatibility promise, not a current-conformance guarantee.",
            "severity": "blocking"
          },
          {
            "observation": "\u00c2\u00a75.4.1 permits iao:isAbout to be 'a project-declared subject IRI (e.g., ecm:CustomerOrderDomain) for which the project itself defines the subject as a topical anchor'. This permits the project to be 'about' an IRI that exists only inside the project's own ABox \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a self-referential anchor. Recommend \u00c2\u00a75.14 add a project TBox sub-class for such anchor subjects (e.g. ecm:ProjectDeclaredTopicalAnchor a owl:Class) so the realist claim is type-checkable.",
            "severity": "advisory"
          }
        ],
        "vmp_completeness_notes": [
          {
            "observation": "ecm:validationReports missing from @context (F8) and ecm:description missing from semantic projection (F7) are VMP completeness defects.",
            "severity": "major"
          },
          {
            "observation": "The \u00c2\u00a75.2 @context does not declare alias mappings for ecm:name, ecm:description, ecm:author, ecm:license, ecm:notes (no @type or @language). Their expanded form is JSON-LD-processor-dependent. Recommend declaring each with @type:xsd:string explicitly, or a top-level @language directive in @context.",
            "severity": "minor"
          },
          {
            "observation": "\u00c2\u00a75.11 CanvasLayout permits ecm:adapterState/reactflow as a namespaced adapter field. This is the only place an Editor Layer predicate is allowed to nest under a slash-separated key. The convention is not declared elsewhere; the canonical serializer (\u00c2\u00a75.3) does not address slash-keyed predicates.",
            "severity": "minor"
          }
        ],
