            "raw_stdout": "The spec-reviewer returned 16 findings on `project/SPEC.md` (v0.4 Engineering-Ready), with **recommendation: revise**.\n\n## Blocking issues (3)\n\n- **F1 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Version incoherence.** Header says v0.4, but \u00c2\u00a73.1, \u00c2\u00a73.2, \u00c2\u00a721, and \u00c2\u00a722 are still scoped/titled for v0.3. Conformance scope is undefined.\n- **F2 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Severity contradiction for realist-anchor findings.** \u00c2\u00a717.1 defines info as \"informational only,\" yet \u00c2\u00a717.4 + \u00c2\u00a710.4 make `LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER` (info) block export. `MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR` is also given inconsistent severity across \u00c2\u00a75.4.1 and \u00c2\u00a717.2.\n- **F3 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Missing FR-C for v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 migration.** \u00c2\u00a710.4 and DoD item 15 require it; FR-C013 covers only v0.2\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.3 and FR-C014 is used for a different purpose.\n\n## Major issues (7)\n\n- **F4** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `ecm:validationReports` appears in \u00c2\u00a75.4 example but is absent from \u00c2\u00a75.2 `@context` containers and \u00c2\u00a75.3 array ordering rules \u00e2\u2020\u2019 round-trip (NFR-012, \u00c2\u00a76.4) broken.\n- **F5** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `ecm:description` is documented as aliasing `rdfs:comment` but has no `@context` mapping; semantic projection (\u00c2\u00a76.3) drops it.\n- **F6** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d SPEC's 5-layer model (\u00c2\u00a74.1) is unreconciled with ARCHITECTURE.md / CLAUDE.md's 3-layer model.\n- **F7** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `iao:OntologyDesignPattern` is minted under IAO's `purl.obolibrary.org` namespace without authority (acknowledged in \u00c2\u00a75.14).\n- **F8** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d \u00c2\u00a77.5 defers domain/range to \"v0.4\" but the spec *is* v0.4.\n- **F9** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d \u00c2\u00a721.3 still references `canonical-v0.3/` fixtures while revision notes declare v0.3 goldens superseded; no `canonical-v0.4/` is defined.\n- **F10** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d COMPUTATION_MODEL.md's kernel error taxonomy and `provenance.rulesApplied` contract are entirely disconnected from SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a717's validation taxonomy.\n\n## Minor issues (4)\n\n- **F11** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d \u00c2\u00a75.3 rule 8 says \"no fractional seconds in v0.3\" inside a v0.4 spec.\n- **F12** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d TBox said to be \"logically present\" but no mechanical resolution path defined; \u00c2\u00a75.4 example lacks any tbox reference.\n- **F13** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d RFC 2119 boilerplate is absent from SPEC.md (present in ARCHITECTURE.md, COMPUTATION_MODEL.md, CLAUDE.md) despite pervasive lowercase must/should/may.\n- **F14** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `ecm:name` has no `@type`/`@language` declaration in `@context`; expanded form is implementation-defined.\n\n## Advisory (2)\n\n- **F15** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `state.jsonld` uses non-resolvable `fnsr.example` context URL co-located in repo root.\n- **F16** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d \u00c2\u00a727 OED-001 calls `ecm:` namespace a \"placeholder\" but v0.4 normatively mints load-bearing IRIs under it.\n\nThe blocking trio (version coherence, severity model, migration FR) should be resolved before any v0.4 implementation work proceeds.\n"
