            "raw_stdout": "The spec-reviewer returned **14 findings** against `project/SPEC.md` (v0.4) with a **`revise`** recommendation.\n\n## Blocking findings (3)\n- **F1** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d SPEC.md's six-phase delivery plan (\u00c2\u00a729) is structurally misaligned with ROADMAP.md's four-phase FNSR kernel plan. The two authoritative documents describe different systems.\n- **F2** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d No RFC 2119 conformance declaration in SPEC.md, despite using normative \"must\"/\"should\"/\"may\". ARCHITECTURE.md and COMPUTATION_MODEL.md both carry the declaration; SPEC.md does not.\n- **F3** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `iao:OntologyDesignPattern` is declared under the canonical IAO namespace (`http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/iao#`) but the spec admits IAO does not define this term. Namespace authority conflict \u00e2\u20ac\u201d any linked-data consumer dereferencing the IRI will fail.\n\n## Major findings (6)\n- **F4** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `ecm:validationReports` is used as a top-level array in \u00c2\u00a75.4 but is not declared in the normative `@context` (\u00c2\u00a75.2); silently breaks `@container: @set` array expansion.\n- **F5** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d \u00c2\u00a73.2 out-of-scope list cross-references \u00c2\u00a77.5 for blank nodes; \u00c2\u00a77.5 is \"Domain and Range.\" Blank nodes are in \u00c2\u00a77.3.\n- **F6** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d FR-C013 only covers v0.2 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 v0.3 migration; no FR captures the required v0.3 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 v0.4 leg, despite \u00c2\u00a722 and \u00c2\u00a731 DoD requiring it.\n- **F7** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Prose claims `ecm:description` provides `rdfs:comment`, but no alias is declared in the context. These are different IRIs.\n- **F8** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER` is classified Info in \u00c2\u00a717.4 yet blocks export, contradicting \u00c2\u00a717.1's rule that only Errors block export unconditionally.\n- **F9** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d SPEC.md uses a five-layer model with no mapping to ARCHITECTURE.md/CLAUDE.md's three-layer (`src/kernel`, `src/composition`, `src/adapters`) model.\n\n## Minor / advisory (5)\n- **F10** stale \"new in v0.3\" inline note in a v0.4 doc; **F11** `ecm:specVersion` format is unconstrained; **F12** CCO version-pin claim has no ADR backing in DECISIONS.md; **F13** UUIDv5 namespace UUID is unspecified, breaking NFR-013 byte-identicality across implementations; **F14** \u00c2\u00a715.9.4 references an external normative guide with no DOI, URL, or repo inclusion.\n\n**Recommendation: revise** \u00e2\u20ac\u201d particularly the three blocking items (SPEC\u00e2\u2020\u201dROADMAP alignment, RFC 2119 declaration, IAO namespace misattribution) before the document can be relied on as authoritative for implementation.\n"
          },
