        "overall_verdict": "reviewer_under_rigorous",
        "summary": "The reviewer's 19 findings are accurate and well-evidenced; every cited line and contradiction checks out. Two verdicts are extended rather than confirmed because severity or scope was imprecisely framed (F12 conflates JSON-LD expansion determinism with linked-data dereferenceability; F17 overstates the impact on semantic exports while understating it for the canonical project.jsonld; F14 missed \u00c2\u00a713.5's stale-v0.3 deferral). Critically, the reviewer missed one blocking-severity defect (M1: the `iao:` @context binding is the wrong namespace shape \u00e2\u20ac\u201d OBO IAO does not publish hash-namespaced terms, so `iao:isAbout` itself is unreachable, undermining the realist anchoring more deeply than F4 captures) and four major structural defects (canvas-layout nested-array ordering breaking NFR-012/013 for any UI-edited project; undefined scalar-vs-array canonical form for @type; the \u00c2\u00a75.14 TBox using rdfs:domain/range while \u00c2\u00a77.5 defers them; the \u00c2\u00a75.11 adapter-state discard rule conflicting with NFR-012 round-trip). The acceptance gate (`can_proceed_to_implementation: false`) is correct, and the five required resolutions should be extended to include the iao: namespace binding fix and the canvas-layout ordering rule before v0.4 can be called engineering-ready."
