            "rationale": "Reviewer's F10 cited SPEC sec 17.2:1242-1259 (sixteen domain-anchored hard error codes) versus COMPUTATION_MODEL.md sec 7:137-142 (four codes \u00e2\u20ac\u201d INVALID_INPUT/INVALID_CONTEXT/MALFORMED_JSONLD/MISSING_MANDATORY_NODE \u00e2\u20ac\u201d with 'codes MUST be stable across versions'). COMPUTATION_MODEL.md sec 5:55-71 mandates provenance.rulesApplied; absent from SPEC sec 5.4 example, sec 6.3 projection, and sec 19 manifest. CLAUDE.md sec 7 names provenance.rulesApplied as load-bearing. Critic confirmed and intensified: two normative documents specify mutually inconsistent kernel I/O contracts; implementers cannot satisfy both without arbitrary reconciliation.",
