          {
            "id": "I17",
            "title": "Project TBox inline-in-canonical-jsonld relationship undefined; sec 5.14 'at user's request' inlining breaks NFR-013 cross-implementation byte-identity",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "merge",
            "severity": "minor",
            "rationale": "Reviewer's F17 raised the TBox / canonical-bytes relationship as undefined. Critic narrowed and corrected the impact: sec 6.3 step 5:732 explicitly mandates prepending TBox declarations on semantic export, so semantic JSON-LD, Turtle, and N-Triples exports always include the TBox and NFR-013 is verifiable for them. The actual undefined surface is the canonical project.jsonld: sec 5.14:597 permits implementations to inline TBox 'at the user's request' while sec 5.3:327-336 makes no provision for inline TBox in the canonical document. An implementation that honors the user request produces a canonically-valid file that another implementation cannot reproduce without the same request. NFR-012 holds; NFR-013 does not for projects with user-requested inline TBox. Merged into critic's narrower framing.",
            "trace": {
              "reviewer_finding_id": "F17",
              "critic_verdict_id": "F17"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I18",
