            "raw_stdout": "```json\n{\n  \"outputs\": {\n    \"issues\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"I1\",\n        \"title\": \"Version-label incoherence: header declares v0.4 while \u00c2\u00a73.1, \u00c2\u00a73.2, \u00c2\u00a721, \u00c2\u00a722 remain scoped to v0.3\",\n        \"consensus\": \"both_agree\",\n        \"resolution\": \"accept_reviewer\",\n        \"severity\": \"blocking\",\n        \"rationale\": \"Critic confirmed verbatim with additional line-level evidence (SPEC.md:1762 DoD heading). No material scope extension; the reviewer's finding and fix prescription are sufficient. The blocking conformance gap \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a v0.4 implementer cannot determine which scope/MVP/test-strategy sections apply \u00e2\u20ac\u201d is undisputed.\",\n        \"trace\": { \"reviewer_finding_id\": \"F1\", \"critic_verdict_id\": \"F1\" }\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"I2\",\n        \"title\": \"Severity taxonomy contradiction: LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER is 'info' yet blocks export\",\n        \"consensus\": \"both_agree\",\n        \"resolution\": \"accept_reviewer\",\n        \"severity\": \"blocking\",\n        \"rationale\": \"Critic confirmed with verbatim citation of all four conflicting clauses (\u00c2\u00a717.1, \u00c2\u00a717.4, \u00c2\u00a710.4, \u00c2\u00a75.4.1). The three-level severity contract is broken: an 'informational-only' finding blocks export unconditionally. Downstream tooling cannot determine blocking behavior from severity alone. No refutation or material extension was offered.\",\n        \"trace\": { \"reviewer_finding_id\": \"F2\", \"critic_verdict_id\": \"F2\" }\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"I3\",\n        \"title\": \"v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 migration is normatively required but no FR-C identifier gates it\",\n        \"consensus\": \"both_agree\",\n        \"resolution\": \"merge\",\n        \"severity\": \"blocking\",\n        \"rationale\": \"Critic confirmed and extended: not only is the v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 leg uncovered by any FR-C, but FR-C013's own description still references 'v0.3' as the migration target inside a v0.4 spec, meaning even the v0.2\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 chain lacks a valid acceptance criterion against the actual version. The merged issue encompasses both the missing FR-C for the v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 leg and the stale target version in FR-C013.\",\n        \"trace\": { \"reviewer_finding_id\": \"F3\", \"critic_verdict_id\": \"F3\" }\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"I4\",\n        \"title\": \"iao:OntologyDesignPattern minted under OBO IAO namespace without authority\",\n        \"consensus\": \"both_agree\",\n        \"resolution\": \"merge\",\n        \"severity\": \"blocking\",\n        \"rationale\": \"Critic confirmed and flagged that the structural fix prescribed by the reviewer (mint under ecm: or coordinate with IAO) is necessary but not sufficient without also resolving M1 (see I10). The namespace hijacking means linked-data consumers dereferencing http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/iao#OntologyDesignPattern will get a 404 or unrelated term. The blocking severity is correct. Merged scope: the iao: binding problem is broader than OntologyDesignPattern alone (see I10 for the iao:isAbout dimension).\",\n        \"trace\": { \"reviewer_finding_id\": \"F4\", \"critic_verdict_id\": \"F4\" }\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"I5\",\n        \"title\": \"UUIDv5 namespace UUID and operation-context canonical encoding are unspecified; NFR-013 is unverifiable in deterministic mode\",\n        \"consensus\": \"both_agree\",\n        \"resolution\": \"accept_reviewer\",\n        \"severity\": \"blocking\",\n        \"rationale\": \"Critic confirmed against RFC 4122 \u00c2\u00a74.3. Neither the namespace UUID nor the canonical serialization of 'operation context' fields (which fields, what order, what byte encoding) is defined anywhere in the spec. Two RFC-conformant implementations will produce different UUIDs from the same seed. NFR-013 byte-identicality is unachievable in ecm:deterministic mode.\",\n        \"trace\": { \"reviewer_finding_id\": \"F5\", \"critic_verdict_id\": \"F5\" }\n      },\n      {\n        \"id\": \"I6\",\n        \"title\": \"SPEC \u00c2\u00a74.1 five-layer model is unreconciled with ARCHITECTURE.md/CLAUDE.md three-layer model enforced by npm run test:purity\",\n        \"consensus\": \"both_agree\",\n        \"resolution\": \"accept_reviewer\",\n        \"seve"
          },
