              "critic_verdict_id": "F2"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I3",
            "title": "Phase 6 DoD verification of \u00c2\u00a731 item 14 (byte-identical outputs across two implementations) is unexecutable \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no second implementation is scheduled anywhere in the ROADMAP",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "accept_reviewer",
            "severity": "major",
            "rationale": "Phase 6 scope explicitly states: 'Final v0.4 Definition of Done verification per \u00c2\u00a731: \u00e2\u20ac\u00a6 byte-identical golden suite green across two independent implementations.' SPEC \u00c2\u00a731 item 14 requires two compliant implementations to produce byte-identical canonical and derived artifacts for conformance fixtures. No phase in the ROADMAP \u00e2\u20ac\u201d neither the six numbered phases nor the Cross-Cutting Commitments \u00e2\u20ac\u201d schedules, scopes, staffs, or names the creation of a second implementation. The Cross-Cutting Commitments Determinism bullet states the normative property but delivers nothing to make it verifiable. Phase 6's DoD verification step for item 14 is aspirational rather than executable on the ROADMAP as written. The critic confirmed this without material extension. The source artifact confirms both the Phase 6 scope line and the absence of a second-implementation deliverable.",
            "trace": {
              "reviewer_finding_id": "F3",
              "critic_verdict_id": "F3"
