          },
          {
            "id": "I4",
            "title": "Cross-Cutting Commitments silently drop NFR-007 through NFR-012, narrowing the binding invariant set beyond what the SPEC authorizes",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "accept_reviewer",
            "severity": "major",
            "rationale": "The ROADMAP's Cross-Cutting Commitments enumerate NFR-014, NFR-001/002, NFR-003/013, NFR-005, NFR-006, and NFR-004 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d six bullets covering eight NFRs. NFR-007 (no lock-in / open formats), NFR-008 (UI explains semantic modeling), NFR-009 (UI exposes IRIs/RDF/terms/triples), NFR-010 (canvas prioritizes understandable modeling), NFR-011 (performance bounds per \u00c2\u00a714.2/14.3), and NFR-012 (lossless canonical round-trip per \u00c2\u00a75.3, \u00c2\u00a76.4) are absent. The critic confirmed and prioritized: NFR-012 is the most critical omission \u00e2\u20ac\u201d it is a determinism-adjacent invariant constraining every phase that touches the canonical project document, yet it is absent while the adjacent Determinism bullet is present. NFR-011 binds Phase 3 (50 MB hard limit, 10,000-term threshold) and Phase 5 (large-project persistence). NFR-007 constrains every export-format choice in Phase 4. Their absence from the cross-cutting set allows phases to appear 'done' while silently dropping these requirements. The source artifact confirms the Cross-Cutting Commitments enumeration exactly as reported.",
            "trace": {
              "reviewer_finding_id": "F4",
              "critic_verdict_id": "F4"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I5",
            "title": "Phase 5 schedules IndexedDB adapter implementation alongside unresolved OED-302 (schema versioning), inverting the dependency",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "accept_reviewer",
            "severity": "major",
            "rationale": "Phase 5 scope includes 'IndexedDB adapter with lossless canonical-document storage and recent-projects project picker (FR-S003\u00e2\u20ac\u201cFR-S004).' Phase 5 Decisions Deferred includes 'OED-302 (IndexedDB schema versioning). How IndexedDB schema migrations are coordinated with ecm:specVersion bumps.' The IndexedDB schema version number, object-store layout, index structure, versionchange event handler shape, upgrade callback logic, and keyspace are all determined by the schema versioning decision. Building the adapter before resolving OED-302 inverts this dependency. The ROADMAP contains no gate requiring OED-302 closure before IndexedDB implementation begins. The critic confirmed this and added the specific implementation elements affected (upgrade callbacks, keyspace). The source artifact confirms both the Phase 5 scope line and the co-located deferred decision.",
            "trace": {
