          },
          {
            "id": "I12",
            "title": "Phase dependencies are implied by linear ordering with no DAG; valid concurrency opportunities are hidden and the critical path is inflated",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "merge",
            "severity": "minor",
            "rationale": "The ROADMAP presents Phases 1\u00e2\u20ac\u201c6 in linear order with no 'depends_on' field or DAG annotation. The reviewer identified the structural gap; the critic materially extended it with a specific independence analysis: Phase 4 (Export and Packaging) requires Phase 1 emitters and Phase 2 browser UI shell, but not Phase 3 (Ontology Import) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the Phase 4 scope contains no import-dependent features. Phase 5 (Local Persistence Adapters) requires Phase 2 (browser UI shell) but is independent of Phase 3 and Phase 4 for most of its scope, since persistence adapters wrap the canonical document and do not require export-format browser flows or ontology import. The linear presentation hides these independencies and encourages strict serial execution, inflating the critical path. SPEC \u00c2\u00a729 has the same linear shape; the ROADMAP missed the opportunity to refine it with dependency declarations.",
