          {
            "id": "I14",
            "title": "ROADMAP does not bind any phase to the SPEC \u00c2\u00a730 risk register, allowing phases to declare themselves done without verifying their risk mitigations",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "accept_reviewer",
            "severity": "advisory",
            "rationale": "SPEC \u00c2\u00a730 lists nine risks with named mitigations; several reference specific phases (Risk 2 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Phase 3 mitigations: named-term extraction, 50 MB limit, degraded mode; Risk 4 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Phase 1 mitigations: constrained VMP, bundled context; Risk 7/8 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Phase 1 and Phase 6). The ROADMAP contains no risk register and no per-phase risk acknowledgement. The critic confirmed and extended with specific risk-to-phase mappings: Risk 4 (JSON-LD complexity) maps to Phase 1 (constrained VMP, bundled context); Risk 8 (determinism claims) maps to Phase 1 (CI job per \u00c2\u00a721.4); Risk 2 (browser crashes on large ontologies) maps to Phase 3. Without per-phase risk acknowledgements in the ROADMAP, a phase can declare itself complete without verifying its mitigations are implemented.",
            "trace": {
              "reviewer_finding_id": "F14",
              "critic_verdict_id": "F14"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I15",
            "title": "'Prepended to semantic JSON-LD exports' is operationally imprecise \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the ROADMAP faithfully inherits this defect from SPEC \u00c2\u00a76.3 step 5 and \u00c2\u00a731 DoD item 2",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "merge",
            "severity": "advisory",
            "rationale": "The reviewer correctly identified that 'prepend' is well-defined for Turtle/N-Triples (TBox triples emitted before ABox triples in the same file) but operationally ambiguous for JSON-LD, where the analogous operation is inclusion of TBox node objects in @graph. The critic extended this materially: the ROADMAP's Phase 1 scope line ('prepended to Turtle / N-Triples / semantic JSON-LD exports') faithfully reproduces SPEC \u00c2\u00a76.3 step 5 ('Prepend the Project TBox declarations from \u00c2\u00a75.14 to the resulting RDF graph' \u00e2\u20ac\u201d applied to the semantic JSON-LD export algorithm) and SPEC \u00c2\u00a731 DoD item 2 ('prepended to all semantic exports'). The imprecision is therefore a SPEC defect that the ROADMAP inherits, not a ROADMAP-specific deviation. The ROADMAP cannot be corrected in isolation; any fix requires the SPEC to distinguish file-level prepend (Turtle/N-Triples) from graph-level TBox node insertion (JSON-LD). Advisory severity is confirmed as appropriate. The source artifact confirms the Phase 1 scope line at line 32.",
            "trace": {
              "reviewer_finding_id": "F15",
              "critic_verdict_id": "F15"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I16",
