        "open_questions": [
          "OED-307 (CLI stub strategy): What is the intended Phase 1 behavior for 'import-ontology' and 'export --format zip'? Options are (a) registered stubs returning exit code 2 with an explicit 'not available until Phase N' message, or (b) commands left unregistered until their phase ships. This must be decided before Phase 1 CLI integration tests are authored and must be reflected in IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md acceptance criteria.",
          "OED-303 elevation: This proposal documents the Phase 1 empty-ecm:validationReports assumption as a temporary constraint pending OED-303. An alternative resolution is to formally elevate OED-303 to Phase 1 as the owning phase, requiring it to close before Phase 1 goldens are committed. The Human Orchestrator must confirm which approach is preferred.",
          "Second implementation (\u00c2\u00a731 item 14): The proposal registers this as an open decision in Phase 6 Decisions Deferred. The Human Orchestrator must choose one of: (a) scope a second implementation workstream, (b) relax \u00c2\u00a731 item 14 for v0.4 with a SPEC amendment, or (c) formally defer \u00c2\u00a731 item 14 to post-v0.4. This decision gates Phase 6.",
          "OED numbers 306\u00e2\u20ac\u201c312 are newly assigned by this proposal. The Human Orchestrator must confirm these identifiers do not conflict with any OEDs registered outside the ROADMAP (e.g., in SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a729 or in planning documents not reviewed here). SPEC.md currently lists OED-301 through OED-305 only.",
          "Phase Dependency Map: The map asserts Phase 4 is fully independent of Phase 3 and Phase 5 is fully independent of Phase 3 and Phase 4 for core scope. The Human Orchestrator should validate this analysis \u00e2\u20ac\u201d particularly that no Phase 5 persistence feature depends on Phase 4 export-format browser flows (e.g., if the FSA adapter must trigger a download as part of its save flow).",
          "IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md: No specific phase has been assigned to author this document. The Human Orchestrator must decide when it is created, by whom, and whether it is a prerequisite gate for Phase 1 kickoff or a parallel deliverable.",
          "SPEC \u00c2\u00a76.3 / \u00c2\u00a731 item 2 'prepend' imprecision (I15): The note added in C3 flags a SPEC-level defect inherited by the ROADMAP. Should a separate Barcode task be queued to route a SPEC-level clarification through the semantic-sme agent before Phase 1 golden files for the semantic JSON-LD emitter are committed?"
        ],
        "summary": "15 targeted changes to project/ROADMAP.md addressing all 18 synthesist issues. Major structural additions: (1) Cross-Cutting Commitments expanded with NFR-007 through NFR-012, \u00c2\u00a710 versioning obligation, golden-file governance policy, and \u00c2\u00a730 risk-register binding \u00e2\u20ac\u201d eliminating the silent NFR drop identified in I4/I9/I17/I14. (2) Phase 1 CLI self-contradiction resolved by limiting Phase 1 export to non-ZIP formats and adding OED-307 for the stub strategy decision (I16). (3) Phase 1 golden-file scope disambiguated across three phases: Phase 1 covers canonical JSON-LD and emitter format outputs for OED-306 fixtures; Phase 4 adds manifest.jsonld and ZIP goldens; Phase 6 adds per-starter goldens (I1). (4) OED-303 empty-array assumption documented in Phase 1 Decisions Deferred with a cross-reference from Phase 3 that binds OED-303 resolution to retrospective rulings on Phase 1 and Phase 2 (I2/I10). (5) Phase 5 Decisions Deferred expanded from 1 OED to 5 OEDs \u00e2\u20ac\u201d adding OED-308 through OED-311 for the four most critical FSA sub-decisions \u00e2\u20ac\u201d and an explicit gate requiring OED-302 closure before IndexedDB implementation begins (I5/I18). (6) Phase 6 renamed from 'Edge Canonical Bridge' to 'Onboarding Content, Semantic Linting, and v0.4 DoD Verification' (I7). (7) Phase 6 heuristic findings scoped against \u00c2\u00a717.4 enumeration, \u00c2\u00a75.13 required fields, and OED-312 (I6). (8) Phase 6 DoD \u00c2\u00a731 item 14 qualified as aspirational pending a second-implementation decision registered in Phase 6 Decisions Deferred (I3). (9) Phase Dependency Map section added documenting Phase 4 independence from Phase 3 and Phase 5 independence from Phase 3 and Phase 4 (I12). Minor/advisory changes: Turtle parser parenthetical removed (I8); TBox prepend imprecision flagged as inherited SPEC defect (I15); OED-306 identifier assigned to conformance fixture set (I13); IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md prerequisite noted in header (I11). Seven open decisions remain and are surfaced in open_questions for Human Orchestrator resolution before Phase 1 begins.",
        "self_assessment": "needs_review"
      },
