      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:052-recon-vmp-serializer",
      "agent": "reconnaissance",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "findings": [
          {
            "id": "F1",
            "claim": "src/kernel/canonicalize.ts exports stableStringify(value, pretty) implementing only alphabetical key sorting \u00e2\u20ac\u201d it does NOT implement the \u00c2\u00a75.3 rule 2 top-level key priority ordering (`@context`, `id`, `type`, `ecm:specVersion` first).",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/kernel/canonicalize.ts",
                "lines": "21-38",
                "excerpt": "const keys = Object.keys(obj).sort();\nconst sorted: Record<string, unknown> = {};\nfor (const key of keys) {\n  sorted[key] = canonicalize(obj[key]);\n}"
              },
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "330",
                "excerpt": "2. Order top-level keys: `@context`, `id`, `type`, `ecm:specVersion`, then all other keys alphabetically."
              },
              {
                "file": "project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md",
                "lines": "34",
                "excerpt": "- Emit top-level key order: `@context`, `id`, `type`, `ecm:specVersion`, then remaining keys alphabetically (\u00c2\u00a75.3 rule 2)."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F2",
            "claim": "stableStringify preserves array element order as-is and does not implement \u00c2\u00a75.3 rule 4 (sort named arrays by element `id`) or rule 5 (sort IRI arrays lexicographically).",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/kernel/canonicalize.ts",
                "lines": "26-28",
                "excerpt": "if (Array.isArray(value)) {\n  return value.map(canonicalize);\n}"
              },
              {
                "file": "src/kernel/canonicalize.ts",
                "lines": "18-20",
                "excerpt": "* Arrays are preserved in their original order (caller is responsible\n * for ensuring semantic ordering if needed)."
              },
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "332-333",
                "excerpt": "4. Order array elements of `ecm:terms`, `ecm:instances`, `ecm:relations`, `ecm:literalAssertions`, `ecm:ontologies`, `ecm:layouts`, `ecm:snapshots`, `ecm:serializations` by their `id` (lexicographically).\n5. Order IRI arrays (`ecm:classIris`, `iao:isAbout`, `rdfs:subClassOf`, `rdfs:subPropertyOf`) lexicographically."
              },
              {
                "file": "project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md",
                "lines": "35-37",
