          "  - Three-character sequence visible as a-with-circumflex followed by Euro-sign followed by double-quote should become the em-dash character (Unicode codepoint U+2014).",
          "  - Three-character sequence visible as a-with-circumflex followed by dagger followed by single-quote should become the rightwards arrow character (Unicode codepoint U+2192).",
          "STEP 3: For EACH mojibake instance (or group of nearby instances), emit ONE change with mode=edit. The before field MUST contain the mojibake-bearing substring EXACTLY as your Read tool sees it (so the applier finds it on disk). The after field MUST contain the same substring with the mojibake replaced by the proper Unicode character.",
          "STEP 4: CRITICAL output-encoding constraint. To avoid re-introducing mojibake in your own JSON output, emit non-ASCII characters in your before and after fields using the JSON Unicode-escape syntax. Examples: the section sign is \\u00a7; the em-dash is \\u2014; the rightwards arrow is \\u2192. Do not emit the raw non-ASCII bytes in your JSON output anywhere.",
          "STEP 5: For the before field specifically, the mojibake characters need to be written as their decoded codepoints. The two-character mojibake for the section sign decodes as codepoint U+00C2 followed by codepoint U+00A7; write this as \\u00c2\\u00a7. The em-dash mojibake decodes as three codepoints which you should write as \\u00e2\\u20ac\\u201c (these are the three Unicode codepoints that the Read tool produces when decoding the mojibake bytes as UTF-8). The arrow mojibake similarly: \\u00e2\\u2020\\u2019.",
          "STEP 6: Make each before snippet large enough to be UNIQUE in the file. Include 10-20 characters of surrounding context. The applier requires exactly-one match per before field; non-unique snippets fail with before_not_unique.",
          "STEP 7: Do NOT modify any TypeScript expressions, function bodies, control flow, or exported symbol shapes. Comments only. If you cannot reduce the change to comment-text replacement, emit an error rather than modifying runtime code.",
