        "summary": "Reconnaissance for Phase 1 task 1.3 (Structural Validator) reveals a well-specified but entirely unimplemented target. SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a717.2\u00e2\u20ac\u201c\u00c2\u00a717.4 fully enumerates all 26 finding codes (16 hard errors, 7 warnings, 3 info) with descriptions; \u00c2\u00a75.13 defines the ValidationReport/ValidationFinding JSON-LD shape with five required finding fields. Tasks 1.1 and 1.2 are complete (src/kernel/canonicalize.ts and src/tbox/index.ts both present with tests), but no validator module exists anywhere in src/ and no test fixtures directory exists. Two open OED gates are directly relevant: OED-303 (validation report retention policy, Phase 1 exit gate per ADR-004) governs the `ecm:validationReports` array shape in golden files; OED-313 (conformance fixture set scope, Phase 1+4 joint exit gate per ADR-005) blocks all golden-file commits. The existing tbox-bundle.test.ts provides a clear precedent for stubbing OED-gated ACs without failing dispatch. Three structural tensions require operator resolution before or alongside developer dispatch: (1) module location for validate() \u00e2\u20ac\u201d src/kernel/ vs src/validate/ \u00e2\u20ac\u201d is unresolved with no governing ADR; (2) STALE_SAVE_TARGET warning requires filesystem/concurrency context that a pure-kernel function cannot access without a parameter extension; (3) LARGE_IMPORT and DANGLING_INSTANCE_CLASS_REF reference imported ontologies (Phase 3 scope) and need explicit Phase 1 handling decisions (stub/skip/empty-check). No coverage tooling (c8, nyc, etc.) exists in package.json; the \u00c2\u00a721.2 coverage AC is CI-deferred and follows the same deferral pattern as property-based tests. Scope-splitting is a real risk: 26 codes \u00c3\u2014 per-code fixture + validate() types + test harness is likely 600\u00e2\u20ac\u201c900 lines of developer output, potentially warranting sub-chain decomposition by finding category (project-level checks, structural entity checks, cross-reference dangling checks, warnings, info).",
