        "open_questions": [
          "Should validate() live in src/kernel/validate.ts (part of the core kernel layer, subject to purity constraints and the \u00c2\u00a721.2 'core layer' coverage target) or in a new src/validate/ module analogous to src/tbox/ (separate module, potentially allowing impure parameters for STALE_SAVE_TARGET)?",
          "How should STALE_SAVE_TARGET (a \u00c2\u00a711.2 filesystem-concurrency concern) be implemented inside a pure kernel validate() function? Options observed: (a) accept an optional `loadedAt: string` parameter and only emit the finding when caller provides it, (b) always-omit in Phase 1 with a stub/TODO, (c) scope STALE_SAVE_TARGET to an orchestration layer rather than the kernel validator.",
          "How should LARGE_IMPORT and DANGLING_INSTANCE_CLASS_REF (which reference imported ontologies, a Phase 3 scope) be handled in the Phase 1 validator? Options: (a) treat as always-empty-pass when ecm:ontologies is empty, (b) stub the checks with explicit Phase 3 TODO comments, (c) implement the 'project-terms-only' variant of DANGLING_INSTANCE_CLASS_REF now and extend in Phase 3.",
          "Is the \u00c2\u00a721.2 \u00e2\u2030\u00a585% branch coverage AC for the validator deferrable to CI setup (adding c8 as a devDependency in a separate task) using the same OED-gating-stub pattern established in tbox-bundle.test.ts, or must this dispatch ship coverage tooling?",
          "Should the developer dispatch for task 1.3 be scope-split into sub-tasks by finding category (e.g., project-level checks + types in one dispatch; structural entity checks in a second; cross-reference dangling checks + warnings + info in a third) given the 26-code + 16-fixture + validate() implementation surface?"
        ],
