          "Coverage AC (section 21.2, >= 85% branch): deferred per AC-coverage stub. The reconnaissance confirmed no c8/nyc in package.json devDependencies and no CI configuration. If the operator wants to ship coverage tooling in this same dispatch chain, propose adding c8 as a devDependency with an npm run test:coverage script in a follow-up change. The scope_strategy_hint recommended deferral; this proposal follows that recommendation.",
          "Follow-up chain sequencing: remaining 24 codes split into three natural groups -- (A) project-level structural checks: MISSING_PROJECT_ID, MISSING_PROJECT_NAME, MALFORMED_TERM, MALFORMED_INSTANCE, MALFORMED_RELATION, MALFORMED_LITERAL_ASSERTION, MALFORMED_SERIALIZATION_ENTRY, DUPLICATE_IRI; (B) cross-reference dangling checks: DANGLING_RELATION_SUBJECT_REF, DANGLING_RELATION_OBJECT_REF, DANGLING_RELATION_PREDICATE_REF, DANGLING_LITERAL_SUBJECT_REF, DANGLING_LITERAL_PREDICATE_REF, DANGLING_INSTANCE_CLASS_REF (project-terms variant); (C) warnings + info: DUPLICATE_TRIPLE, DISCONNECTED_INSTANCE, INSTANCE_WITHOUT_CLASS, TERM_WITHOUT_LABEL, LITERAL_DATATYPE_MISMATCH, LEGACY_DOCUMENT_MIGRATED, LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER, NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE. STALE_SAVE_TARGET and LARGE_IMPORT remain deferred to task 5.7 and Phase 3 respectively."
