      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal introduces a new validator module (src/validate/), new TypeScript types (ValidationReport, ValidationFinding, ValidationSeverity), two implemented validation-code detection paths, a new test file, and all-code file additions \u00e2\u20ac\u201d well beyond editorial-correction scope of typo/formatting/terminology-tightening.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance (093) is present in UPSTREAM; the refusal contract is not triggered. The proposal is evaluated against each review_focus criterion:\n\n**Reconciliation with reconnaissance findings:** All 21 recon findings are addressed or explicitly acknowledged. F6/F13 (no validator, unresolved module location) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 resolved via src/validate/ placement per task inputs scope_constraints. F8/F20 (no fixture directory; OED-313 gating) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C3 stubs AC-fixture per the tbox-bundle.test.ts precedent (F10). F9 (no coverage tooling) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C3 stubs AC-coverage with explicit c8/nyc rationale. F15 (STALE_SAVE_TARGET pure-kernel tension) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 deferred to task 5.7 with inline documentation in both codes.ts and index.ts. F16 (LARGE_IMPORT/DANGLING_INSTANCE_CLASS_REF Phase 3 scope) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 LARGE_IMPORT deferred to Phase 3/task 3.3; DANGLING_INSTANCE_CLASS_REF phase-split noted (project-terms variant in follow-up chain B; imported-ontology variant Phase 3). F11/F12 (OED-303/OED-313 gates) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 documented and respected. Partial gap: F14 (no ADR for validator architecture decisions) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the module placement decision was resolved by task inputs scope_constraints rather than a formal ADR. No ADR was authored for src/validate/ vs src/kernel/, STALE_SAVE_TARGET handling, or Phase-3-scoped checks in Phase 1. This is a documentation-debt gap, not a blocking defect.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.13 conformance:** The ValidationFinding interface declares all five required finding fields (ecm:severity, ecm:code, ecm:message, ecm:target, ecm:acknowledged) plus the required type discriminator. The ValidationReport interface declares id, type, ecm:createdAt, ecm:findings. The stub id (urn:ecm:report:phase1-stub) and ecm:createdAt (1970-01-01T00:00:00Z) are Phase 1 placeholders correctly deferred to task 1.6 (IRI generation); the developer's open question #3 correctly flags the static-id collision risk pending OED-303 resolution. Type-level conformance is complete.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a717.2/17.3/17.4 coverage \u00e2\u20ac\u201d scope-split:** This dispatch implements 2 of 26 SPEC-declared codes (MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR + INVALID_SPEC_VERSION). The remaining 24 codes are fully accounted for across follow-up chains A (8 project-level structural errors), B (6 dangling cross-reference errors), C (5 warnings + 3 info codes), and task-specific deferrals (STALE_SAVE_TARGET \u00e2\u2020\u2019 task 5.7; LARGE_IMPORT \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Phase 3; LEGACY_* \u00e2\u2020\u2019 task 1.9; NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE \u00e2\u2020\u2019 task 1.10). The 2 + 8 + 6 + 8 + 2 = 26 total matches the SPEC \u00c2\u00a717.2-17.4 enumeration exactly. The scope-split is documented with sufficient specificity; sub-chain commitments are captured in developer open_questions. Recon F21 justified the split (600\u00e2\u20ac\u201c900 line output budget risk). The follow-up chain commitments are in open_questions, not yet formalized as state.jsonld tasks \u00e2\u20ac\u201d operator should queue chains A/B/C before declaring task 1.3 complete.\n\n**Per-AC coverage:** AC1 (per-code malformed fixtures) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 stubbed per OED-313 gating, following established precedent. AC2 (fully valid v0.4 project \u00e2\u2020\u2019 empty findings) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 AC-valid test verified with VALID_V04 fixture. AC3 (MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR positive+negative \u00e2\u20ac\u201d two separate tests) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 AC-anchor1 (fires for placeholder-only), AC-anchor2 (does not fire for real IRI), plus three additional edge cases (absent, empty array, mixed). AC4 (INVALID_SPEC_VERSION fires for '0.5') \u00e2\u2020\u2019 AC-version tests cover fires-for-0.5, fires-for-absent, fires-for-malformed, no-fire-for-0.4, no-fire-for-0.3. AC5 (\u00e2\u2030\u00a585% branch coverage) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 stubbed per AC-coverage deferral with explicit c8/nyc rationale. AC6 (all \u00c2\u00a75.13 fields present in every finding) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 AC-schema test checks all 5 required fields + type discriminator + severity enum + acknowledged=false. All 6 ACs are either verified or properly stubbed. The IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.3 sub-tasks name MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR and INVALID_SPEC_VERSION specifically; this dispatch satisfies those named sub-tasks plus the AC machinery needed to frame the remaining chains.\n\n**Coverage AC handling:** Deferred to CI tooling addition. The deferral is consistent with the tbox-bundle.test.ts pattern (OED-313 gating stub) and with the recon finding F9 that confirmed no c8/nyc in package.json devDependencies and no CI configuration. Deferral is accepted.\n\n**Kernel purity:** C2 (src/validate/index.ts) contains no Date.now(), new Date(), Math.random(), I/O calls (readFile, fetch, XMLHttpRequest), or process.env references. The report id and ecm:createdAt are stub literals. The function signature is Record<string, unknown> \u00e2\u2020\u2019 ValidationReport with no async surface. Purity is confirmed by inspection. Structural caveat: the kernel purity checker (ensure-kernel-purity.ts) scans only dist-tests/src/kernel/; src/validate/ is outside its scope, meaning purity of src/validate/ is enforced by discipline only. The current implementation is clean; the enforcement gap is a forward-track concern, not a ratification blocker.\n\n**Layer boundaries:** C2 imports only from ./codes.js (same module). No imports from src/adapters/ or src/composition/. Placement in src/validate/ (analogous to src/tbox/) is architecturally coherent: it permits future cross-module imports from src/tbox/ (e.g., the ECM_UNSPECIFIED constant per recon F19) without violating the kernel purity checker, which is scoped to src/kernel/. The developer chose to hard-code ECM_UNSPECIFIED as a string literal in C2 rather than import from src/tbox/; this is acceptable and avoids an inter-module dependency.\n\n**DevDep additions:** None. No new runtime or devDependencies added. Coverage tooling deferred to a separate follow-up task.\n\n**tsconfig/test-discovery compatibility:** tsconfig.json include: src/**/* picks up src/validate/ automatically. tsconfig.test.json include: src/**/*,tests/**/* picks up both src/validate/ and the new test file. run-tests.ts discovers *.test.js by glob in dist-tests/tests/; structural-validator.test.ts compiles to dist-tests/tests/structural-validator.test.js and will be auto-discovered. Import path ../src/validate/index.js from tests/ resolves correctly under tsconfig.test.json rootDir:'.'. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**Summary verdict:** The proposal correctly executes a scope-split sanctioned by recon F21, delivers the two explicitly named IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.3 codes, satisfies all 6 ACs (fully or with OED-gated stubs), maintains \u00c2\u00a75.13 type conformance, respects purity and layer constraints, and documents all 24 remaining codes with explicit follow-up chain assignments. The ADR gap (F14) is a discipline debt the operator should address, but it is not a blocking defect \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the decision was made by task inputs scope_constraints, which provides traceability. The static stub id collision risk (open question #3) is correctly deferred to OED-303. Ratification is granted with the condition that chains A, B, C are queued as follow-up tasks before task 1.3 is declared complete, and that the MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR vs LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER ambiguity (open question #1) is resolved before task 1.9 is dispatched.",
