        "summary": "Phase 1 task 1.4 (Semantic Projection / Editor-Layer Stripping) has not yet been implemented: no `projectSemantic()` function exists anywhere in `src/`, and no TypeScript test file for semantic projection exists in `tests/`. The two declared dependencies for task 1.4 are fully implemented: `serializeVmp` (task 1.1, `src/kernel/canonicalize.ts`) and `getProjectTBoxNodes()` / `getProjectTBoxTurtle()` (task 1.2, `src/tbox/index.ts`). Two normative tensions in the SPEC bear on the implementation: (1) SPEC \u00c2\u00a76.1's predicate allowlist omits `ecm:name` but \u00c2\u00a76.2 prose names it as a Semantic Layer field on the project root \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a question a strict-allowlist implementation of `projectSemantic` must resolve; (2) SPEC \u00c2\u00a78.3 discards `rdfs:label` from relation assertions even though `rdfs:label` is in the \u00c2\u00a76.1 predicate allowlist, making the per-entity discard rule for relations narrower than the general allowlist. The IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.4 AC3 property-based test (canvas-layout-invariance, \u00e2\u2030\u00a550 samples) requires a property-based test library; `fast-check` is absent from `package.json` devDependencies and its addition is explicitly noted as deferred pending Human Orchestrator approval, with the existing test pattern being hand-rolled (`node:assert`, process-isolation runner). A tracked ambiguity in IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.5 (SPEC \u00c2\u00a76.3 step 5 'prepend' vs \u00c2\u00a731 '@graph' insertion) is resolved by implementation assumption as TBox-as-@graph-node-objects; this applies to task 1.5 but the TBox integration in task 1.4 step 5 is subject to the same question. The `getProjectTBoxNodes()` source carries a code comment flagging that `rdfs:domain`/`rdfs:range` compact IRIs require supplemental VMP_CONTEXT entries for full expansion \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a noted gap for task 1.4 to address. The `DUPLICATE_TRIPLE` validation code (corresponding to \u00c2\u00a78.2's save-time warning) is not yet implemented in `src/validate/index.ts`, deferred to follow-up chain C; this does not block `projectSemantic` itself but affects the validate-before-export workflow.",
