        "bankings": [
          {
            "id": "B1",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "The seeded Mulberry32 PRNG pattern (pure arithmetic, no external dependency, fixed seed producing deterministic samples) is established in this task as the approved technique for hand-rolled property-based tests in the GraphWrite test suite. The pattern satisfies IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN '\u00e2\u2030\u00a550 samples' AC language without requiring fast-check as a devDependency, and is consistent with the zero-external-dependency ethos of the kernel. Future property-based ACs (cascade reversibility, cascade idempotency, canonical idempotency per IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.12) should follow this same pattern unless the Human Orchestrator explicitly approves fast-check."
          },
          {
            "id": "B2",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "The `src/projection/` module placement \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a sibling directory to `src/tbox/` and `src/validate/`, importing from `src/kernel/` and `src/tbox/` but not from `src/adapters/` or `src/composition/` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d establishes the canonical location pattern for domain-function modules that apply kernel primitives without constituting kernel-layer code. This is distinct from the three-layer boundary enforced by `npm run test:purity`, which targets `src/kernel/` isolation only. Future semantic-export pipeline modules (task 1.5 emitters) should follow this placement pattern."
          }
        ]
      },
