        "summary": "Task 1.5 (emitters) has zero implementation in the codebase: no src/emit/ directory or files exist. The upstream dependencies are fully in place: src/projection/index.ts exports projectSemantic() which already implements FR-C005 (Semantic JSON-LD) completely \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the emitter wrapper for that format is trivial. src/tbox/index.ts provides getProjectTBoxTurtle() and getProjectTBoxNodes() for TBox prepending. The n3@1.21.0 devDependency is sufficient for Turtle (FR-C003) and N-Triples (FR-C004) serialization via N3.Writer, which is confirmed synchronous when not streaming. Markdown (FR-C007) and Triple Narration (FR-C008) require no external library and can be hand-rolled from VMP document arrays. Mermaid (FR-C006) is a structural stub per OED-301 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the implementation generates Mermaid DSL text directly (no Mermaid.js rendering library needed); the SPEC explicitly states Mermaid and Markdown use a simpler view of instances and relations only (not the TBox-inclusive semantic projection). Of the 7 ACs: AC1/AC2 (N3 parse validity), AC4 (Mermaid structural), AC5 (Markdown substring), AC6 (idempotency), and AC7 (TBox string search) are all testable without golden files. Only AC3 (byte-identical golden files) is blocked on OED-306 and OED-313 (both Open). Key open questions: (1) whether n3 should move from devDependencies to dependencies for emitter source files; (2) whether the ecm:classIris \u00e2\u2020\u2019 rdf:type triple expansion is handled inside the emitter or must be pre-processed before handing quads to N3.Writer; (3) whether ecm:name should be accessible to the Markdown emitter given the \u00c2\u00a76.1/\u00c2\u00a76.2 tension already noted in src/projection/index.ts. Scope-split assessment: the effective implementation surface is smaller than the nominal 5-emitter count suggests \u00e2\u20ac\u201d FR-C005 is already done, FR-C006 is a stub. A single chain can cover Turtle + N-Triples (N3-based) + Semantic JSON-LD (wrapper) + Mermaid (stub) + Markdown + Triple Narration (hand-rolled), with golden-file tests stubbed per OED gates.",
