        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "Changes C3 and C4 introduce a new runtime conditional branch (`!p.startsWith(\"_:\")`) that codifies behavior for blank-node predicate inputs \u00e2\u20ac\u201d changing from undefined/potentially-runtime-error behavior to defined silent-omission behavior \u00e2\u20ac\u201d which crosses the editorial boundary even though the guard is only exercised by structurally-invalid RDF inputs; C1, C2, and C5 are pure type-annotation corrections that would be editorial in isolation, but the bundled proposal is classified by its most-substantive constituent.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:108-recon-emitter-typefix) with comprehensive findings F1\u00e2\u20ac\u201cF16, satisfying the Pass 2a sequencing requirement. All five proposed changes are evaluated against the reconnaissance record:\n\n**C1 (Import Quad)**: Correct enabling change for C2/C5. `n3.Quad` is the concrete class that declares `implements RDF.Quad` (node_modules/@types/n3/index.d.ts:92\u00e2\u20ac\u201c100); importing it directly sidesteps the `ReturnType<typeof makeQuad>` last-overload inference problem identified in F7.\n\n**C2 (nodeToQuads return type)**: Directly addresses Root Cause B at `nodeToQuads`. The before-snippet matches turtle.ts:121\u00e2\u20ac\u201c122 exactly. Replacing `ReturnType<typeof makeQuad>[]` with `Quad[]` is analytically correct per F7/F9/F12: TypeScript's last-overload ReturnType inference resolves to the generic constraint (`BaseQuad`) not the default concrete type (`Quad`); the annotation was always misrepresenting the runtime type.\n\n**C3 (bare-triple predicate fix)**: Addresses Root Cause A at turtle.ts:131 (F4). Before-snippet matches lines 130\u00e2\u20ac\u201c132 exactly. The fix replaces `termForIri(p)` with `namedNode(expandIri(p))` guarded by `!p.startsWith(\"_:\")`. The guard is RDF-spec defensible: `Quad_Predicate = NamedNode | Variable` in both `@types/n3` (line 76) and `@rdfjs/types` (line 147) codifies the RDF specification constraint that blank nodes cannot be predicates. The test fixture at tests/emitters.test.ts uses only full-IRI predicates (PRED_IRI = `urn:uuid:...`), confirming that valid production inputs never trigger the new branch. The silent-omission behavior for blank-node predicates is defined and consistent with the defensive filtering pattern used elsewhere in the file (malformed entries silently skipped per the `graphToQuads` JSDoc).\n\n**C4 (LiteralAssertion predicate fix)**: Identical structural fix as C3 for turtle.ts:148\u00e2\u20ac\u201c157 (F5). Before-snippet matches exactly. Same defensibility arguments apply.\n\n**C5 (graphToQuads return type)**: Addresses Root Cause B at `graphToQuads` and transitively fixes both turtle.ts:259 and n-triples.ts:49 without modifying n-triples.ts. The before-snippet matches lines 230\u00e2\u20ac\u201c231 exactly. Since `n3.Quad` implements `RDF.Quad`, `Quad[]` is directly assignable to the `Writer.addQuads(RDF.Quad[])` parameter (confirmed by reconnaissance F11 which noted `n3.Quad` implements `RDF.Quad` while `n3.BaseQuad` does not).\n\n**Scope completeness**: All four cited type errors are resolved (F4 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C3; F5 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C4; F9/turtle.ts:259 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C5; F10/n-triples.ts:49 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C5). No additional predicate-position violations exist beyond lines 131 and 154 (F6/F14 confirmed). triple-narration.ts correctly untouched (F13).\n\n**Open questions do not block**: F16 (exact tsc error text unavailable) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the analytical grounding in F7 is internally consistent with the n3 type declarations and sufficient for ratification; the fix is correct regardless of exact error phrasing. The data model invariant question (F12 open question 3) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d blank-node predicates are structurally invalid per the RDF data model and per both type libraries; the filter is defensible with or without a formal spec-level guarantee.\n\n**Before-snippet fidelity**: All five `before` strings verified against source at expected lines. No divergence.\n\n**No canonical-doc mutations**: All changes target `src/emit/turtle.ts` (code artifact, not canonical-doc path); ADR-citation CPS check is not triggered.\n\nProposal is approved for Pass 2b execution.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
