        "summary": "Task 1.6 (IRI Generation) requires creating two new artifacts that do not yet exist: src/iri/index.ts (the generateIri module) and tests/iri-generation.test.ts (three in-scope ACs; AC4 deferred per OED-313). The proposed module location (src/iri/) is established by the chain definition file. No UUID npm package is needed: Node 22's built-in crypto.randomUUID() covers UUIDv4 and node:crypto createHash('sha1') supports a manual RFC 4122 \u00c2\u00a74.3 UUIDv5 implementation, both covered by the already-installed @types/node@^22.0.0 devDep without adding runtime dependencies. The kernel purity checker only enforces src/kernel/, so src/iri/ is outside its enforcement scope \u00e2\u20ac\u201d UUIDv4 non-determinism is SPEC-acknowledged and confined to the non-kernel module. Two gaps require architect attention: (1) SPEC \u00c2\u00a79.3 does not specify the UUIDv5 namespace UUID or the exact 'operation context' string format, leaving the RFC 4122 \u00c2\u00a74.3 implementation underspecified; (2) src/validate/index.ts has a stub with an inline comment attributing the wiring of report id/ecm:createdAt to task 1.6, but the developer task 114 scope_constraints prohibit modifying src/validate/* \u00e2\u20ac\u201d so either the wiring is a follow-up task not yet queued, or the constraint needs relaxation. No IRI-related ADRs exist in project/DECISIONS.md; a new ADR may be needed to ratify the UUID library decision and UUIDv5 namespace choice.",
