        "rationale": "Reconnaissance task 118 established all six errors precisely (F1\u00e2\u20ac\u201cF6, F9\u00e2\u20ac\u201cF13) and identified the shared root cause: providing a single explicit type argument to Array.from alongside a mapfn second argument restricts overload resolution to the 1-type-param overloads (each accepting exactly 1 argument), making mapfn a superfluous second argument (TS2554). TypeScript error-recovery then infers bytes as unknown[], cascading to TS2571 at lines 75/77 and TS18046 at line 79. Developer task 119 proposes the minimal correct fix: drop the explicit type argument from both Array.from calls so TypeScript can select the 2-type-param overload and infer element types (number[] and string[] respectively) from the mapfn return types. Pre-ratification file reads confirm: (1) C1 before-snippet matches src/iri/index.ts line 71 exactly; (2) C2 before-snippet matches tests/iri-generation.test.ts line 99 exactly; (3) both after-snippets introduce no new imports, abstractions, or behavioral logic \u00e2\u20ac\u201d only the incorrect type argument token is removed; (4) src/iri/index.ts JSDoc (lines 10\u00e2\u20ac\u201c15) explicitly documents that src/iri/ is outside the kernel purity scope, and the manualUuidV4 fallback's Math.random() usage is acknowledged non-determinism per SPEC section 9.2 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the fix leaves this function structurally unchanged; (5) the modified test file tests/iri-generation.test.ts is not one of the three protected spec tests (determinism.test.ts, no-network.test.ts, snapshot.test.ts); (6) tsconfig.json confirms lib=[ES2022], strict:true, no noUncheckedIndexedAccess \u00e2\u20ac\u201d consistent with reconnaissance F11/F13 ruling out noUncheckedIndexedAccess as a contributing factor; (7) no new packages or devDependencies are introduced. All six compiler errors are addressed: C1 resolves the TS2554 at src/iri/index.ts:71,52 and its four cascade errors (TS2571 at 75,15 and 77,15; TS18046 at 79,29 and 79,51); C2 resolves the independent TS2554 at tests/iri-generation.test.ts:99,50. The open questions from reconnaissance (whether manualUuidV4 is dead code on Node 22+; whether for-loop+push is a style preference) are correctly deferred by the developer as out-of-scope for this minimal type-fix. No contract violations, no layer boundary crossings, no protected-file mutations.",
