        "summary": "Task 1.7 requires implementing `refactorIri(project, oldIri, newIri): RefactorResult` as a new module (no src/refactor/ or src/iri/refactor.ts exists yet). The cascade update targets four IRI reference field types \u00e2\u20ac\u201d ecm:classIris (arrays on ecm:instances items), ecm:predicateIri (strings on ecm:relations and ecm:literalAssertions items), ecm:subjectIri (strings on ecm:relations and ecm:literalAssertions items), and ecm:objectIri (strings on ecm:relations items only) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d per SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.2/\u00c2\u00a713.4 and IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.7. ecm:snapshots must never be touched at any traversal depth (SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.7; AC5). The RefactorResult shape is { project, oldIri, newIri, referenceCount, affectedEntityTypes, collision? }, with collision aborting and returning the project unmodified (AC2). The collision check per SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.5 requires scanning entity id fields for newIri presence before applying any mutation. Two property-based invariants are required at \u00e2\u2030\u00a550 samples each: reversibility (A\u00e2\u2020\u2019B then B\u00e2\u2020\u2019A \u00e2\u2030\u00a1 original P) and idempotency (A\u00e2\u2020\u2019A is a no-op), implemented using the established hand-rolled Mulberry32 PRNG pattern from tests/semantic-projection.test.ts \u00e2\u20ac\u201d fast-check is not a project dependency and the developer task explicitly prohibits it, though a naming conflict exists with IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.12 which mentions fast-check by name. Two notable gaps in the acceptance criteria: (a) AC1 checks the four reference fields but does not explicitly verify that the entity's own id field (the entity being renamed) is updated to newIri; (b) the SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.5 describes an instance-on-instance merge path that the IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.7 does not scope into AC \u00e2\u20ac\u201d it only requires abort-and-report.",
