        "summary": "Phase 1 task 1.8 targets a new `generateManifestEntries(project, artifacts): SerializationEntry[]` function with no existing code in the repository. SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.15 (lines 643\u00e2\u20ac\u201c677) defines the SerializationEntry shape with 7 Required fields: `id`, `type`, `ecm:format`, `ecm:filename`, `ecm:contentHash`, `ecm:generatedAt`, `ecm:isSerializationOf`. The `ecm:byteLength` field is present in the \u00c2\u00a75.15 JSON example and in the \u00c2\u00a76.1 semantic predicate allowlist and the \u00c2\u00a719 manifest description, but is absent from the \u00c2\u00a75.15 Required: line \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a fact that creates a three-way count mismatch: SPEC lists 7 required fields, IMPL plan \u00c2\u00a71.8 sub-tasks enumerate 8 (adding byteLength), and IMPL plan \u00c2\u00a71.8 AC1 says 'six'. The MIME-type-to-format mapping is fully specified in \u00c2\u00a75.15 line 664. SHA-256 hashing uses the `sha256-` + hex pattern also specified for \u00c2\u00a73.1 ontology import; the `node:crypto` `createHash` API is already in use at `src/iri/index.ts:20` for SHA-1/UUIDv5, and `@types/node ^22.0.0` is already a devDependency. No `src/manifest/` module exists yet. The module would live outside `src/kernel/` (following the pattern of `src/iri/`, `src/emit/`, etc.) and outside the kernel purity checker scope. Tests follow a hand-rolled `node:assert` pattern without a framework; no manifest test file exists. Task 1.8 is explicitly scoped to the data structure only \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the full `manifest.jsonld` RDF document generation is deferred to Phase 4 task 4.5.",
