          "RESOLUTION QUESTION (ft-097-test-validator-3): When v0.3->v0.4 migration sets iao:isAbout to ['ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter'], does the resulting validate() output emit MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR (per existing task 1.3 implementation: fires when isAbout contains only UnspecifiedSubjectMatter) OR is MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR suppressed when LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER is present (since the migration placeholder is documented info-finding, not actual error)? Per IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md section 1.9 AC2: 'migrate(v0.3Fixture, '0.4') chained with validate() produces zero hard errors (only LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER info finding)'. This implies MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR is SUPPRESSED in legacy-migrated docs. Confirm and surface as a finding.",
