        "summary": "The Phase 1 task 1.11 CLI surface has not been started: no src/cli/ directory exists, package.json has no 'bin' field, and no CLI integration tests are present. The kernel-tier dispatch functions are all in place (validate, migrate, refactorIri, generateIri, emitTurtle, emitNTriples, projectSemantic, normalizeOnLoad) except for the mermaid and markdown emitters, which do not exist. The existing src/kernel/index.ts is a single-argument stub unrelated to the \u00c2\u00a723 command set. Node 22's built-in util.parseArgs is available at the declared engine baseline \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no extra devDependency is needed. Two structural concerns are present: (1) SPEC \u00c2\u00a723 defines exit code 2 as 'file I/O errors' while IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.11 and ADR-003 use exit code 2 for both path containment violations and 'not yet implemented' stubs \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this is a documented broadening, not an undefined conflict; (2) the scope-split direction in phase1-task-1-11-chain.json includes 'export --format markdown' in Chain 1 but src/emit/markdown.ts does not yet exist, making it a prerequisite creation, while Mermaid is properly deferred. Golden-file ACs are blocked by OED-306 and OED-313 (both Open). The path containment implementation is absent from all existing code. All eight \u00c2\u00a71.11 ACs are uncovered.",
