        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change creates three new source files (src/emit/markdown.ts, src/cli/index.ts, tests/cli-integration.test.ts) and mutates package.json to add a bin entry point, implementing the full \u00c2\u00a723 CLI surface \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this is behavioral specification content and new code, not terminology tightening or formatting.",
        "rationale": "All preconditions for ratification are satisfied. Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (task:143-recon-cli-surface). OED-307 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d which gates 'CLI integration tests for stub commands' \u00e2\u20ac\u201d is resolved by ADR-003 (explicitly annotated in phase1-task-1-11-chain.json focus_areas line 17: 'OED-307 resolved: import-ontology + export --format zip are stubs in Phase 1'; confirmed by ADR-003 consequences: 'Stub behaviour must be covered by Phase 1 CLI integration tests to prevent silent regression'). Each check in the review_focus passes:\n\n(1) SPEC \u00c2\u00a723 + \u00c2\u00a712.2 CONFORMANCE: All \u00c2\u00a723 commands are present (validate, export, migrate, refactor-iri, import-ontology). All export formats named in \u00c2\u00a723 are addressed: turtle/n-triples/markdown as full implementations, json-ld and mermaid as deferred stubs, zip as ADR-003-mandated Phase 4 stub. \u00c2\u00a712.2 path containment is implemented in safeResolve() using relative(cwd, resolved).startsWith('..') || isAbsolute(rel) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d covers both parent-traversal and Windows cross-drive escapes. --allow-outside-cwd flag is wired through all commands. The --out output path also passes through safeResolve, which is correct and matches \u00c2\u00a712.2 'CLI file path arguments' (plural).\n\n(2) 8 ACS COVERAGE: Developer's 8 ACs map to all reachable IMPL PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.11 ACs. Golden-file ACs (#4: byte-identical turtle, #5: deterministic golden) are explicitly deferred with OED-306 and OED-313 gates documented; structural @prefix assertion substituted for AC4. This is a correct scope-split \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the deferred ACs are blocked by open OEDs, not by developer choice. The added migrate AC (AC8) is grounded in \u00c2\u00a71.11 sub-tasks. OED-307 resolved, so stub ACs (AC6, AC7) are authoring-permitted.\n\n(3) EXIT CODE MAPPING: Correct. Exit 0 (success), 1 (validation hard errors excluding version), 2 (I/O error + path escape + not-implemented per ADR-003 broadening), 3 (malformed input / parse failure / missing required argument), 4 (INVALID_SPEC_VERSION). The validate/cmdMigrate INVALID_SPEC_VERSION\u00e2\u2020\u2019exit 4 path is correctly threaded via INVALID_SPEC_VERSION constant import from validate/codes.ts. One borderline point: unknown export format \u00e2\u2020\u2019 exit 2 rather than exit 3. This is defensible under ADR-003 ('unavailable in this build') but exit 3 could also be argued ('malformed input'). Not blocking.\n\n(4) PATH CONTAINMENT: safeResolve() applied to all file path arguments (input and --out). AC5 test exercises '../../etc/passwd' traversal \u00e2\u2020\u2019 exit 2. Correct.\n\n(5) STUB EXIT CODES + STDERR TEXT: Both ADR-003-named stubs match exactly. export --format zip \u00e2\u2020\u2019 exit 2, stderr 'not yet implemented; available in Phase 4'. import-ontology \u00e2\u2020\u2019 exit 2, stderr 'not yet implemented; available in Phase 3'. Tests AC6/AC7 assert these exact strings.\n\n(6) KERNEL PURITY: Confirmed by reading scripts/ensure-kernel-purity.ts. The purity checker scans only files in src/kernel/ matching *.js; src/cli/ is never scanned. src/cli/index.ts imports FROM kernel-tier modules (canonicalize, validate, migrate, refactor, emit \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all correct adapter-tier consumption). No kernel module can import FROM src/cli/ since src/cli/ is new and no kernel module references it.\n\n(7) NO NEW DEVDEPENDENCIES: util.parseArgs from node:util is a Node 22 built-in. Confirmed by package.json engines: >=22.0.0. devDependencies unchanged.\n\nMinor observations not blocking ratification: (a) json-ld stub message 'available in Phase 2' is potentially inaccurate if json-ld export is Phase 1 Chain 2 scope \u00e2\u20ac\u201d advisory, affects only a stub message; (b) TypeScript compilation unknowns (parseArgs return type inference, definite-assignment of content/raw through process.exit() never paths) are acknowledged by the developer with fix directions \u00e2\u20ac\u201d build verification by the operator is the resolution path, as expected for code changes; (c) 'graphwrite' bin name is sourced from phase1-task-1-11-chain.json (operator-composed chain file) rather than SPEC \u00c2\u00a723 or IMPL PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.11 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d operator should confirm the name at build-verification time. None of these require re-ratification.",
