        "summary": "Task 1.12 (Test Harness) is the final Phase 1 task and its scope is materially larger than its in-plan description suggests. The core tension is that IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a71.12 explicitly mandates 'Configure Vitest/Jest with TypeScript + coverage' and 'Property-based tests (fast-check)', but tasks 1.1\u00e2\u20ac\u201c1.11 have uniformly established a hand-rolled framework (tests/run-tests.ts + node:assert + Mulberry32 PRNG) across all 14 test files, with no Vitest/Jest/fast-check anywhere in the devDependencies. Of the four SPEC \u00c2\u00a721.1 property-based invariants, three already have \u00e2\u2030\u00a550-sample hand-rolled implementations (cascade reversibility, cascade idempotency, semantic-projection stability in iri-refactor.test.ts and semantic-projection.test.ts); the fourth (canonical idempotency) tests only 2 pre-defined fixtures and its file header explicitly defers 'true property-based tests (fast-check)' pending operator approval. No test fixture files exist on disk (test/fixtures/ absent); no golden files exist on disk (test/golden/ absent); 7 unconditional pass() stubs defer real byte-comparison until OED-306 + OED-313 close. No coverage tooling is present and the existing CI has no coverage step or deterministic-export step. All 5 relevant OEDs (OED-306, OED-307, OED-303, OED-313, OED-301) are recorded as Open in IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md's OED tracking table, though OED-307's gated work (stub CLI integration tests) is now implemented in cli-integration.test.ts (task 1.11). No ADR records the framework or fast-check adoption decision, leaving the IMPL_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.12 'Configure Vitest/Jest' sub-task as the sole formal authority on the question.",
