          {
            "id": "C2",
            "file": "tests/vmp-serializer.test.ts",
            "rationale": "Remove the 'deferred pending Human Orchestrator approval' note (approval now granted via task 1.12) and add 'import * as fc from fast-check'. The import must precede node:assert to keep fast-check in the top-level import block.",
            "before": " * Note: true property-based tests (fast-check) are deferred pending Human\n * Orchestrator approval to add fast-check as a devDependency.\n */\n\nimport { strictEqual, deepStrictEqual } from \"node:assert\";",
            "after": " * Note: true property-based tests (fast-check) approved per task 1.12.\n * Canonical idempotency PBT uses fast-check (>= 100 samples; seed 0xcafef00d).\n */\n\nimport * as fc from \"fast-check\";\nimport { strictEqual, deepStrictEqual } from \"node:assert\";",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C3",
            "file": "tests/vmp-serializer.test.ts",
            "rationale": "Insert the fast-check property-based test for canonical idempotency (SPEC section 21.1, 4th invariant) immediately before the Summary block. The arbitrary varies timestamps (non-canonical forms that normalizeTimestamp must canonicalize), ecm:terms ordering (named-array sort), and iao:isAbout ordering (lex-sort). Uses 100 runs with a fixed seed for deterministic reproduction. Existing 2-fixture AC2 tests are preserved; this adds the PBT layer the file header always intended.",
            "before": "// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Summary\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\nconsole.log(`\\n  ${passed} passed, ${failed} failed`);\nif (failed > 0) process.exit(1);",
            "after": "// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// AC2-PBT: Canonical idempotency property-based test (fast-check, 100 samples)\n// SPEC section 21.1: serialize(parse(serialize(P))) === serialize(P) bytewise.\n// Exercises: varied timestamps, named-array ordering, IRI-array ordering.\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\nconsole.log(\"\\nAC2-PBT: Canonical idempotency property-based test (fast-check, 100 samples)\");\n\ntry {\n  const emptyArrArb = fc.constant([] as unknown[]);\n\n  const vmpArb = fc.record({\n    \"id\": fc.constantFrom(\n      \"urn:uuid:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001\",\n      \"urn:uuid:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002\",\n      \"urn:uuid:aaaabbbb-cccc-dddd-eeee-ffffffffffff\",\n    ),\n    \"type\": fc.constant([\"ecm:Project\", \"iao:OntologyDesignPattern\"] as unknown[]),\n    \"ecm:specVersion\": fc.constantFrom(\"0.4\", \"0.3\", \"0.0\"),\n    \"ecm:name\": fc.constantFrom(\"Project A\", \"Project B\", \"Test Project\"),\n    \"ecm:createdAt\": fc.constantFrom(\n      \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"2026-05-14T12:00:00.123Z\",\n      \"2026-05-14T12:00:00+00:00\",\n      \"2026-05-14T12:00:00.456+05:30\",\n    ),\n    \"ecm:updatedAt\": fc.constantFrom(\n      \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"2026-05-14T12:30:00.999Z\",\n      \"2026-05-14T12:00:00-08:00\",\n    ),\n    \"iao:isAbout\": fc.array(\n      fc.constantFrom(\n        \"https://example.org/s/A\",\n        \"https://example.org/s/B\",\n        \"https://example.org/s/C\",\n      ),\n      { minLength: 1, maxLength: 3 },\n    ),\n    \"ecm:terms\": fc.array(\n      fc.record({\n        \"id\": fc.constantFrom(\"urn:t:a\", \"urn:t:b\", \"urn:t:c\", \"urn:t:z\"),\n        \"ecm:label\": fc.constantFrom(\"Alpha\", \"Beta\", \"Gamma\"),\n      }),\n      { minLength: 0, maxLength: 3 },\n    ),\n    \"ecm:instances\": emptyArrArb,\n    \"ecm:relations\": emptyArrArb,\n    \"ecm:literalAssertions\": emptyArrArb,\n    \"ecm:ontologies\": emptyArrArb,\n    \"ecm:layouts\": emptyArrArb,\n    \"ecm:snapshots\": emptyArrArb,\n    \"ecm:serializations\": emptyArrArb,\n  });\n\n  fc.assert(\n    fc.property(vmpArb, (doc) => {\n      const s1 = serializeVmp(doc as Record<string, unknown>);\n      const s2 = serializeVmp(JSON.parse(s1) as Record<string, unknown>);\n      return s1 === s2;\n    }),\n    { numRuns: 100, seed: 0xcafef00d },\n  );\n  pass(\n    \"canonical idempotency: 100 samples pass \" +\n      \"(AC2-PBT, SPEC section 21.1; fast-check seed 0xcafef00d)\",\n  );\n} catch (e) {\n  fail(\"canonical idempotency property-based test (AC2-PBT, SPEC section 21.1)\", e);\n}\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Summary\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\nconsole.log(`\\n  ${passed} passed, ${failed} failed`);\nif (failed > 0) process.exit(1);",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C4",
            "file": "test/fixtures/canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld",
            "rationale": "New minimal canonical v0.4 fixture. Represents the expected serialized output of serializeVmp on a valid project: full @context in alphabetical key order (matching vmpCanonicalizeObject recursive sort), compact id/type aliases, ISO 8601 Z timestamps, real iao:isAbout IRI (so MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR does not fire), all named arrays empty. Trailing newline matches serializeVmp rule (section 5.3 rule 6). Gated future use: golden-file byte-comparison once OED-306+OED-313 close.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "{\n  \"@context\": {\n    \"cco\": \"https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/\",\n    \"ecm\": \"https://edgecanonical.org/ns/modeler#\",\n    \"ecm:classIris\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:instances\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:isSerializationOf\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:layouts\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:literalAssertions\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:objectIri\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:ontologies\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:predicateIri\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:relations\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:serializations\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:snapshots\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:subjectIri\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:terms\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"iao\": \"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/iao#\",\n    \"iao:isAbout\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"id\": \"@id\",\n    \"owl\": \"http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#\",\n    \"rdf\": \"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\",\n    \"rdfs\": \"http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#\",\n    \"rdfs:subClassOf\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"rdfs:subPropertyOf\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"type\": \"@type\",\n    \"xsd\": \"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#\"\n  },\n  \"id\": \"urn:uuid:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000010\",\n  \"type\": [\n    \"ecm:Project\",\n    \"iao:OntologyDesignPattern\"\n  ],\n  \"ecm:specVersion\": \"0.4\",\n  \"ecm:createdAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"ecm:instances\": [],\n  \"ecm:layouts\": [],\n  \"ecm:literalAssertions\": [],\n  \"ecm:name\": \"Minimal v0.4 Project\",\n  \"ecm:ontologies\": [],\n  \"ecm:relations\": [],\n  \"ecm:serializations\": [],\n  \"ecm:snapshots\": [],\n  \"ecm:terms\": [],\n  \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"iao:isAbout\": [\n    \"https://example.org/subjects/CustomerOrders\"\n  ]\n}\n",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C5",
            "file": "test/fixtures/malformed/missing-realist-anchor.jsonld",
            "rationale": "New malformed fixture triggering MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR. iao:isAbout contains only ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter and ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder is absent, so the hard error (not the info finding) fires. Intentionally minimal: no @context (the structural validator does not inspect @context). All other fields are valid so only MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR fires.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "{\n  \"id\": \"urn:uuid:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000020\",\n  \"type\": [\"ecm:Project\", \"iao:OntologyDesignPattern\"],\n  \"ecm:specVersion\": \"0.4\",\n  \"ecm:name\": \"Malformed: MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR (unspecified placeholder)\",\n  \"ecm:createdAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"iao:isAbout\": [\"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\"],\n  \"ecm:ontologies\": [],\n  \"ecm:terms\": [],\n  \"ecm:instances\": [],\n  \"ecm:relations\": [],\n  \"ecm:literalAssertions\": [],\n  \"ecm:layouts\": [],\n  \"ecm:snapshots\": [],\n  \"ecm:serializations\": []\n}\n",
