    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:150-rat-test-harness",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change adds a new devDependency (fast-check), inserts executable property-based test logic into a test file, and creates three new fixture files on disk \u00e2\u20ac\u201d these are functional mutations to the codebase, not typo, formatting, or terminology-tightening corrections.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:148-recon-test-harness, F1\u00e2\u20ac\u201cF15) and covers all relevant artifacts: package.json, all 14 test files, SPEC \u00c2\u00a721.1\u00e2\u20ac\u201c21.4, IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.12, DECISIONS.md ADR-001\u00e2\u20ac\u201cADR-006, OED tracking table, and .github/workflows/ci.yml. The reconnaissance evidence is sufficient to evaluate the proposed changes.\n\nC1 (fast-check ^3.0.0 devDep): Correctly scoped. fast-check v3 ships its own TypeScript type declarations; the review focus note 'plus @types/fast-check if needed' is addressed by the developer's rationale ('fast-check v3 bundles its own TypeScript types; no @types/fast-check needed') and this is accurate. Alphabetical insertion between @types/node and n3 is consistent with existing ordering. The before-snippet matches the actual package.json lines 34\u00e2\u20ac\u201c40 exactly.\n\nC2 (vmp-serializer.test.ts header + import): Removes the 'deferred pending Human Orchestrator approval' comment (the approval is implicit in queuing task 1.12) and adds 'import * as fc from \"fast-check\"' above the node:assert import. The before-snippet matches the actual file lines 12\u00e2\u20ac\u201c16. The after preserves the import line for '../src/kernel/canonicalize.js' which falls outside the snippet window \u00e2\u20ac\u201d applier substring matching will correctly leave it in place.\n\nC3 (AC2-PBT fast-check block): The before-snippet matches the actual Summary block at lines 245\u00e2\u20ac\u201c249. The vmpArb exercises all three idempotency-relevant dimensions identified by SPEC \u00c2\u00a721.1: timestamp normalization variants (fractional-second and offset inputs that normalizeTimestamp must canonicalize), named-array ordering (ecm:terms), and IRI-array ordering (iao:isAbout). 100 samples with a fixed seed (0xcafef00d) satisfies the \u00e2\u2030\u00a550-sample requirement and is deterministically reproducible. One cosmetic issue: the existing block at lines 199\u00e2\u20ac\u201c217 is labeled 'AC2: idempotency' and the new block is labeled 'AC2-PBT', creating two pass() messages tied to the same AC. This is not functionally wrong \u00e2\u20ac\u201d both tests exercise SPEC \u00c2\u00a721.1 canonical idempotency \u00e2\u20ac\u201d but the label collision is noted.\n\nC4/C5/C6 (fixture files): Paths are correct per SPEC \u00c2\u00a721.3 ('Committed under test/fixtures/'). C5 (MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR) and C6 (INVALID_SPEC_VERSION) represent 2 of 16 \u00c2\u00a717.2 codes; the remaining 14 are deferred to the follow-up chain described in the developer's open_questions. This partial delivery is acceptable given OED-313 (which scopes fixture enumeration) remains Open. C4 (canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld) is committed as a future golden-file anchor; its key ordering is claimed to match serializeVmp output exactly, but this claim is unverified until OED-306+OED-313 close.\n\nScope-split (Option B): Keeping the hand-rolled framework and adding fast-check only for the canonical-idempotency invariant is a correct decision given Phase 1's uniform hand-rolled pattern across all 14 test files. However, IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a71.12 still mandates 'Configure Vitest/Jest with TypeScript + coverage' \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this mandate is now overridden by the scope-split but no ADR records the override. Recon F9 confirms DECISIONS.md contains ADR-001 through ADR-006 with no framework-choice ADR. This leaves a dormant conflict: the IMPL_PLAN mandate remains authoritative until an ADR supersedes it. An ADR (ADR-007 candidate) must be queued and ratified before Phase 1 exit gate review.\n\nTwo operational risks for commit-finalize:\n1. BOM-on-new-files: CLAUDE.md states the applier adds UTF-8 BOM on new files; SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.3 rule 7 requires UTF-8 no-BOM for VMP files. C4, C5, C6 are new files (before: null). If the applier adds a BOM, golden-file byte-comparison once OED-306+OED-313 close will fail. The operator must confirm applier behavior for .jsonld files before the commit-finalize step; if the applier adds BOM, a post-applier strip is needed.\n2. fast-check ESM resolution under NodeNext: tsconfig.test.json uses NodeNext moduleResolution; fast-check v3 ships proper ESM exports. Risk is low but the operator should confirm 'npm run build:tests' succeeds after 'npm i --save-dev fast-check' before declaring the task done.\n\nNeither operational risk blocks ratification of the proposed content. The content of all six changes is correct relative to the SPEC, IMPL_PLAN, and reconnaissance evidence. The scope-split is well-reasoned and its deferred items are clearly gate-conditioned (OED-306, OED-313, CI-infrastructure phase). Ruling: ratified with the ADR-007 documentation debt and two operational risks noted for operator action before Phase 1 exit gate.",
