      "outputs": {
        "findings": [
          {
            "id": "F1",
            "claim": "SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a726 defines five named UI panels for the layout contract: header, left sidebar (Term Manager), center (Instance Canvas), right (Inspector/Explanation), and bottom/secondary (Outputs).",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "1618-1631",
                "excerpt": "**Header:** project name, save/open/export controls, validation status, migration notice if applicable.\n**Left sidebar \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Term Manager:** classes, object properties, datatype properties, search/filter, add term, source indicator\n**Center \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Instance Canvas:** instance cards, directed relations, drag/drop positioning, zoom/pan, node/edge selection.\n**Right panel \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Inspector / Explanation:** selected node details ... contextual explanation, validation findings\n**Bottom or secondary panel \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Outputs:** Mermaid text, rendered Mermaid, Turtle output, Markdown summary, export buttons."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F2",
            "claim": "FR-U001, FR-U002, and FR-U003 are specified as one-line requirements in SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a718.2; IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a72.1 expands each into concrete sub-tasks and five Playwright acceptance criteria.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "1320-1322",
                "excerpt": "| FR-U001 | Create a new project. |\n| FR-U002 | Open a project JSON-LD file. |\n| FR-U003 | Save the active project as `project.jsonld` in canonical form. |"
              },
              {
                "file": "project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md",
                "lines": "304-321",
                "excerpt": "**Sub-tasks:**\n- React + TypeScript browser bundle (Vite). No server-side runtime required.\n- \u00c2\u00a726 layout: header, left sidebar, center canvas, right inspector, bottom outputs panel.\n- FR-U001 New project: minimal valid v0.4 document with `iao:isAbout: [\"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\"]`.\n- FR-U002 Open project: `<input type=\"file\">`, calls `migrate()` + `normalizeOnLoad()` + `validate()`, shows FR-U029 migration notice if migrated.\n- FR-U003 Save project: canonical serialize \u00e2\u2020\u2019 browser download as `project.jsonld`."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F3",
            "claim": "NFR-001 requires core computation to run in both browser and Node.js; NFR-002 prohibits any server-side runtime for core operation. ROADMAP.md cross-cutting layering commitment explicitly states the core MUST NOT depend on DOM, React, IndexedDB, or remote APIs.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "1410-1411",
                "excerpt": "| NFR-001 | Core computation runs in both browser and Node.js. |\n| NFR-002 | No database, server, cloud service, or broker is required for core operation. |"
              },
              {
                "file": "project/ROADMAP.md",
                "lines": "18",
                "excerpt": "**Layering (NFR-005, \u00c2\u00a74).** Computation is core; state, orchestration, integration, UI, and packaging are adapters. The core MUST NOT depend on DOM, React, IndexedDB, File System Access, or remote APIs."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F4",
            "claim": "SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a710.4 defines the migration notice trigger: any v0.2 or v0.3 document load causes migration to v0.4 and must surface a 'Project was migrated from v0.X to v0.Y' notice. IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a72.11 specifies banner text including source version.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "883,885-900",
                "excerpt": "Migration is non-destructive: the original document is preserved on disk under `project.jsonld.pre-migration.<sourceVersion>` unless the caller opts out. UI surfaces a \"Project was migrated from v0.X to v0.Y\" notice.\n### 10.4 Legacy Documents\n**v0.2 documents** ... are loaded as legacy v0.2 and migrated through v0.3 to v0.4 on load.\n**v0.3 / v0.3.1 documents** ... are migrated to v0.4 on load."
              },
              {
                "file": "project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md",
                "lines": "481-488",
                "excerpt": "**Sub-tasks:**\n- Dismissible banner shown when a v0.2 or v0.3 document is migrated on open.\n- Banner text includes source version: \"Project was migrated from v0.X to v0.4.\""
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F5",
            "claim": "The `MigrationReport` interface in src/migrate/index.ts does not include a `sourceVersion` field; the source version is detected internally by `detectSourceVersion()` but is not surfaced to the caller. FR-U029 banner text requires 'from v0.X', so the UI layer will need to independently derive the source version (e.g., by inspecting `ecm:specVersion` on the raw parsed doc before calling `migrate()`).",
            "evidence": [
              {
