            "rationale": "SPEC section 26 five-panel shell: header, left sidebar (Term Manager), center canvas (Instance Canvas), right inspector, bottom outputs. Placeholder content in each panel; panels populated in tasks 2.2 (sidebar), 2.4 (canvas), 2.5+ (inspector), 2.10 (outputs). FR-U001/FR-U002/FR-U003 header controls added in Chain 2. data-testid attributes are the AC1 Playwright assertion targets.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "import \"./App.css\";\n\n/**\n * GraphWrite App shell -- SPEC section 26 five-panel layout.\n *\n * Panels populated in subsequent tasks:\n *   Left sidebar (Term Manager): task 2.2\n *   Center canvas (Instance Canvas): task 2.4\n *   Right inspector: task 2.5+\n *   Bottom outputs: task 2.10\n * FR-U001 / FR-U002 / FR-U003 header controls: task 2.1 Chain 2.\n */\nexport function App() {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"gw-shell\">\n      <header className=\"gw-header\" data-testid=\"gw-header\">\n        <span className=\"gw-brand\">GraphWrite</span>\n        {/* New / Open / Save -- task 2.1 Chain 2 */}\n      </header>\n\n      <div className=\"gw-body\">\n        <aside className=\"gw-sidebar\" data-testid=\"gw-sidebar\">\n          <p className=\"gw-placeholder\">Term Manager -- task 2.2</p>\n        </aside>\n\n        <main className=\"gw-canvas\" data-testid=\"gw-canvas\">\n          <p className=\"gw-placeholder\">Instance Canvas -- task 2.4</p>\n        </main>\n\n        <aside className=\"gw-inspector\" data-testid=\"gw-inspector\">\n          <p className=\"gw-placeholder\">Inspector -- task 2.5</p>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n\n      <section className=\"gw-outputs\" data-testid=\"gw-outputs\">\n        <p className=\"gw-placeholder\">Outputs -- task 2.10</p>\n      </section>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C11",
            "file": "src/ui/App.css",
            "rationale": "CSS layout for the SPEC section 26 five-panel shell. Flex column root (gw-shell); fixed-height header and outputs strip; gw-body flex row with fixed-width sidebar (240px) and inspector (280px) flanking a flex-1 center canvas. All colors are hex literals (ASCII). No non-ASCII characters.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "*,\n*::before,\n*::after {\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n  margin: 0;\n  padding: 0;\n}\n\nhtml,\nbody,\n#root {\n  height: 100%;\n}\n\n.gw-shell {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  height: 100%;\n  font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;\n}\n\n.gw-header {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  gap: 0.75rem;\n  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;\n  background: #1e293b;\n  color: #f1f5f9;\n  min-height: 3rem;\n  flex-shrink: 0;\n}\n\n.gw-brand {\n  font-weight: 600;\n  font-size: 1rem;\n}\n\n.gw-body {\n  display: flex;\n  flex: 1;\n  overflow: hidden;\n}\n\n.gw-sidebar {\n  width: 240px;\n  flex-shrink: 0;\n  background: #f8fafc;\n  border-right: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\n  overflow-y: auto;\n  padding: 0.75rem;\n}\n\n.gw-canvas {\n  flex: 1;\n  background: #ffffff;\n  overflow: hidden;\n  position: relative;\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\n}\n\n.gw-inspector {\n  width: 280px;\n  flex-shrink: 0;\n  background: #f8fafc;\n  border-left: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\n  overflow-y: auto;\n  padding: 0.75rem;\n}\n\n.gw-outputs {\n  height: 180px;\n  flex-shrink: 0;\n  background: #f1f5f9;\n  border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\n  overflow-y: auto;\n  padding: 0.75rem;\n}\n\n.gw-placeholder {\n  color: #94a3b8;\n  font-size: 0.875rem;\n  font-style: italic;\n}\n",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C12",
            "file": "playwright.config.ts",
            "rationale": "Playwright configuration targeting Chromium (AC1 requires Chromium >= 110). webServer uses 'npm run preview' (vite preview -- static bundle server, no dynamic routes) satisfying AC5's static-server constraint by design. baseURL http://localhost:4173 matches vite preview default port. reuseExistingServer:true for local dev, false in CI.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "import { defineConfig, devices } from \"@playwright/test\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  testDir: \"./tests/playwright\",\n  timeout: 30_000,\n  expect: { timeout: 5_000 },\n  fullyParallel: true,\n  forbidOnly: !!process.env[\"CI\"],\n  retries: process.env[\"CI\"] ? 2 : 0,\n  reporter: \"list\",\n  use: {\n    headless: true,\n    baseURL: \"http://localhost:4173\",\n  },\n  projects: [\n    {\n      name: \"chromium\",\n      use: { ...devices[\"Desktop Chrome\"] },\n    },\n  ],\n  webServer: {\n    command: \"npm run preview\",\n    url: \"http://localhost:4173\",\n    reuseExistingServer: !process.env[\"CI\"],\n    stdout: \"pipe\",\n    stderr: \"pipe\",\n  },\n});\n",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C13",
            "file": "tests/playwright/shell.spec.ts",
            "rationale": "AC1: asserts all five data-testid panels are visible and no JS console errors on load. AC5: asserts the webServer (vite preview = static-only) returns 200 for an unknown path via SPA fallback (sirv single:true mode, default in vite preview with appType:spa). AC2-AC4 (New/Open/Save roundtrip + migration notice) deferred to Chain 2.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "import { test, expect } from \"@playwright/test\";\n\n/**\n * Task 2.1 Chain 1 smoke tests.\n *\n * AC1: App loads in Chromium >= 110 with no JS console errors;\n *      all four layout panels rendered (IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md section 2.1).\n * AC5: Bundle served by static file server only (no dynamic routes).\n *      Structurally guaranteed: webServer is 'vite preview' (static-only).\n *      Test confirms app loads and SPA fallback returns 200 for unknown paths.\n *\n * AC2-AC4 (New/Save roundtrip, Open v0.4 roundtrip, migration notice):\n *      implemented in task 2.1 Chain 2.\n */\ntest.describe(\"GraphWrite shell (task 2.1 AC1 + AC5)\", () => {\n  test(\"AC1: four layout panels visible with no console errors\", async ({\n    page,\n  }) => {\n    const consoleErrors: string[] = [];\n    page.on(\"console\", (msg) => {\n      if (msg.type() === \"error\") {\n        consoleErrors.push(msg.text());\n      }\n    });\n\n    await page.goto(\"/\");\n\n    await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-header\")).toBeVisible();\n    await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-sidebar\")).toBeVisible();\n    await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-canvas\")).toBeVisible();\n    await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-inspector\")).toBeVisible();\n    await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-outputs\")).toBeVisible();\n\n    expect(consoleErrors, \"no JS console errors on load\").toHaveLength(0);\n  });\n\n  test(\"AC5: static server -- SPA fallback returns 200 for unknown path\", async ({\n    page,\n  }) => {\n    await page.goto(\"/\");\n    await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-header\")).toBeVisible();\n\n    // vite preview (sirv, appType:spa) falls back to index.html on 404 -> 200.\n    const response = await page.goto(\"/__nonexistent_route__\");\n    expect(\n      response?.status(),\n      \"vite preview SPA fallback serves 200 for any path\",\n    ).toBe(200);\n  });\n});\n",
            "scope": "minimal"
          }
        ],
        "tests_recommended": [
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/new-open-save.spec.ts",
            "describe": "Chain 2: AC2 (New->Save->parse: ecm:specVersion 0.4, correct type array, iao:isAbout UnspecifiedSubjectMatter), AC3 (Open v0.4 fixture->Save->re-parse: bytewise identical to fixture), AC4 (Open v0.3 fixture: migration notice visible before any user action). Requires fixture files tests/playwright/fixtures/v04-minimal.jsonld and tests/playwright/fixtures/v03-sample.jsonld, and src/ui/ New/Open/Save implementation."
          },
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/shell.spec.ts",
            "describe": "Extend in Chain 2 with download-intercept helper for Save button testing once FR-U003 is implemented."
          }
        ],
        "open_questions": [
          "Chain 2 must be queued as a follow-up task before task 2.1 is marked complete: it adds src/ui/useProject.ts (in-memory project state hook), src/ui/MigrationNotice.tsx (FR-U029 dismissible banner), header New/Open/Save controls in App.tsx, Playwright fixture files (v0.3 and v0.4 .jsonld), and the new-open-save.spec.ts covering AC2-AC4. AC1 and AC5 are covered by this Chain 1 proposal.",
          "npm install must be run after the applier writes the updated package.json before any build:ui or test:e2e script will succeed. This is operator action, not part of the applier step.",
          "npm run build:ui must complete successfully (produces dist/ui/) before npm run test:e2e can start the vite preview webServer. Playwright webServer.command='npm run preview' requires a built dist/ui/index.html to exist. Operator workflow: npm install -> npm run build:ui -> npm run test:e2e.",
          "The vite preview SPA fallback (AC5 test) depends on Vite 5's default appType:spa behavior in sirv. If the project later sets appType:'mpa' or 'custom' in vite.config.ts, the fallback test will need adjustment.",
          "Recon finding F5: MigrationReport does not expose sourceVersion. Chain 2's FR-U029 banner ('Project was migrated from v0.X to v0.4') must read ecm:specVersion from the raw parsed document BEFORE calling migrate(), not from the MigrationReport. This is a Chain 2 implementation constraint, not a Chain 1 concern.",
          "React Flow (@xyflow/react) is NOT included here per task 2.1 scope -- it is a task 2.4 deliverable. The center canvas placeholder is sufficient for Chain 1."
        ],
        "summary": "Chain 1 of task 2.1: establishes the complete Phase 2 build tooling and SPEC section 26 five-panel shell. 13 changes: 4 edits (package.json scripts, package.json devDependencies, tsconfig.json exclude, tsconfig.test.json exclude) + 9 new files (tsconfig.ui.json, vite.config.ts, index.html, src/ui/vite-env.d.ts, src/ui/main.tsx, src/ui/App.tsx, src/ui/App.css, playwright.config.ts, tests/playwright/shell.spec.ts). Covers AC1 (four panels, no console errors) and AC5 (static server). AC2-AC4 (New/Open/Save + migration notice) deferred to Chain 2. Key tsconfig isolation: src/ui excluded from both tsconfig.json and tsconfig.test.json (each declares its own exclude; child does not inherit parent); tests/playwright excluded from tsconfig.test.json so Playwright's own esbuild runner handles spec compilation. Vite esbuild handles JSX via @vitejs/plugin-react (no tsconfig jsx field required in the main build); tsconfig.ui.json with noEmit:true provides type-checking via typecheck:ui script.",
        "self_assessment": "confident"
      },
      "depends_on": [
