    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:155-rat-react-shell",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change introduces a new build pipeline (Vite), a new top-level source directory (src/ui/), a new test framework (Playwright), new devDependencies, and new TypeScript configuration files \u00e2\u20ac\u201d none of which are typo corrections, formatting changes, terminology tightening, or citation-format updates.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:153-recon-react-shell). The proposal was evaluated against all 18 reconnaissance findings, SPEC \u00c2\u00a726, IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.1, NFR-001/NFR-002, FR-U001\u00e2\u20ac\u201cU003/U029, ADR-001, and the OPERATOR-MEDIATION-LOG Event 3 devDep ruling. Each review focus area resolves as follows:\n\n**Reconnaissance reconciliation (F1\u00e2\u20ac\u201cF18):** All findings are addressed or explicitly deferred with documented follow-up. F8/F9 (absent src/ui/ and devDeps) are resolved by C9\u00e2\u20ac\u201cC11 and C2. F10/F11 (tsconfig incompatibility) are resolved by C3/C4/C5. F5 (MigrationReport missing sourceVersion) is acknowledged in developer open_questions[4] as a Chain 2 implementation constraint. F13 (React Flow deferred) is correctly out of Chain 1 scope. F17 (missing scripts) is resolved by C1.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a726 layout conformance:** App.tsx (C10) implements all five named areas \u00e2\u20ac\u201d gw-header, gw-sidebar (Term Manager placeholder), gw-canvas (Instance Canvas placeholder), gw-inspector (Inspector placeholder), gw-outputs (Outputs placeholder) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d with data-testid attributes as AC1 Playwright assertion targets. IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.1 AC1 says 'four layout panels' but SPEC \u00c2\u00a726 defines five areas (header + four body panels); shell.spec.ts correctly asserts all five. The AC1 wording discrepancy is a minor typo in IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN, not a structural defect.\n\n**FR-U001/U002/U003:** Explicitly deferred to Chain 2 with clear documentation (C10 comment, open_questions[0], C13 rationale). Chain 2 is identified as a prerequisite for marking task 2.1 complete. The scope split is legitimate and the follow-up is traceable.\n\n**FR-U029 migration notice trigger:** Correctly deferred to Chain 2. Developer open_questions[4] documents the exact constraint: Chain 2 must read ecm:specVersion from the raw parsed document BEFORE calling migrate(), because MigrationReport does not expose sourceVersion. The trigger condition (wasMigrated true, i.e., v0.2 or v0.3 input per SPEC \u00c2\u00a710.4) is correctly framed.\n\n**NFR-001/NFR-002 static-only:** C12 (playwright.config.ts) uses 'npm run preview' (vite preview = static file server, no dynamic routes) as the webServer command. C6 (vite.config.ts) has no server-side runtime configuration. No server-side APIs appear in src/ui/. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**Dep classification:** C2 places all new packages (react, react-dom, @types/react, @types/react-dom, @vitejs/plugin-react, vite, @playwright/test) in devDependencies. No additions to dependencies. Compliant with OPERATOR-MEDIATION-LOG Event 3 ruling. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**Layer boundaries:** C3 adds src/ui to tsconfig.json's exclude list, preventing the CLI/kernel Node build from seeing DOM+JSX code. C4 adds src/ui and tests/playwright to tsconfig.test.json's exclude list (tsconfig.test.json's exclude replaces, not merges, the parent's per TypeScript extends semantics \u00e2\u20ac\u201d correctly noted by developer). tsconfig.ui.json (C5) is a standalone non-extending config; kernel cannot transitively import from src/ui/. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**Gap-13 caution:** The proposal uses standard React 18 patterns with explicit null guard on getElementById (C9), standard JSX without exotic type narrowing (C10), and CSS import covered by vite-env.d.ts (C8). tsconfig.ui.json uses moduleResolution:bundler (TypeScript 5.0+ per ^5.7.0), jsx:react-jsx, isolatedModules:true, noEmit:true \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all correct for type-checking-only under Vite. No library-specific type-narrowing issues analogous to the N3.js Quad_Subject/Quad_Predicate issues in gap-13 are present in Chain 1 (no Phase 1 library types consumed in Chain 1 scope). \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**Before-snippet fidelity:** All four edit changes (C1\u00e2\u20ac\u201cC4) have before snippets that exactly match current disk content as read from package.json, tsconfig.json, and tsconfig.test.json. The nine new-file changes (C5\u00e2\u20ac\u201cC13) have before:null as correct applier create semantics.\n\n**Operational sequencing:** The developer correctly documents the required operator sequence: npm install \u00e2\u2020\u2019 npm run build:ui \u00e2\u2020\u2019 npm run test:e2e. The webServer.command='npm run preview' requires a built dist/ui/ before Playwright can start the server. This is an operational constraint, not a structural defect.\n\nNo contract violations, ADR conflicts, scope violations, or architectural boundary breaks were identified. The change is approved for Pass 2b (applier).",
