        "bankings": [
          {
            "id": "B1",
            "category": "methodology-refinement-candidate",
            "content": "Chain 1 / Chain 2 task decomposition as a token-limit-aware and complexity-aware split pattern within a single IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN task: Chain 1 establishes build infrastructure and layout scaffold; Chain 2 lands functional flows and the remaining ACs. The developer explicitly documents that the task is not marked done until both chains complete, preserving AC-completeness as the done condition while allowing independent ratification and application of each chain. This extends the gap-7 (large-content token-limit) and gap-14 (scope-ambiguity handling) disciplines into subject-project implementation task decomposition. The first concrete use in Phase 2; establishes a reusable chain-decomposition pattern for subsequent complex Phase 2 tasks."
          },
          {
            "id": "B2",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "MigrationReport API boundary gap surfaced at the Phase 1/Phase 2 consumer interface: the MigrationReport interface does not expose sourceVersion, so Phase 2 UI code consuming migrate() cannot obtain 'v0.X' for the FR-U029 banner text from the return value alone. The UI must inspect ecm:specVersion from the raw parsed document BEFORE calling migrate(). This is a class of API gap where Phase 1 internal state (detectSourceVersion is called internally) is not forwarded to the caller surface, forcing Phase 2 consumers to re-derive information the Phase 1 implementation already computed. The pattern suggests a Phase 1 follow-up candidate: add sourceVersion to MigrationReport for consumer ergonomics, or document the pre-inspect-before-migrate contract in src/migrate/index.ts JSDoc."
          }
        ]
      },
