        "summary": "The Chain 1 developer left src/ui/App.tsx with a JSX comment placeholder for New/Open/Save buttons (line 18) and no button elements, state, or handlers \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all three controls are absent stubs. The kernel pipeline is fully implemented: migrate() (src/migrate/index.ts) returns {document, migrationReport} with MigrationReport.{addedFields, removedFields, transformedFields, info}; there is no wasMigrated, fromVersion, or toVersion field, so the UI must infer migration occurred by examining the migrationReport arrays or by reading doc[\"ecm:specVersion\"] before calling migrate(). normalizeOnLoad() returns {document, wasNormalized: boolean}. validate() returns a ValidationReport with ecm:findings[]. serializeVmp() (src/kernel/canonicalize.ts) returns a canonical string only \u00e2\u20ac\u201d browser Blob/download wiring is not present anywhere in src/. The FR-U029 migration notice is specified as a dismissible banner (IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a72.11) with text 'Project was migrated from v0.X to v0.4'; SPEC \u00c2\u00a726 places it in the header. SPEC \u00c2\u00a710.4 explicitly states the LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER info finding does not block save, only blocks export. No AC3/AC4 validation-error-display requirement exists in the \u00c2\u00a72.1 ACs. A critical fixture gap exists: there is no test/fixtures/canonical-v0.3/ directory or any v0.3-format fixture for the AC4 Playwright test; only test/fixtures/canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld exists (suitable for AC3 roundtrip). shell.spec.ts contains AC1+AC5 only and its own JSDoc names Chain 2 as the AC2\u00e2\u20ac\u201cAC4 owner. The playwright.config.ts webServer runs 'npm run preview'; no pretest:e2e build hook exists in package.json. Playwright ^1.44.0 natively supports setInputFiles for file-input simulation. src/ui/ is not assigned to any named layer in the architecture; the purity checker only covers src/kernel/, leaving src/ui/ free to import from src/kernel/, src/migrate/, src/normalize/, and src/validate/ without violating any enforced rule \u00e2\u20ac\u201d though SPEC \u00c2\u00a74.1.2 classifies browser download/upload as an adapter concern. LEGACY_DOCUMENT_MIGRATED is declared in codes.ts but not emitted by migrate() as shipped.",
