            "describe": "AC4 dismiss sub-case: after dismissal, re-opening the same v0.3 fixture should show the banner again (state reset). Not in AC4 spec but useful regression guard for the banner lifecycle."
          }
        ],
        "open_questions": [
          "LF line endings on the v0.4 fixture (test/fixtures/canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld): no .gitattributes is present in the repo. If git is configured with core.autocrlf=true on Windows the fixture may have CRLF on disk; serializeVmp always emits LF. AC3's bytewise comparison would then fail. Recommend adding a .gitattributes entry '*.jsonld text eol=lf' or verifying the fixture's on-disk line endings before running the e2e suite.",
          "Vite import resolution for UI->non-UI source: App.tsx imports from '../migrate/index.js', '../normalize/index.js', '../validate/index.js', '../kernel/canonicalize.js' using .js extensions (matching the project convention). Vite's bundler module resolution maps .js to .ts at build time; tsc --noEmit -p tsconfig.ui.json also resolves them transitively from the src/ui root. If 'npm run typecheck:ui' reveals unresolved module errors, the fix is to verify Vite + tsconfig.ui.json bundler resolution is active (already set in tsconfig.ui.json as moduleResolution: bundler).",
          "AC3 bytewise identity relies on the v0.4 fixture being in canonical serializeVmp form. The reconnaissance finding F14 noted this requires running the code to confirm. If normalizeOnLoad returns wasNormalized=true for the fixture, the saved file will differ (ecm:_wasNormalizedOnLoad marker added, plus re-sorted structure). Recommend running a quick Node REPL check: import {normalizeOnLoad} from './src/normalize/index.js'; import doc from './test/fixtures/canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld' assert {type:'json'}; console.log(normalizeOnLoad(doc).wasNormalized) -- should print false.",
          "pretest:e2e wiring: playwright.config.ts webServer runs 'npm run preview' which serves dist/ui/. If dist/ui/ is stale (built before C1/C2 were applied), the e2e suite would test the old bundle. Recommend adding a 'pretest:e2e': 'npm run build:ui' script to package.json so the correct bundle is always served. This was flagged as optional in the scope constraints -- surfacing here for operator decision before CI integration.",
          "The buildNewDocument() helper uses static timestamps ('1970-01-01T00:00:00Z') because src/kernel/ is pure-function-only (no Date.now()). Task 1.6 (IRI generation) is the planned home for real UUID/timestamp injection. If the operator wants the New document to carry a meaningful creation timestamp, this requires either a Date.now() call in the UI adapter layer (permitted -- purity constraint is on src/kernel/ only) or deferring to task 1.6. Surfacing the choice here before apply."
        ],
        "summary": "Four changes implement FR-U001/FR-U002/FR-U003/FR-U029 and the AC2/AC3/AC4 Playwright coverage. C1 replaces App.tsx entirely with a stateful component (useState for project + banner text, useRef for hidden file input, three handlers). C2 appends button-group and migration-banner CSS. C3 creates the missing v0.3 Playwright fixture (reconnaissance gap F12). C4 adds the new-open-save.spec.ts file with the three AC tests. All four scope constraints are respected: kernel/migrate/normalize/validate/emit modules are untouched; src/ui imports are additive consumers; no Node-only APIs in component code (FileReader/Blob/URL.createObjectURL are browser-native); npm test vs test:e2e separation preserved.",
        "self_assessment": "uncertain"
      },
      "depends_on": [
        "urn:fnsr:task:160-recon-react-shell-2"
      ],
      "inputs": {
        "task_context": "Phase 2 task 2.1 Chain 2: implements New/Open/Save user flows + FR-U029 migration notice",
        "output_envelope_constraint": "Output wrapped: outputs.changes[] (mode=create or edit), outputs.summary, outputs.self_assessment.",
        "goal": "Propose changes[] implementing Phase 2 task 2.1 Chain 2 \u2014 covers AC2 (New\u2192Save roundtrip), AC3 (Open v0.4 roundtrip), AC4 (Open v0.3 shows migration notice). AC1 + AC5 already verified by Chain 1.",
        "implementation_directions": [
          "Extend src/ui/App.tsx (or its child components) to wire New/Open/Save buttons to handlers. Use React state hooks for the in-memory document; lift state to App level so all three buttons share the document state.",
          "FR-U001 New: button calls a helper that constructs the minimal v0.4 document object with iao:isAbout: ['ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter'] + type: ['ecm:Project', 'iao:OntologyDesignPattern'] + ecm:specVersion: '0.4' + required \u00a75 fields. Sets document state to this new doc.",
          "FR-U002 Open: <input type='file'> with onChange handler that reads file via FileReader as text, JSON.parses, calls migrate() -> normalizeOnLoad() -> validate(). On success, sets document state. If migrate() returned wasMigrated=true, surfaces FR-U029 migration notice (modal or banner).",
          "FR-U003 Save: button calls serializeVmp(document) to produce canonical text; creates Blob; creates object URL; triggers download via anchor element with download='project.jsonld'.",
          "FR-U029 migration notice: per SPEC \u00a710.4, surface a modal or banner with the migration message; only triggered when migrate returned wasMigrated true; dismissible.",
          "Tests: extend tests/playwright/shell.spec.ts (or add tests/playwright/new-open-save.spec.ts) with three new Playwright tests: AC2, AC3, AC4. Use Playwright setInputFiles + download capture (page.waitForEvent('download')) for the file IO ACs.",
          "Test fixtures: if the Phase 1 test corpus already has v0.3 + v0.4 fixtures, copy or symlink them under tests/playwright/fixtures/ (or reference directly). If not, the developer should propose creating minimal Playwright-test-private fixtures."
