    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:162-rat-react-shell-2",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change introduces three new user-facing interaction flows (FR-U001 New, FR-U002 Open, FR-U003 Save), a first-of-kind migration-notice UX (FR-U029 dismissible banner), new React state machinery, a new v0.3 fixture, and a new Playwright spec file \u00e2\u20ac\u201d none of which fall within typo-fix, formatting-consistency, terminology-tightening, or citation-format-update scope.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance (task 160) is present in UPSTREAM and the proposed four changes reconcile all 23 reconnaissance findings as follows.\n\n**C1 (App.tsx):** The before-snippet matches the current file exactly (confirmed by disk read). The after-content is a fully-wired stateful React component. Every reconnaissance gap is addressed: (F1) placeholder comment replaced with real button elements and handlers; (F2/F3) migrate() shape without wasMigrated or fromVersion is handled by dual-signal approach \u00e2\u20ac\u201d fromVersion captured from `parsed[\"ecm:specVersion\"]` BEFORE calling migrate() (for banner text), wasMigrated inferred by checking migrationReport.{addedFields, removedFields, transformedFields, info} for non-emptiness (correct: for v0.3 input, migrateV3toV4 produces non-empty addedFields and transformedFields and info pushes LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER; for v0.4 input all four arrays are empty); (F8) Blob/download wiring in handleSave correctly wraps serializeVmp output; (F9) normalizeOnLoad destructured to `const { document: normalized }`; (F10) validate() called and its return value discarded with `void` (FR-U028 deferred to task 2.8); (F7/SPEC \u00c2\u00a710.4) Save disabled only on `project === null`, never on validation findings, consistent with SPEC's statement that LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER does not block save.\n\n**FR-U029 trigger discipline confirmed:** `setMigrationBannerText` is set inside `if (wasMigrated)` and cleared to null in the else branch. The banner JSX is gated `{migrationBannerText !== null && ...}`. For any v0.4 input all migrationReport arrays are empty \u00e2\u2020\u2019 wasMigrated=false \u00e2\u2020\u2019 no banner. For v0.3 input migrateV3toV4 populates addedFields (iao:isAbout), transformedFields (type, @context, ecm:specVersion), and info (LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 wasMigrated=true \u00e2\u2020\u2019 banner with correct text. FR-U029 is triggered exclusively on wasMigrated=true per SPEC \u00c2\u00a710.4.\n\n**NFR-001/NFR-002 (static-only):** FileReader, Blob, URL.createObjectURL are browser-native APIs. No fetch, XMLHttpRequest, or server-side calls appear anywhere in the proposed component code.\n\n**Kernel/migrate/normalize/validate not modified:** C1 touches only App.tsx; C2 only App.css; C3 is a new fixture file; C4 is a new Playwright spec file. No migration, normalization, validation, or kernel source is modified.\n\n**Layer boundaries respected:** App.tsx imports from migrate/index.js, normalize/index.js, validate/index.js, kernel/canonicalize.js (consumer direction only). No reverse imports. The purity checker (confirmed by F18/reconnaissance) covers only src/kernel/ files and finds no violation. ARCHITECTURE.md assigns no enforced boundary to src/ui/. The Blob/download implementation directly in App.tsx rather than in src/adapters/ is a recognized open question (F22, SPEC \u00c2\u00a74.1.2); there is no enforced architectural rule that blocks this, and both reconnaissance and developer correctly surface it as a deferred refactoring consideration.\n\n**C3 (v0.3 fixture):** Provides ecm:specVersion '0.3', no iao:isAbout, and the SETTINGS_DEFAULTS block matching src/migrate/index.ts \u00e2\u20ac\u201d sufficient for detectSourceVersion to return '0.3', for migrateV3toV4 to fire, and for wasMigrated=true. Placement in tests/playwright/fixtures/ (not test/fixtures/) is architecturally clean.\n\n**C4 (Playwright tests):** AC2 uses waitForEvent+click download capture. AC3/AC4 use setInputFiles (confirmed available in Playwright ^1.44.0 per F17). AC4 asserts banner visibility, `toContainText(\"migrated from v0.3 to v0.4\")` (substring of the full banner text \u00e2\u20ac\u201d correct), and dismiss removes the banner. The [download] destructuring pattern is the standard Playwright recommendation for blob-URL downloads.\n\n**TypeScript type safety:** `useState<string | null>` for banner text; `ProgressEvent<FileReader>` for onload; null-check `!== null` on JSX conditional (avoids rendering '0' or 'null'); `as Record<string, unknown>` on JSON.parse (standard); `void validate(normalized)` (explicit discard, TypeScript-valid for a synchronous function whose return is intentionally unused). No gap-13 violations identified.\n\n**Remaining open risks (non-blocking):** (1) AC3 bytewise identity assumes the v0.4 fixture is already in canonical serializeVmp form \u00e2\u20ac\u201d requires a runtime check to confirm normalizeOnLoad returns wasNormalized=false for that fixture (reconnaissance F14; developer open question #3). This is a known conditional risk, not a design flaw; the test is structurally correct. (2) pretest:e2e build hook is absent \u00e2\u20ac\u201d developer open question #4 correctly surfaces this as an operator decision before CI integration. (3) buildNewDocument() uses epoch timestamps \u00e2\u20ac\u201d purity constraint applies only to src/kernel/, so this is advisory.\n\nAll four changes are internally consistent, reconciled against all 23 reconnaissance findings, and correctly scoped to the FR-U001/U002/U003/FR-U029 surface without touching FR-U028 or any subsequent task scope.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
