        "bankings": [
          {
            "id": "B1",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "When a library function (migrate()) does not return an explicit 'wasMigrated' boolean, the adapter layer can use a dual-signal approach: capture the source version from the raw document BEFORE calling migrate() for user-facing text (banner message), while determining the trigger condition (wasMigrated) by checking whether any migrationReport output arrays are non-empty. The two signals serve distinct purposes \u00e2\u20ac\u201d fromVersion drives message content; migrationReport non-emptiness drives the display predicate \u00e2\u20ac\u201d and the pattern remains correct even if the library adds new report array categories in future migrations."
          },
          {
            "id": "B2",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "UI-adapter-layer test fixtures (Playwright inputs such as minimal-v0.3.jsonld) belong in a test-adjacency directory (tests/playwright/fixtures/) rather than in the canonical-snapshot fixture directory (test/fixtures/). The canonical fixture directory holds only snapshots that the kernel's determinism/snapshot tests depend on; placing UI-test fixtures there conflates two fixture audiences and creates a maintenance hazard when the canonical fixture set changes. This placement convention should be treated as an explicit project discipline."
          },
          {
            "id": "B3",
            "category": "methodology-refinement-candidate",
            "content": "Using the TypeScript `void` operator to call a pure synchronous function whose return value is explicitly deferred to a later implementation task (e.g., `void validate(normalized)` with a comment citing the deferred task ID) is a clean signaling pattern. It distinguishes intentional discard from accidental omission, communicates the deferred-scope boundary at the call site, and avoids linting noise from unused-variable rules \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all without introducing placeholder state. This pattern is worth formalizing as a project convention for any Phase N function call whose result display is scoped to Phase N+M."
          }
        ]
      },
