        "summary": "The left sidebar in src/ui/App.tsx (post-Chain-2) is a pure placeholder: a single <p> element with text 'Term Manager -- task 2.2' inside the existing <aside class=\"gw-sidebar\" data-testid=\"gw-sidebar\"> element. The sidebar container CSS (240px wide, overflow-y: auto, padding 0.75rem) is already defined in App.css. There is no src/ui/components/ subdirectory and no prior extracted component file \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the entire UI lives in App.tsx. The term object schema (SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.7) has fields id, type, rdfs:label, rdfs:comment, rdfs:subClassOf/rdfs:subPropertyOf, ecm:source, ecm:ontologyId, ecm:createdAt, ecm:updatedAt; ecm:source is the source-indicator field name with three allowed values (ecm:imported-ontology, ecm:project-created, ecm:system-starter-example). No typed accessor for ecm:terms entries exists in src/kernel/ or src/normalize/; existing emit and refactor code reads project[\"ecm:terms\"] directly as an untyped array. A label-derivation fallback (rdfs:label ?? id) exists in triple-narration.ts but is not specified in SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.7 or IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.2; TERM_WITHOUT_LABEL is a validation warning (not an error), so label-absent terms are structurally valid. All four existing fixtures (canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld, two malformed fixtures, minimal-v0.3.jsonld) have empty ecm:terms arrays \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no fixture demonstrates any ecm:source value or any term shape. A new fixture with 2 classes + 1 OP + 1 DP covering at minimum ecm:project-created (and ideally all three ecm:source values) must be created for task 2.2 Playwright tests. The AC in IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.2 specifies the source-indicator must appear as a CSS class or aria-label assertion.",
