        "open_questions": [
          "The fixture ecm:ontologyId is null for the ecm:imported-ontology term (HasRole). Validate() may emit an ontology-reference warning. This is acceptable since error display is deferred to task 2.8, but the operator should confirm no blocking validation error is defined for a null ontologyId on an imported term.",
          "The TermEntry interface types 'type' as string. SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.7 specifies single-string type for term objects; if a non-conforming document has an array type on a term, the filter (t.type === 'owl:Class') will not match it. This is a silent miss, not a crash. Raise for task 2.3 if needed.",
          "The fixture id urn:uuid:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000030 is a synthetic zero-padded UUID. If a future roundtrip test is added for this fixture, operator should confirm the fixture passes serializeVmp idempotency (normalizeOnLoad wasNormalized: false). The canonical key ordering in C6 was derived by tracing vmpCanonicalizeObject but has not been machine-verified."
        ],
        "summary": "Six changes implement task 2.2: (C1) new TermSidebar.tsx component in src/ui/ partitioning ecm:terms into three typed sections with IRI-tail label fallback and source-indicator badges carrying both CSS class and aria-label; (C2+C3) App.tsx wired to import and render TermSidebar, replacing the placeholder, with no new state (project prop passed directly); (C4) App.css extended with TermSidebar layout and badge variant styles; (C5) new Playwright spec tests/playwright/term-sidebar.spec.ts covering AC1 (section item counts) and AC2 (project-created badge visibility + class assertion); (C6) canonical v0.4 fixture with 2 classes / 1 OP / 1 DP covering all three ecm:source values, key-ordered per SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.3.",
