      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:167-rat-term-sidebar",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal introduces a new React component file (src/ui/TermSidebar.tsx), new Playwright test coverage, a new canonical fixture, CSS additions, and an import wire-up \u00e2\u20ac\u201d collectively a new visual surface implementing FR-U004/FR-U005, well outside the editorial-correction scope of typo or formatting changes.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present (urn:fnsr:task:165-recon-term-sidebar). All six changes are evaluated and ratified:\n\n**C1 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d TermSidebar.tsx (new file, src/ui/):** Addresses F3/F4 (no prior components/ dir; developer chose sibling-file pattern, resolving recon open question 1 in the maintainable direction). TermEntry interface covers the SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.7 fields used by the sidebar (id, type, rdfs:label, ecm:source); gap-13 caution observed \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the `type` field is `string` rather than a closed union, acknowledged by developer as a silent-miss risk acceptable for Phase 2. The toTermEntry guard is correct. partitionTerms reads project[\"ecm:terms\"] as unknown[] \u00e2\u2020\u2019 TermEntry[], consistent with F12 (same pattern as triple-narration.ts and markdown.ts). iriTail fallback matches triple-narration.ts precedent (F13); TERM_WITHOUT_LABEL is a warning not an error (F14) so label-absent terms are valid inputs. FR-U004 covered: three TermSection components, always rendered. FR-U005 covered: SourceBadge emits both CSS modifier class (gw-badge--{variant}) and aria-label={raw ecm: source value}, satisfying AC2's 'CSS class OR aria-label' contract. Empty-state behaviour is invariant \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all sections always render; zero-item sections show 'No {title.toLowerCase()} yet' text rather than hiding, consistent with progressive-disclosure UI intent. Layer boundaries: TermSidebar imports nothing from src/kernel/, src/composition/, or src/adapters/; the component receives the already-processed project prop from App-level useState \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no boundary violation.\n\n**C2 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d App.tsx import addition:** before snippet matches file exactly (lines 1\u00e2\u20ac\u201c3). Import is placed after App.css import, before migrate import \u00e2\u20ac\u201d logical UI-layer import grouping. The .js extension is consistent with the project's ESM import convention.\n\n**C3 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d App.tsx placeholder replacement:** before snippet matches file exactly (lines 186\u00e2\u20ac\u201c188). Passes project prop (already Record<string,unknown>|null at App level per F2); no new state introduced.\n\n**C4 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d App.css TermSidebar styles:** before snippet matches the migration-dismiss block exactly (lines 131\u00e2\u20ac\u201c139). New rules are additive and consistent with the existing color palette (#e2e8f0 borders, #64748b secondary text, Tailwind-compatible hex values). Badge variants cover all three ecm:source values plus an unknown fallback.\n\n**C5 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d term-sidebar.spec.ts (new Playwright test):** follows existing test patterns from F17/F18 (page.goto('/'), setInputFiles, await save enabled, getByTestId scoped queries). AC1 test asserts per-section item counts (2/1/1). AC2 test asserts aria-label='ecm:project-created' badge is visible and carries gw-badge--project-created class \u00e2\u20ac\u201d both assertion mechanisms required by IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.2. Fixture referenced via process.cwd() + tests/playwright/fixtures path construction, consistent with V03_FIXTURE pattern in new-open-save.spec.ts.\n\n**C6 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld fixture:** canonical v0.4 form verified against SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.3 rules: (1) @context identical to canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld reference fixture; (2) top-level key order @context \u00e2\u2020\u2019 id \u00e2\u2020\u2019 type \u00e2\u2020\u2019 ecm:specVersion \u00e2\u2020\u2019 alphabetical remainder correct (ecm:createdAt, ecm:instances, ecm:layouts, ecm:literalAssertions, ecm:name, ecm:ontologies, ecm:relations, ecm:serializations, ecm:snapshots, ecm:terms, ecm:updatedAt, iao:isAbout); (3) nested term object keys all alphabetical (ecm:createdAt < ecm:ontologyId < ecm:source < ecm:updatedAt < id < rdfs:label < type); (4) terms sorted by id (AgeProperty < HasRole < Organization < Person lexicographically); (5) no BOM; LF line endings; UTF-8; no fractional timestamps. Covers all three ecm:source values (ecm:project-created \u00c3\u20142, ecm:imported-ontology \u00c3\u20141, ecm:system-starter-example \u00c3\u20141) and all three type values (owl:Class \u00c3\u20142, owl:ObjectProperty \u00c3\u20141, owl:DatatypeProperty \u00c3\u20141), satisfying F15/F16/F19. Developer open question 3 (roundtrip idempotency not machine-verified) is noted \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the key ordering was derived by tracing vmpCanonicalizeObject manually; this is a minor advisory tracked in developer open questions, not a blocking ratification concern.",
