            "claim": "The SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.8 cited in the task inputs is titled 'Refactor vs. Create New' (the UI modal choice between 'Refactor IRI' and 'Create New Term/Instance'); the namespace/slug/uniqueness-check IRI generation policy is defined in \u00c2\u00a75.5 (settings object), not \u00c2\u00a713.8.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "1027-1034",
                "excerpt": "### 13.8 Refactor vs. Create New\n\nIn the UI, editing an IRI offers a single explicit choice:\n- **Refactor IRI:** update this identifier and all project references.\n- **Create New Term/Instance:** preserve the old identifier and create a new resource.\n\nThe default is \"Refactor IRI\" with a confirmation dialog showing affected references."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F4",
            "claim": "The IRI refactor helper `refactorIri(project, oldIri, newIri): RefactorResult` is implemented in `src/refactor/index.ts`; it returns the modified project document, `referenceCount` (count of individual field replacements across `ecm:classIris`, `ecm:predicateIri`, `ecm:subjectIri`, `ecm:objectIri`), `affectedEntityTypes` (deduplicated sorted list), and a `collision` report when `newIri` already exists as an entity `id`.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/refactor/index.ts",
                "lines": "57-83",
                "excerpt": "export interface RefactorResult { project: Record<string, unknown>; oldIri: string; newIri: string; referenceCount: number; affectedEntityTypes: string[]; collision?: CollisionReport; }"
              },
              {
                "file": "src/refactor/index.ts",
                "lines": "157-268",
                "excerpt": "export function refactorIri(project, oldIri, newIri): RefactorResult { ... }"
              }
