        "summary": "Task 2.3 (Term CRUD) has two solid kernel-layer anchors: `generateIri()` in `src/iri/index.ts` (UUID generation, callable for the Add form's IRI auto-generation) and `refactorIri()` in `src/refactor/index.ts` (returns both the modified document and `referenceCount`/`affectedEntityTypes` for the confirmation dialog). The SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.5 slug/namespace IRI pattern (`ecm:baseIri`, `ecm:pattern`, etc.) is not implemented in `src/iri/` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the current `generateIri` produces only `urn:uuid:<UUID>` forms. The source-indicator field is `\"ecm:source\"` on term entries; `\"ecm:project-created\"` is editable, `\"ecm:imported-ontology\"` is read-only; the existing `term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld` fixture contains an imported-ontology term (HasRole) and is directly reusable for AC4. On the UI side, there are no dialog, modal, or form UI primitives anywhere in `src/ui/`; no UI component library is present in `package.json`; and `TermSidebar`'s `TermSidebarProps` exposes no mutation callback \u00e2\u20ac\u201d App.tsx must be extended to wire CRUD. The `TermEntry` interface lacks `rdfs:comment`, which the edit form requires. `buildNewDocument()` omits `ecm:settings`, so the Add form cannot read a project namespace and must default to UUIDv4. The `collectSemanticEntityIds` helper needed for duplicate-IRI checking is unexported. The cited \u00c2\u00a713.8 in the task inputs describes the Refactor-vs-Create-New UI choice, not the namespace/slug policy (which lives in \u00c2\u00a75.5). The work volume is structurally heavier than task 2.2: three Add-form variants, one Edit-form, one confirmation dialog, and one read-only stub mode, each with Playwright coverage \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this gap between the two tasks' complexity is a factual observation the developer's `self_assessment` should address.",
