          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/term-crud.spec.ts",
            "describe": "Add Object Property and Add Datatype Property: same flow as AC1 but via gw-btn-add-object-property and gw-btn-add-datatype-property; assert owl:ObjectProperty / owl:DatatypeProperty type in ecm:terms after save."
          }
        ],
        "open_questions": [
          "src/iri/index.ts uses `import { createHash, randomUUID } from 'node:crypto'` which is not importable in a Vite browser bundle. AddTermDialog.tsx therefore calls `crypto.randomUUID()` (Web Crypto API) directly. Recommended resolution: add a browser-compatible re-export to src/iri/ (e.g. `export function generateUuidUrn(): string { return 'urn:uuid:' + crypto.randomUUID(); }`) that the browser UI can import, while the existing node:crypto path remains for CLI use. This aligns with the reconnaissance finding F1 ('use the canonical IRI helper') without violating the scope constraint (src/iri/ not modified in this chain).",
          "collectSemanticEntityIds in src/refactor/index.ts is not exported (recon F13). The inline duplicate-IRI check in AddTermDialog.tsx replicates its logic. Recommended resolution for Chain B or a separate task: export this helper so the UI layer can consume it without duplication.",
          "The open question F9 from urn:fnsr:task:123-recon-iri-refactor (refactorIri does not update entity id fields) is unresolved and is load-bearing for Chain B's Edit IRI flow. The term's own id field must be replaced in the UI layer before calling refactorIri() for cascade. Operator should confirm: update term.id directly in the terms array (spread replacement) before calling refactorIri(), or request a new updateTermId helper in src/refactor/?",
          "buildNewDocument() in App.tsx has no ecm:settings block (recon F12). Add Class from a new document will always use urn:uuid: auto-generation. Acceptable for Phase 2 per recon finding F12? If so, no action needed in this chain.",
          "Chain B (AC2/AC3: Edit term label + IRI + Refactor-IRI confirmation dialog) and Chain C (AC4: imported term read-only stub) are explicitly deferred from this proposal. Each should be queued as an independent ratification+apply chain."
        ],
        "summary": "Chain A proposes 7 changes implementing the Add-term flows (FR-U006/007/008) and the AC1 Playwright test. Two new UI primitives (Dialog.tsx, AddTermDialog.tsx) plus updates to TermSidebar.tsx (full replacement: adds useState, AddTermDialog import, onTermsChange prop, section-header flex wrapper with '+' button, dialog state + sort-and-append handler), App.tsx (1-line: wire onTermsChange), and App.css (2 snippets: section-header flex layout + dialog/form CSS block). The IRI generation uses browser-native crypto.randomUUID() rather than src/iri/index.ts, which imports node:crypto and is not bundleable by Vite for the browser. Chains B (Edit + Refactor-IRI, AC2/AC3) and C (imported read-only stub, AC4) are deferred.",
        "self_assessment": "confident"
      },
      "depends_on": [
        "urn:fnsr:task:170-recon-term-crud"
      ],
      "inputs": {
        "task_context": "Phase 2 task 2.3 Chain A: Term CRUD implementation. May be scope-split per developer self_assessment.",
        "output_envelope_constraint": "Output wrapped: outputs.changes[] (mode=create or edit), outputs.summary, outputs.self_assessment.",
        "goal": "Propose changes[] implementing Phase 2 task 2.3. Cover as many of AC1-AC4 as fits the token budget; explicitly scope-split via self_assessment if needed.",
        "implementation_directions": [
          "Add Class form (FR-U006): button in TermSidebar Classes section header opens an Add Class dialog with label input + optional IRI-override input. On submit: call iri-generation helper if no override, validate uniqueness within document, append new entry to ecm:terms with type owl:Class + generated IRI + source=ecm:project-created. Document state updated via setProject.",
          "Add Object Property form (FR-U007): same pattern as Add Class, type owl:ObjectProperty.",
          "Add Datatype Property form (FR-U008): same pattern, type owl:DatatypeProperty.",
          "Edit project-created term form (FR-U009): clicking a project-created term in TermSidebar opens an Edit dialog with label, comment, and IRI fields pre-populated. If IRI is changed: BEFORE applying, open Refactor IRI confirmation dialog showing a count of references that will be updated atomically (across ecm:classIris, iao:isAbout, rdfs:subClassOf, etc., per Phase 1 refactor helper).",
          "Block imported term edit (FR-U010): clicking an imported term in TermSidebar does NOT open the Edit dialog (or the dialog opens read-only with disabled inputs). Phase 2 STUB level: source=ecm:imported-ontology terms render without a clickable edit affordance; visual indication that they are read-only (e.g., aria-disabled OR no click handler).",
          "Use the canonical IRI helper from src/iri/ (per reconnaissance findings) for both generation and refactor; do NOT reimplement.",
          "Tests: tests/playwright/term-crud.spec.ts with 4 tests (AC1-AC4). Reuse the task 2.2 fixture (term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld) where possible. Create test/fixtures/imported-terms.jsonld OR tests/playwright/fixtures/imported-term.jsonld with at least one ecm:imported-ontology term for AC4.",
          "Component organization: Add form, Edit form, Refactor-IRI dialog SHOULD each be separate components under src/ui/. Use a shared Dialog primitive component if helpful.",
          "If scope-split is necessary, recommended split is: Chain A = Add flows + AC1; Chain B = Edit + Refactor-IRI + AC2/AC3; Chain C = Imported read-only + AC4. Each chain ratifies + applies + verifies independently."
        ],
        "scope_constraints": [
          "Do NOT modify existing src/kernel/* / src/iri/* / src/refactor/* / src/migrate/* / src/normalize/* / src/validate/* \u2014 they are stable; UI consumes them",
          "Layer boundaries: src/ui/ imports kernel/iri/refactor/etc.; reverse not present",
          "TypeScript: compile cleanly per gap-13 caution; type term-entry shapes + dialog props strictly",
          "Browser purity: no Node-only APIs",
          "Fixture files MUST be canonical-form-compliant per gap-15 lesson (no BOM; LF; canonical key order; no trailing whitespace) \u2014 developer's responsibility to emit them this way (applier will preserve BOM-on-create but the fixture-content should still have no BOM in its 'after' payload \u2014 applier's BOM-on-create discipline is the substrate-side gap-15; developer-content should NOT preserve a BOM from input)",
          "Do NOT update package.json test script; keep test:e2e separation"
        ],
        "encoding_constraint": "Emit non-ASCII via \\uXXXX escapes only.",
        "scope_warning_token_limit": "LARGE substantive scope. Estimate output BEFORE emitting changes[]; if >20000 chars, scope-split via self_assessment (recommended split: Chain A = AC1; Chain B = AC2/AC3; Chain C = AC4). Self_assessment MUST state which ACs the current chain covers + which are deferred.",
        "output_shape_required": "outputs.changes[] (create-mode for new components/tests/fixtures; edit-mode for App.tsx/TermSidebar.tsx/App.css); outputs.summary; outputs.self_assessment (with scope-split decision)."
      },
      "history": [
