    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:172-rat-term-crud",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal creates two new React components (Dialog.tsx, AddTermDialog.tsx), replaces TermSidebar.tsx with an extended version carrying new state and props, wires a mutation callback in App.tsx, adds CSS classes, and introduces a new Playwright test file \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a behavioral and structural extension, not a formatting or terminology change.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:170-recon-term-crud); the refusal contract is not triggered.\n\n**Scope fidelity**: Chain A correctly bounds itself to the Add flows (FR-U006/007/008) and AC1 (Add class \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Save \u00e2\u2020\u2019 parse). AC2/AC3 (Edit label + Edit IRI / Refactor-IRI dialog) are explicitly deferred to Chain B; AC4 (imported term read-only, FR-U010) is explicitly deferred to Chain C. Deferred items are named in both open_questions and tests_recommended. The IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.3 acceptance criteria are fully accounted for across the three chains.\n\n**AC1 assertions are arithmetically correct**: The fixture (term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld) contains 4 terms (Organization: owl:Class, Person: owl:Class, HasRole: owl:ObjectProperty, AgeProperty: owl:DatatypeProperty). After adding one class, the test expects 5 total terms and 3 in the Classes section. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**Two canonical-helper bypasses \u00e2\u20ac\u201d both technically necessitated and documented**:\n1. `crypto.randomUUID()` instead of `src/iri/generateIri()`: `src/iri/index.ts` imports `import { createHash, randomUUID as nodeRandomUUID } from 'node:crypto'` (confirmed at line 20), which is not importable in a Vite browser bundle. The Web Crypto API `crypto.randomUUID()` produces semantically equivalent output (`urn:uuid:<UUIDv4>`). The developer documents the recommended resolution (browser-compatible re-export in `src/iri/`) as open_questions[0]. This must be resolved before Chain B, which will need a browser-compatible IRI generation path for the Edit flow.\n2. Inline `collectExistingIris` instead of unexported `collectSemanticEntityIds` from `src/refactor/index.ts` (recon F13, confirmed at lines 121\u00e2\u20ac\u201c132): the function is not exported; the inline `Set<string>` is a simplification appropriate for Add-form duplicate checking (existence only, not source-array identity). Developer documents this as open_questions[1] for Chain B resolution.\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.3 rule 4 compliance**: `handleAddConfirm` in the new TermSidebar.tsx sorts the updated ecm:terms array by id (lexicographic ascending) before calling onTermsChange. New urn:uuid: IRIs sort after https:// terms, preserving order. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.7 term shape compliance**: `AddTermDialog.tsx` emits `id`, `type`, `rdfs:label`, `ecm:source: 'ecm:project-created'`, `ecm:ontologyId: null`, `ecm:createdAt`, `ecm:updatedAt`. Absent fields (`rdfs:comment`, `rdfs:subClassOf`/`rdfs:subPropertyOf`) are optional in \u00c2\u00a75.7 and not required by AC1. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**FR-U010 staging is structurally sound**: In Chain A, term items are rendered as read-only `<li>` elements with no edit affordance on any item. Add affordances appear only at section-header level, guarded by the `canEdit` flag (`project !== null && onTermsChange !== undefined`). Imported terms are de-facto un-interactable in Chain A not by explicit guard but by absence of edit affordance. Chain C must add the explicit guard (no edit affordance for `ecm:imported-ontology` terms) when Chain B introduces the Edit affordance for project-created terms. The review focus concern ('not just visually disabled but un-interactable') becomes load-bearing only at Chain B\u00e2\u2020\u2019C transition.\n\n**gap-13 caution observed**: TypeScript types are sound. `HTMLDialogElement` with `.showModal()`, `.close()`, `.open`, and `addEventListener('close', ...)` are all typed under `lib: DOM` (tsconfig.ui.json line 7: `['ES2022', 'DOM', 'DOM.Iterable']`). `crypto.randomUUID()` is typed in DOM lib since ES2022. `FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>` is correctly typed. `useRef<HTMLDialogElement>(null)` + null guard before use is idiomatic React. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**gap-15 caution**: No new fixture files are introduced in Chain A. The existing `term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld` is reused (confirmed canonical: LF, no BOM in prior verification, `iao:isAbout` non-placeholder per recon F19). \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**Layer boundaries**: Dialog.tsx and AddTermDialog.tsx import only from `react` and sibling UI files (./Dialog.js). TermSidebar.tsx imports from `react` and `./AddTermDialog.js`. No imports from `src/kernel/`, `src/composition/`, or `src/adapters/`. App.tsx change C4 is a 1-line JSX prop addition with no new imports. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**Dialog cleanup pattern**: The `useEffect` in Dialog.tsx removes the `close` event listener before calling `el.close()` on unmount. This prevents the synchronous `close` event fired by `el.close()` from re-invoking `onClose` during cleanup. The stable `onCloseRef` pattern ensures the effect's single-mount listener always calls the latest `onClose`. This is architecturally correct.\n\n**Refactor-IRI dialog (AC3 / Chain B)**: Recon F6 establishes the correct pattern \u00e2\u20ac\u201d call `refactorIri()` to obtain `referenceCount` for the dialog, then apply the returned `project` if user confirms. Chain B must follow this pattern; the confirmation dialog must show `referenceCount` BEFORE state mutation. Chain A does not touch this path.\n\n**before-snippet fidelity**: C3 before matches the current `src/ui/TermSidebar.tsx` content (155 lines, confirmed). C4 before `          <TermSidebar project={project} />` matches App.tsx line 188. C5 before matches the existing `.gw-term-section-title` rule in App.css. C6 before ends at `.gw-badge--unknown` block boundary in App.css.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
