          {
            "id": "F5",
            "claim": "`TermSidebar`'s public props interface does not include any per-term click callback; the only mutation callback is `onTermsChange?: (project: Record<string, unknown>) => void`.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/ui/TermSidebar.tsx",
                "lines": "22-29",
                "excerpt": "interface TermSidebarProps {\n  project: Record<string, unknown> | null;\n  /**\n   * Called with the updated project document after a term is added.\n   * When undefined the Add buttons are hidden (read-only mode).\n   */\n  onTermsChange?: (project: Record<string, unknown>) => void;\n}"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F6",
            "claim": "The `TermEntry` interface in TermSidebar.tsx (the local type used for rendering) does not include `rdfs:comment`; it only declares `id`, `type`, `rdfs:label?`, and `ecm:source?`.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/ui/TermSidebar.tsx",
                "lines": "15-21",
                "excerpt": "interface TermEntry {\n  id: string;\n  type: string;\n  \"rdfs:label\"?: string;\n  \"ecm:source\"?: string;\n}"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F7",
            "claim": "`refactorIri()` in src/refactor/index.ts has NO dry-run or count-only mode; it always runs the full cascade and returns the modified project document alongside `referenceCount` and `affectedEntityTypes`.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/refactor/index.ts",
                "lines": "157-161",
                "excerpt": "export function refactorIri(\n  project: Record<string, unknown>,\n  oldIri: string,\n  newIri: string,\n): RefactorResult {"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F8",
            "claim": "`RefactorResult` has five fields: `project: Record<string, unknown>` (modified or unmodified on collision/no-op), `oldIri: string`, `newIri: string`, `referenceCount: number` (zero on collision or no-op), `affectedEntityTypes: string[]` (deduplicated sorted array; empty on collision or no-op), and an optional `collision?: CollisionReport`.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/refactor/index.ts",
                "lines": "57-83",
                "excerpt": "export interface RefactorResult {\n  project: Record<string, unknown>;\n  oldIri: string;\n  newIri: string;\n  referenceCount: number;\n  affectedEntityTypes: string[];\n  collision?: CollisionReport;\n}"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F9",
            "claim": "Calling `refactorIri()` with the OLD IRI value as both `oldIri` and `newIri` is an explicit idempotent no-op path (returns unmodified `project`, `referenceCount: 0`, `affectedEntityTypes: []`) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the caller can use this to obtain the count for the confirmation dialog only if `newIri` is known at the time of the count request; it cannot query count for a tentative new IRI without executing the full cascade.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/refactor/index.ts",
                "lines": "162-165",
                "excerpt": "// -- Idempotent no-op: A->A is always a no-op (SPEC section 21.1) --\nif (oldIri === newIri) {\n  return { project, oldIri, newIri, referenceCount: 0, affectedEntityTypes: [] };\n}"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F10",
            "claim": "To obtain the affected-reference count for a Refactor-IRI confirmation dialog without committing the change, a caller must call `refactorIri(project, oldIri, newIri)` and read `result.referenceCount` and `result.affectedEntityTypes` while discarding `result.project` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the function is a pure function (no I/O, no side effects) so the result document may be safely discarded.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/refactor/index.ts",
                "lines": "1-32",
                "excerpt": "/**\n * Pure function: no I/O, no Date.now(), no Math.random().\n * Layer boundary: MUST NOT import from src/adapters/ or src/composition/.\n */"
              },
              {
                "file": "src/refactor/index.ts",
                "lines": "253-268",
                "excerpt": "const resultProject: Record<string, unknown> = {\n  ...project,\n  \"ecm:instances\": newInstances,\n  \"ecm:relations\": newRelations,\n  \"ecm:literalAssertions\": newLiterals,\n};\nreturn {\n  project: resultProject,\n  oldIri,\n  newIri,\n  referenceCount,\n  affectedEntityTypes: [...affectedTypes].sort(),\n};"
              }
            ],
