            "claim": "SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.2 requires that on a project-created term IRI edit, all instance `ecm:classIris`, relation `ecm:predicateIri`, and literal-assertion `ecm:predicateIri` entries referencing the old IRI are cascade-updated; \u00c2\u00a713.8 specifies that the default UI action is `Refactor IRI` with a confirmation dialog showing affected references before apply.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "987-993",
                "excerpt": "### 13.2 Project-Created Term IRI Change\nIf a project-created class IRI is edited as a refactor, all instance `ecm:classIris` entries referencing the old IRI are updated to the new IRI.\n...\nThe user is warned before the cascade with: old IRI, new IRI, number of affected references, list of affected entity types."
              },
