        "summary": "Chain A delivered a clean three-component hierarchy: `Dialog` (native-`<dialog>` primitive, 4-prop interface), `AddTermDialog` (form component wrapping Dialog, 4-prop interface), and `TermSidebar` (sidebar with Add flows wired, `onTermsChange` callback propagated through App.tsx). The current `TermSidebar` renders each term as a plain `<li>` with no `onClick` handler and no per-term-click callback in its public interface \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Chain B must add both. `EditTermDialog` does not exist yet (F21 gap). FR-U009 covers label, comment, and IRI fields; `rdfs:comment` is canonical per SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.7 and in the semantic-predicate allowlist, but is absent from all existing UI components (AddTermDialog omits it; TermEntry local type omits it). The `refactorIri()` function in `src/refactor/index.ts` has no dry-run mode; obtaining the affected-reference count for the confirmation dialog requires calling `refactorIri(project, oldIri, newIri)` and reading `result.referenceCount` + `result.affectedEntityTypes` while discarding `result.project` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d safe because the function is a pure function with no side effects. `collectSemanticEntityIds` inside `src/refactor/index.ts` is unexported; `AddTermDialog` already works around this with an inline duplicate. SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.8 specifies 'Refactor IRI' as the default action with a pre-apply confirmation dialog showing old IRI, new IRI, count, and entity types. SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.5 requires collision detection before apply; `refactorIri()` implements this via the `collision?` field on its return value.",
