        "open_questions": [
          "Should `EditTermDialog` be a separate file from `AddTermDialog`, or should a single shared component accept an optional `existingTerm` prop to switch between 'add' and 'edit' semantics? (The two share label + IRI fields but differ in initial state population, submit handler, and title.)",
          "For the Refactor-IRI confirmation dialog (AC3), should the count be computed eagerly when the user edits the IRI field in EditTermDialog (on every keystroke/blur) or only when the user clicks 'Confirm'? The pure-function nature of `refactorIri()` makes eager computation safe, but the UX latency tradeoff is an open question.",
          "Should the `TermSection` component receive a per-term `onTermClick?: (term: TermEntry) => void` prop, or should `TermSidebar` restructure the `<li>` rendering inline to add click handling without adding a new callback slot to `TermSection`?",
          "AC4 in Chain C specifies that imported terms should not be clickable (only project-created terms open EditTermDialog); should this be enforced via conditional `onClick` (present vs absent) or via a disabled/read-only visual state? The current `SourceBadge` already has the `ecm:source` value available at render time.",
          "Is `rdfs:comment` in the EditTermDialog a required field (submit blocked if empty) or optional (matching the SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.7 schema where it appears in the example but the section text does not state it is required)?"
        ],
        "scope_assessment": "Investigated all five files in src/ui/, src/refactor/index.ts, project/SPEC.md (FR-U009, \u00c2\u00a75.7, \u00c2\u00a713.2, \u00c2\u00a713.3, \u00c2\u00a713.5, \u00c2\u00a713.8), and project/ROADMAP.md (Phase 2 scope); also spot-checked src/projection/index.ts and src/emit/turtle.ts for rdfs:comment handling; did not investigate test files, CSS/styling, tsconfig.ui.json, src/iri/index.ts, or Chain C task definitions."
