          "Reconnaissance OQ5: rdfs:comment in EditTermDialog is optional (empty string clears the field; delete updated['rdfs:comment'] removes it). SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.7 shows it in the example but does not state 'required'. If it should be required, the submit guard needs a non-empty check for comment.",
          "Chain C (AC4): imported terms are currently inert (no onClick) per Chain B implementation directions. Chain C should add disabled state + aria-disabled to the <li> for imported/starter terms to satisfy FR-U010's read-only stub requirement. The current gw-term-item--clickable CSS class addition in C4 leaves room for a gw-term-item--readonly class in Chain C.",
