        "implementation_directions": [
          "EditTermDialog.tsx: new component under src/ui/ that opens when a project-created term in TermSidebar is clicked. Pre-populates label, comment (rdfs:comment if present, empty string otherwise), and IRI from the term entry. On submit: if IRI unchanged, update label + comment in place and setProject. If IRI changed, open a Refactor-IRI confirmation sub-dialog showing the reference count from src/refactor/ refactorIri() \u2014 display 'This will update N references across <entity-types>. Continue?' with Confirm + Cancel buttons. On Confirm: apply the refactor (use the already-computed modified document) and setProject. On Cancel: stay in the Edit dialog without applying.",
          "TermSidebar.tsx edit: add onClick handler for project-created terms (source-indicator == 'ecm:project-created') that opens EditTermDialog with the clicked term. Imported terms (FR-U010) are NOT made clickable yet \u2014 Chain C handles the read-only blocking explicitly with disabled state + aria-disabled. Chain B's no-onClick for imported terms is sufficient for now.",
