      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change introduces a new UI component (EditTermDialog.tsx), modifies TermSidebar.tsx's public component API, adds a new test fixture, and adds new Playwright acceptance tests \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all implementing FR-U009 functionality that did not previously exist; this is functional scope addition, not terminology tightening or formatting.",
        "rationale": "All five review-focus areas pass evaluation against the current codebase state and reconnaissance evidence.\n\n**1. Reconnaissance reconciliation (task 175):** Every load-bearing gap finding is addressed. F21 (no EditTermDialog.tsx) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C1 creates it. F4/F22 (TermSection <li> has no onClick, TermSection API has no per-term callback) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C4 adds `onTermClick?: (term: TermEntry) => void` with project-created-only activation. F5/F17 (TermSidebar public interface has no per-term click callback; App.tsx has no onTermEdit) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 the proposal correctly routes click handling internally inside TermSidebar (editTerm state in C5, handleEditConfirm in C6) so App.tsx requires no change \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the existing `onTermsChange` propagation pattern from Chain A covers the state-update path. F6 (TermEntry lacks rdfs:comment) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C3 adds it. F12/F13/F14 (rdfs:comment is canonical per SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.7 + \u00c2\u00a76.2 allowlist but absent from all UI files; FR-U009 requires label + comment + IRI) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C1 includes rdfs:comment textarea. F7/F8/F10 (refactorIri has no dry-run mode; pure function; safe to call and discard result.project) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C1 calls refactorIri(project, originalIri, trimmedIri) on IRI-change submit, reads result.referenceCount + result.affectedEntityTypes for the confirmation body, stores result as pendingRefactor, and discards result.project if the user cancels. F20 (collision path: caller must check result.collision before applying) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 C1 checks `result.collision !== undefined` and shows inline error instead of advancing to confirm phase.\n\n**2. FR-U009 coverage and Refactor-IRI confirmation sequencing:** All three fields (label, comment, IRI) are editable. rdfs:comment is optional (empty string removes the field via `delete updated['rdfs:comment']`), consistent with SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.7 where rdfs:comment appears in the example but is not declared required. The confirmation gate is correctly placed: `onConfirm` fires only inside `handleConfirmRefactor`, which is reached only after the user explicitly clicks Confirm in the confirm-refactor phase \u00e2\u20ac\u201d not at form submit time. This satisfies SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.8's 'confirmation dialog showing affected references before apply' requirement. The `applyTermEdit` function correctly updates the term's own `id` in ecm:terms for the IRI-change path (refactorIri updates reference fields only, not entity id fields; C1 composes both correctly in handleConfirmRefactor).\n\n**3. AC2 + AC3 test credibility:** AC2 is a full round-trip: click project-created Person (which has role=button after C4), edit label, submit (IRI unchanged \u00e2\u2020\u2019 label-only path, no confirmation), verify dialog closes, save, download, parse JSON, assert rdfs:label equals 'Person (Edited)'. SIDEBAR_FIXTURE has Person with ecm:source='ecm:project-created' confirmed. The fs import exists at line 3 of the current test file. AC3: load CROSS_REFS_FIXTURE (C8, Person class + one instance with ecm:classIris=['https://example.org/ontology/Person']), click Person, change IRI, submit, assert gw-dialog-confirm-refactor appears, extract count from the confirmation body text. The fixture guarantees referenceCount=1 (one instance classIris entry matching the old IRI). The regex `/update\\s+(\\d+)\\s+reference/` matches the C1 template 'This will update {referenceCount} reference{...} across...'. The fixture's @context is complete (ecm:classIris with @container:@set, @type:@id) and matches the existing SIDEBAR_FIXTURE context shape.\n\n**4. Dialog.tsx primitive reuse:** C1 imports `Dialog` from `./Dialog.js` (Chain A). The confirm-refactor phase renders a second `<Dialog>` with testId='gw-dialog-confirm-refactor'. No parallel dialog primitive is created.\n\n**5. Layer boundaries:** src/ui/EditTermDialog.tsx imports from src/refactor/index.ts. The refactor module is a lower-layer pure-function module (its header declares 'Layer boundary: MUST NOT import from src/adapters/ or src/composition/'). A UI component importing from a lower-layer pure module is permitted by the layer rules (the prohibition runs bottom-up only: kernel must not import from adapters). The existing AddTermDialog.tsx establishes the same pattern. The new Date().toISOString() call in applyTermEdit is in src/ui/ (not src/kernel/), so the purity constraint does not apply \u00e2\u20ac\u201d AddTermDialog.tsx uses the same pattern at its line 81.\n\n**Minor concerns (non-blocking):** SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.8 describes two options ('Refactor IRI' and 'Create New Term/Instance'), but the proposal implements only the Refactor IRI path (the declared default). The 'Create New' path is not scoped to FR-U009 Chain B and is not blocked by the current changes. The developer's self_assessment 'uncertain' is noted; structural review finds no defect. The ecm:terms array is not re-sorted after an IRI edit: this is acceptable because the canonical serializer downstream handles sort ordering, and the SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.3 sort requirement applies to canonical output, not React state. The C8 fixture instance shape (ecm:classIris, ecm:createdAt, ecm:updatedAt, id, type only) may generate validate() findings when task 2.8 surfaces errors, but this is a non-blocking forward-track for that task.",
