        "bankings": [
          {
            "id": "B1",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "Compute-for-preview, discard-result pattern for pure functions in UI confirmation flows: when a pure function (refactorIri) produces both a primary output (the modified project document) and secondary outputs (referenceCount, affectedEntityTypes, collision status), a UI component can call it once at submit time to obtain all side-outputs for display in a confirmation dialog, storing the full result as pendingRefactor, and then either discard result.project (if the user cancels) or apply it (if the user confirms). This avoids a separate dry-run API on the pure function while keeping the confirmation-to-apply transition atomic within React state \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the pendingRefactor stores the pre-computed cascade so the confirm path does not need to re-execute the cascade. The pattern is safe only when the underlying function is demonstrably pure (no I/O, no side effects), and the developer must document this constraint at the call site."
          },
          {
            "id": "B2",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "Two-phase dialog state machine for sequential confirmation decisions: using a local React state enum (Phase = 'edit' | 'confirm-refactor') plus a stashed intermediate result (pendingRefactor: RefactorResult | null) within a single component mount implements a sequential confirmation flow without mounting and unmounting multiple dialog components. The edit form renders when phase='edit'; the confirmation body renders when phase='confirm-refactor' and pendingRefactor is non-null. Cancel transitions back to 'edit' and clears pendingRefactor; Confirm applies the stashed result. This approach keeps all confirmation context co-located with the form state, avoids intermediate-result threading through parent components, and uses a single Dialog primitive for both phases \u00e2\u20ac\u201d consistent with Chain A's mount/unmount visibility pattern."
          }
        ]
      },
