      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:181-dev-term-crud-c",
      "agent": "developer",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "changes": [
          {
            "id": "C1",
            "file": "src/ui/TermSidebar.tsx",
            "rationale": "Add `isImported` derived variable and `aria-disabled=\"true\"` attribute to the <li> rendered for ecm:imported-ontology terms. This is the single affirmative structural read-only signal required by FR-U010 Phase 2 stub. The attribute is absent (undefined) for project-created and starter-example terms, preserving all existing behavior. `aria-disabled` is chosen over a CSS class because it is directly assertable by Playwright's `toHaveAttribute` without CSS computation, and it is the canonical ARIA signal for 'this interactive surface is disabled'. The `isClickable` guard already ensures no onClick fires; `aria-disabled` adds the explicit machine-readable declaration.",
            "before": "            // Only project-created terms are clickable; imported/starter are not.\n            const isClickable =\n              onTermClick !== undefined &&\n              term[\"ecm:source\"] === \"ecm:project-created\";\n            return (\n              <li\n                key={term.id}\n                className={\n                  isClickable\n                    ? \"gw-term-item gw-term-item--clickable\"\n                    : \"gw-term-item\"\n                }\n                data-testid=\"gw-term-item\"\n                role={isClickable ? \"button\" : undefined}\n                tabIndex={isClickable ? 0 : undefined}\n                onClick={isClickable ? () => { onTermClick(term); } : undefined}",
            "after": "            // Only project-created terms are clickable; imported/starter are not.\n            const isClickable =\n              onTermClick !== undefined &&\n              term[\"ecm:source\"] === \"ecm:project-created\";\n            // Imported-ontology terms carry an affirmative read-only signal (FR-U010; Chain C).\n            const isImported = term[\"ecm:source\"] === \"ecm:imported-ontology\";\n            return (\n              <li\n                key={term.id}\n                className={\n                  isClickable\n                    ? \"gw-term-item gw-term-item--clickable\"\n                    : \"gw-term-item\"\n                }\n                data-testid=\"gw-term-item\"\n                role={isClickable ? \"button\" : undefined}\n                tabIndex={isClickable ? 0 : undefined}\n                aria-disabled={isImported ? \"true\" : undefined}\n                onClick={isClickable ? () => { onTermClick(term); } : undefined}",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C2",
            "file": "tests/playwright/fixtures/imported-term.jsonld",
            "rationale": "New fixture for AC4. Contains one ecm:imported-ontology owl:Class ('Imported Class') and one ecm:project-created owl:Class ('Local Class'). The imported class is the click target for the read-only assertion; the project-created class provides structural completeness (a real project would never have only imported terms). UUID ...000040 is the next sequential stub value after the existing fixtures (...0030, ...0031, ...0032). Canonical @context key order matches term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld exactly. Term entry key order: ecm:createdAt / ecm:ontologyId / ecm:source / ecm:updatedAt / id / rdfs:label / type (alphabetical, matching existing fixtures). Terms sorted by id (ImportedClass before LocalClass). No BOM; LF line endings.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "{\n  \"@context\": {\n    \"cco\": \"https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/\",\n    \"ecm\": \"https://edgecanonical.org/ns/modeler#\",\n    \"ecm:classIris\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:instances\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:isSerializationOf\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:layouts\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:literalAssertions\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:objectIri\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:ontologies\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:predicateIri\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:relations\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:serializations\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:snapshots\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:subjectIri\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:terms\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"iao\": \"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/iao#\",\n    \"iao:isAbout\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"id\": \"@id\",\n    \"owl\": \"http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#\",\n    \"rdf\": \"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\",\n    \"rdfs\": \"http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#\",\n    \"rdfs:subClassOf\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"rdfs:subPropertyOf\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"type\": \"@type\",\n    \"xsd\": \"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#\"\n  },\n  \"id\": \"urn:uuid:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000040\",\n  \"type\": [\n    \"ecm:Project\",\n    \"iao:OntologyDesignPattern\"\n  ],\n  \"ecm:specVersion\": \"0.4\",\n  \"ecm:createdAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"ecm:instances\": [],\n  \"ecm:layouts\": [],\n  \"ecm:literalAssertions\": [],\n  \"ecm:name\": \"Imported Term Fixture (AC4)\",\n  \"ecm:ontologies\": [],\n  \"ecm:relations\": [],\n  \"ecm:serializations\": [],\n  \"ecm:snapshots\": [],\n  \"ecm:terms\": [\n    {\n      \"ecm:createdAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"ecm:ontologyId\": null,\n      \"ecm:source\": \"ecm:imported-ontology\",\n      \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"id\": \"https://example.org/ontology/ImportedClass\",\n      \"rdfs:label\": \"Imported Class\",\n      \"type\": \"owl:Class\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"ecm:createdAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"ecm:ontologyId\": null,\n      \"ecm:source\": \"ecm:project-created\",\n      \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"id\": \"https://example.org/ontology/LocalClass\",\n      \"rdfs:label\": \"Local Class\",\n      \"type\": \"owl:Class\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"iao:isAbout\": [\n    \"https://example.org/subjects/ImportedTermTest\"\n  ]\n}\n",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C3",
            "file": "tests/playwright/term-crud.spec.ts",
            "rationale": "Remove the '(deferred)' label from Chain B and Chain C lines in the module JSDoc header, and add the FR-U010 reference to the Chain C description. Both chains are now implemented in this file.",
            "before": " * Chain B (deferred): AC2 (Edit label) + AC3 (Edit IRI / Refactor-IRI dialog).\n * Chain C (deferred): AC4 (Imported term read-only stub).\n */",
            "after": " * Chain B: AC2 (Edit label) + AC3 (Edit IRI / Refactor-IRI dialog).\n * Chain C: AC4 (Imported term read-only stub; FR-U010).\n */",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C4",
            "file": "tests/playwright/term-crud.spec.ts",
            "rationale": "Add IMPORTED_TERM_FIXTURE path constant pointing to the new imported-term.jsonld fixture created in C2. Follows the same path.join pattern as SIDEBAR_FIXTURE and CROSS_REFS_FIXTURE above it.",
            "before": "const CROSS_REFS_FIXTURE = path.join(\n  process.cwd(),\n  \"tests\",\n  \"playwright\",\n  \"fixtures\",\n  \"term-sidebar-cross-refs.jsonld\",\n);",
            "after": "const CROSS_REFS_FIXTURE = path.join(\n  process.cwd(),\n  \"tests\",\n  \"playwright\",\n  \"fixtures\",\n  \"term-sidebar-cross-refs.jsonld\",\n);\n\nconst IMPORTED_TERM_FIXTURE = path.join(\n  process.cwd(),\n  \"tests\",\n  \"playwright\",\n  \"fixtures\",\n  \"imported-term.jsonld\",\n);",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C5",
            "file": "tests/playwright/term-crud.spec.ts",
            "rationale": "Add AC4 test inside the existing describe block. The test: (a) loads the imported-term.jsonld fixture (C2), (b) asserts aria-disabled='true' on the imported class item (the affirmative read-only signal added in C1), (c) asserts role='button' is absent on that item, (d) clicks the item and asserts EditTermDialog does not open. All three assertions together cover the FR-U010 Phase 2 stub acceptance criteria. The `filter({ hasText: 'Imported Class' })` locator pattern is consistent with how AC2/AC3 use `filter({ hasText: '...' })` to scope within a section.",
            "before": "      ).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n    },\n  );\n});",
            "after": "      ).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n    },\n  );\n\n  test(\n    \"AC4: Imported term read-only: aria-disabled present; click does not open EditTermDialog (FR-U010; Chain C)\",\n    async ({ page }) => {\n      await page.goto(\"/\");\n\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-file-input\").setInputFiles(IMPORTED_TERM_FIXTURE);\n      await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\")).toBeEnabled();\n\n      const classesSec = page.getByTestId(\"gw-term-section-classes\");\n\n      // Locate the imported class in the Classes section.\n      const importedItem = classesSec\n        .getByTestId(\"gw-term-item\")\n        .filter({ hasText: \"Imported Class\" });\n\n      // Structural read-only signal: aria-disabled=\"true\" must be present (FR-U010; Chain C).\n      await expect(importedItem).toHaveAttribute(\"aria-disabled\", \"true\");\n\n      // Imported-ontology terms must NOT carry role=\"button\".\n      await expect(importedItem).not.toHaveAttribute(\"role\", \"button\");\n\n      // Clicking the imported term must NOT open the EditTermDialog.\n      await importedItem.click();\n      await expect(\n        page.getByTestId(\"gw-dialog-edit-term\"),\n      ).not.toBeVisible();\n    },\n  );\n});",
            "scope": "minimal"
          }
        ],
        "tests_recommended": [
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/term-crud.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC4 test (C5) is the primary verification. Run `npx playwright test term-crud` to confirm all five changes wire correctly end-to-end: C1 (aria-disabled on the DOM element), C2 (fixture loaded), C4+C5 (constant + test body). Also run `npm run build` to confirm C1's TypeScript compiles cleanly (aria-disabled is a standard React HTML attribute; no type annotation needed)."
          }
        ],
        "open_questions": [
          "The CSS class gw-term-item--clickable is applied in JSX (C1 is unchanged here) but has no CSS rule (recon F4). Should cursor:pointer be added to .gw-term-item--clickable and cursor:default to the base .gw-term-item in App.css as a Phase 2 follow-up, or is that deferred to Phase 3? This proposal does not add CSS rules; the visual cursor gap remains open.",
          "Phase 3 ROADMAP line 113 lists 'Imported-term immutability enforced; project-local replacement and remap references workflow'. Does Phase 3 Chain C follow-up need richer ARIA (e.g., aria-readonly on a tooltip or popover explaining the immutability) beyond the Phase 2 aria-disabled stub? Flagging for Phase 3 chain planning."
        ],
        "summary": "Five targeted changes implement FR-U010 Phase 2 stub (imported-term read-only enforcement) and its AC4 Playwright test. C1 adds `isImported` + `aria-disabled={isImported ? \"true\" : undefined}` to the TermSidebar <li> for ecm:imported-ontology terms \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the single affirmative structural read-only signal. C2 creates a minimal canonical-form fixture with one imported owl:Class and one project-created owl:Class. C3 removes the '(deferred)' labels from the spec file header. C4 adds the IMPORTED_TERM_FIXTURE path constant. C5 adds the AC4 test asserting aria-disabled presence, absence of role='button', and no EditTermDialog on click. No kernel, IRI, or other stable-module files are touched. Layer boundaries respected.",
        "self_assessment": "confident"
