    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:182-rat-term-crud-c",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal introduces new component attribute logic (aria-disabled on imported-ontology terms in TermSidebar.tsx), a net-new Playwright fixture file, and a new test body \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all of which are behavioral and structural additions well outside formatting, terminology-tightening, or citation-format-update scope.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance evidence (task 180) is present in UPSTREAM and is sufficient to evaluate the five proposed changes. Each change is grounded in specific recon findings and the reconciliation is sound.\n\n**C1 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d TermSidebar.tsx (aria-disabled)**: The `before` snippet matches the actual file at lines 148\u00e2\u20ac\u201c163 exactly. The change adds `isImported = term[\"ecm:source\"] === \"ecm:imported-ontology\"` and `aria-disabled={isImported ? \"true\" : undefined}` to the `<li>`. This is the direct answer to recon F3 (no affirmative ARIA read-only signal) and recon open question #3 (does Phase 2 stub require an affirmative ARIA signal). The attribute is absent (undefined) for project-created and starter-example terms, so existing behavior is fully preserved. The `isClickable` guard already prevents onClick; aria-disabled adds the machine-readable declaration required by the AC4 assertion. The implementation choice of aria-disabled on a non-role `<li>` is semantically non-standard (aria-disabled is normatively defined for interactive widgets), but is acceptable for a Phase 2 stub whose primary consumer is the Playwright assertion layer \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Phase 3 can elevate to a richer ARIA contract. This is a known advisory, not blocking.\n\n**C2 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d imported-term.jsonld fixture**: The `before` is null (new file), which is correct. The @context key order was verified against term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all 25 keys match exactly in the same order. Top-level field order (id, type, ecm:specVersion, ecm:createdAt, ecm:instances, \u00e2\u20ac\u00a6, ecm:updatedAt, iao:isAbout) matches. Term entry key order (ecm:createdAt, ecm:ontologyId, ecm:source, ecm:updatedAt, id, rdfs:label, type) matches. The fixture contains one ecm:imported-ontology owl:Class ('Imported Class') and one ecm:project-created owl:Class ('Local Class') \u00e2\u20ac\u201d both in the Classes section, which directly addresses recon F11 (the existing term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld fixture has its imported term in Object Properties, not Classes). The UUID 000040 follows the established decade-gap allocation pattern (000020 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 000030 \u00e2\u2020\u2019 000040), consistent with observed fixture convention. The developer's claim of \"next sequential\" is loosely worded but the value is correct within the decade-gap model. ecm:specVersion 0.4 is consistent with all Phase 2 fixtures. Canonical-form compliance per gap-15 is confirmed.\n\n**C3 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Header comment update**: The `before` snippet (lines 11\u00e2\u20ac\u201c13 of term-crud.spec.ts) matches exactly. Removing '(deferred)' labels from Chain B and Chain C is appropriate \u00e2\u20ac\u201d both chains are now implemented. Adding the FR-U010 reference to the Chain C description is correct and traceable. Advisory: the inline component comment at TermSidebar.tsx line 104\u00e2\u20ac\u201c106 ('onTermClick fires only for project-created terms (FR-U009; Chain B)') is not updated by this chain, but that comment describes click behavior (still Chain B), not ARIA signaling (Chain C), so the omission is defensible and non-blocking.\n\n**C4 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d IMPORTED_TERM_FIXTURE constant**: The `before` snippet matches lines 23\u00e2\u20ac\u201c29 exactly. The new constant follows the same path.join pattern as SIDEBAR_FIXTURE and CROSS_REFS_FIXTURE. No issues.\n\n**C5 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d AC4 test body**: The `before` snippet matches lines 196\u00e2\u20ac\u201c201 exactly (the closing of the describe block). The test asserts three independent conditions: (a) aria-disabled='true' present on the imported class item \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the affirmative read-only signal added in C1; (b) role='button' absent \u00e2\u20ac\u201d confirming non-interactive classification; (c) click does not open gw-dialog-edit-term \u00e2\u20ac\u201d behavioral confirmation. This three-part assertion fully covers the FR-U010 Phase 2 stub acceptance criteria and directly addresses recon F15 (confirmed gap against Chain C deferred label). The `filter({ hasText: 'Imported Class' })` locator pattern is consistent with AC2/AC3 usage. One advisory: the `not.toBeVisible()` assertion on the dialog passes whether the dialog element is hidden OR absent from the DOM; if the EditTermDialog testid is never rendered (which is the case for this fixture), the assertion is vacuously true. However this is standard Playwright negative-click pattern and credible for a non-interactive element \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a click event will be dispatched, and any accidentally-attached handler would still fire before the assertion runs. Not blocking.\n\n**Recon open questions addressed**: All four recon open questions are resolved by the proposal. Q1 (which assertions for AC4) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 (a)+(b)+(c) in C5. Q2 (cursor gap accepted as Phase 2 stub) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 dev explicitly defers; CSS cursor gap remains an acknowledged open item. Q3 (affirmative ARIA signal required?) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 yes, C1 adds aria-disabled. Q4 (reuse existing fixture or new?) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 new fixture in the Classes section (correct choice, since the existing fixture's imported term is in Object Properties).\n\n**Summary**: All five `before` snippets match on-disk content. The fixture is canonical-form-compliant. The test is credible. The changes are minimal-scope and address the reconnaissance gaps directly. The two open items (CSS cursor, Phase 3 ARIA contract) are correctly deferred and flagged.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
            "type": "upstream_task",
            "id": "urn:fnsr:task:180-recon-term-crud-c",
            "field": "outputs.findings"
