        "summary": "Phase 2 task 2.4 Chain A introduces the React Flow canvas component (`CanvasView.tsx`) bound to the canonical project document's `ecm:instances` and `ecm:relations` arrays as a derived read-only view (mutations deferred to Chains B/C/D). The SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.11 schemas are fully specified: `ecm:CanvasNode` has five fields (instanceIri + x/y/width/height); `ecm:CanvasEdge` references its relation by `ecm:relationId` (editor-internal UUID IRI) rather than source/target IRI directly, requiring a join against `ecm:relations` to obtain React Flow `source`/`target` node IDs. The semantic projection (`src/projection/index.ts`) already correctly excludes `ecm:layouts` from entity processing and omits all three canvas types from `SEMANTIC_TYPE_ALLOWLIST`, satisfying AC5's semantic-stripping guarantee at the kernel level \u00e2\u20ac\u201d but no UI semantic-JSON-LD export button exists yet, so the AC5 Playwright 'export \u00e2\u2020\u2019 parse \u00e2\u2020\u2019 assert' test cannot be wired in Chain A; it is explicitly acknowledged as a 'stand-in plan' item in the developer task. No `@xyflow/react` package exists in `package.json`; state.jsonld operator notes specify `@xyflow/react ^12` as the target, classified as devDependency per OPERATOR-MEDIATION-LOG Event 3 convention. The center panel (`gw-canvas`) is a pure placeholder. All current Playwright fixtures have empty `ecm:instances` or at most 1 instance with no relations and no canvas layouts; a new `canvas-3i-2r.jsonld` fixture must be created for AC1. SPEC \u00c2\u00a76.2 does not contain visual-semantics specifications (node shapes per term type, edge styles per relation type) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d that focus-area parenthetical does not correspond to actual \u00c2\u00a76.2 content.",
