            "id": "C5",
            "file": "tests/playwright/fixtures/canvas-3i-2r.jsonld",
            "rationale": "New fixture with 3 ecm:Instance entries, 2 ecm:RelationAssertion entries, and 1 ecm:CanvasLayout with explicit positions for all 3 nodes and 2 edges. Explicit positions ensure deterministic rendering in headless Chromium. Context follows exact key order of existing fixtures (alphabetical). No BOM. LF line endings. Canvas-specific fields (ecm:instanceIri, ecm:x/y/width/height, ecm:nodes, ecm:edges, ecm:relationId, ecm:sourceHandle, ecm:targetHandle) are Editor Layer data and need no special @context entries -- they remain plain JSON values in the in-memory document.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "{\n  \"@context\": {\n    \"cco\": \"https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/\",\n    \"ecm\": \"https://edgecanonical.org/ns/modeler#\",\n    \"ecm:classIris\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:instances\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:isSerializationOf\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:layouts\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:literalAssertions\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:objectIri\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:ontologies\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:predicateIri\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:relations\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:serializations\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:snapshots\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:subjectIri\": {\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"ecm:terms\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\"\n    },\n    \"iao\": \"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/iao#\",\n    \"iao:isAbout\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"id\": \"@id\",\n    \"owl\": \"http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#\",\n    \"rdf\": \"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\",\n    \"rdfs\": \"http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#\",\n    \"rdfs:subClassOf\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"rdfs:subPropertyOf\": {\n      \"@container\": \"@set\",\n      \"@type\": \"@id\"\n    },\n    \"type\": \"@type\",\n    \"xsd\": \"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#\"\n  },\n  \"id\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000\",\n  \"type\": [\n    \"ecm:Project\",\n    \"iao:OntologyDesignPattern\"\n  ],\n  \"ecm:specVersion\": \"0.4\",\n  \"ecm:createdAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"ecm:instances\": [\n    {\n      \"ecm:classIris\": [\n        \"https://example.org/ontology/Thing\"\n      ],\n      \"ecm:createdAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"id\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001\",\n      \"type\": \"ecm:Instance\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"ecm:classIris\": [\n        \"https://example.org/ontology/Thing\"\n      ],\n      \"ecm:createdAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"id\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002\",\n      \"type\": \"ecm:Instance\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"ecm:classIris\": [\n        \"https://example.org/ontology/Thing\"\n      ],\n      \"ecm:createdAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"id\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003\",\n      \"type\": \"ecm:Instance\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ecm:layouts\": [\n    {\n      \"ecm:edges\": [\n        {\n          \"ecm:relationId\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011\",\n          \"ecm:sourceHandle\": \"default-source\",\n          \"ecm:targetHandle\": \"default-target\",\n          \"type\": \"ecm:CanvasEdge\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"ecm:relationId\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012\",\n          \"ecm:sourceHandle\": \"default-source\",\n          \"ecm:targetHandle\": \"default-target\",\n          \"type\": \"ecm:CanvasEdge\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"ecm:name\": \"Default Layout\",\n      \"ecm:nodes\": [\n        {\n          \"ecm:height\": 120,\n          \"ecm:instanceIri\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001\",\n          \"ecm:width\": 220,\n          \"ecm:x\": 100,\n          \"ecm:y\": 100,\n          \"type\": \"ecm:CanvasNode\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"ecm:height\": 120,\n          \"ecm:instanceIri\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002\",\n          \"ecm:width\": 220,\n          \"ecm:x\": 400,\n          \"ecm:y\": 100,\n          \"type\": \"ecm:CanvasNode\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"ecm:height\": 120,\n          \"ecm:instanceIri\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003\",\n          \"ecm:width\": 220,\n          \"ecm:x\": 700,\n          \"ecm:y\": 100,\n          \"type\": \"ecm:CanvasNode\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"id\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000020\",\n      \"type\": \"ecm:CanvasLayout\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ecm:literalAssertions\": [],\n  \"ecm:name\": \"Canvas Fixture (3 instances, 2 relations)\",\n  \"ecm:ontologies\": [],\n  \"ecm:relations\": [\n    {\n      \"ecm:objectIri\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002\",\n      \"ecm:predicateIri\": \"https://example.org/ontology/relatesTo\",\n      \"ecm:subjectIri\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001\",\n      \"id\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011\",\n      \"type\": \"ecm:RelationAssertion\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"ecm:objectIri\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003\",\n      \"ecm:predicateIri\": \"https://example.org/ontology/relatesTo\",\n      \"ecm:subjectIri\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002\",\n      \"id\": \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012\",\n      \"type\": \"ecm:RelationAssertion\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ecm:serializations\": [],\n  \"ecm:snapshots\": [],\n  \"ecm:terms\": [],\n  \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"iao:isAbout\": [\n    \"https://example.org/subjects/CanvasTest\"\n  ]\n}\n",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C6",
            "file": "tests/playwright/canvas.spec.ts",
            "rationale": "AC1 Playwright test: loads canvas-3i-2r.jsonld, waits for React Flow to mount, asserts 3 .react-flow__node elements and 2 .react-flow__edge elements within the gw-canvas-view container. Follows patterns established in term-crud.spec.ts (setInputFiles, toBeEnabled guard, toHaveCount with retry). 10s timeout on the first node assertion accommodates React Flow's ResizeObserver + initial layout cycle in headless Chromium.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "import { test, expect } from \"@playwright/test\";\nimport path from \"path\";\n\n/**\n * Task 2.4 Chain A -- Instance Canvas acceptance tests.\n *\n * AC1: Project with 3 instances and 2 relations renders 3 React Flow nodes\n *      and 2 edges. Playwright test. IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN section 2.4.\n *\n * Chain B: AC2 (create instance via canvas; FR-U011).\n * Chain C: AC3 (move node; layout persistence to ecm:CanvasLayout).\n * Chain D: AC5 (semantic export strips ecm:CanvasLayout; requires export UI).\n */\n\nconst CANVAS_FIXTURE = path.join(\n  process.cwd(),\n  \"tests\",\n  \"playwright\",\n  \"fixtures\",\n  \"canvas-3i-2r.jsonld\",\n);\n\ntest.describe(\"Canvas view (task 2.4 Chain A)\", () => {\n  test(\n    \"AC1: 3-instance / 2-relation fixture renders 3 nodes and 2 edges\",\n    async ({ page }) => {\n      await page.goto(\"/\");\n\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-file-input\").setInputFiles(CANVAS_FIXTURE);\n      await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\")).toBeEnabled();\n\n      // Canvas view wrapper must be visible before asserting React Flow internals.\n      const canvasView = page.getByTestId(\"gw-canvas-view\");\n      await expect(canvasView).toBeVisible();\n\n      // React Flow renders one .react-flow__node div per node.\n      // 10s timeout accommodates ResizeObserver + fitView initialization.\n      await expect(canvasView.locator(\".react-flow__node\")).toHaveCount(3, {\n        timeout: 10_000,\n      });\n\n      // React Flow renders one .react-flow__edge <g> per edge (SVG layer).\n      await expect(canvasView.locator(\".react-flow__edge\")).toHaveCount(2);\n    },\n  );\n});\n",
            "scope": "minimal"
          }
        ],
        "tests_recommended": [
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/canvas.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC1 already implemented in C6. Additional tests for future chains: AC2 (drag-to-create instance writes ecm:Instance + ecm:CanvasNode to project document on save), AC3 (drag node updates ecm:CanvasNode position in saved document), AC5 (semantic export download parses to JSON-LD with no ecm:CanvasLayout type entries -- requires an export button in the UI, deferred to Chain D / Phase 4)."
          },
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/shell.spec.ts",
            "describe": "Existing AC1 (no console errors on load) should still pass: CanvasView renders a <p> placeholder when project === null, so React Flow is not mounted and emits no warnings on the initial page load."
          }
        ],
        "open_questions": [
          "Active-layout selection policy (upstream recon open question 1): when ecm:layouts has multiple ecm:CanvasLayout entries, Chain A uses the first valid one. This needs a policy decision before Chain C introduces layout write-back. Recommend adding a project-settings pointer or a convention (e.g., first entry is canonical) in SPEC section 5.11 errata or DECISIONS.md.",
          "Auto-layout write-back (upstream recon open question 2): Chain A uses a read-only auto-grid when no layout exists; it does NOT write back positions to ecm:layouts. Chain B or C should decide whether creating the first instance also creates an ecm:CanvasLayout entry, or whether layout creation is a separate explicit user action.",
          "AC5 Turtle stand-in plan: the IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN section 2.4 AC5 test (semantic export strips canvas layout nodes) requires a UI export button. No such button exists. Recommended plan for Chain D: add a minimal 'Export Semantic' button to the header (aligns with Phase 4 Turtle/JSON-LD download flows); the Playwright test downloads the semantic JSON-LD blob and asserts no entry has type === 'ecm:CanvasLayout'. The projection layer (src/projection/index.ts) already excludes ecm:layouts from ENTITY_ARRAY_KEYS and omits all three canvas types from SEMANTIC_TYPE_ALLOWLIST -- the kernel guarantee exists; only the UI trigger and test wiring are missing.",
          "TypeScript build validation: the flatMap<InstanceNode> and flatMap<RelationEdge> generic type parameters may require explicit return-type annotation on the callbacks if tsc infers the union ambiguously. If tsc errors, replace flatMap with explicit for-of loops pushing into a typed array (semantically equivalent, no logic change). Recommend running npm run build after applying before merging.",
          "React Flow CSS path: @xyflow/react dist/style.css is correct for v12. If the package ships the CSS at a different subpath in a future patch, the import in App.tsx will need updating. The build (vite) will surface this immediately as a missing module error."
        ],
        "summary": "Six changes implement Phase 2 task 2.4 Chain A. C1 adds @xyflow/react ^12 to devDependencies. C2-C3 edit App.tsx to import the CSS + CanvasView component and replace the center-panel placeholder. C4 creates CanvasView.tsx with typed derivation logic: ecm:instances -> Node<InstanceNodeData> using positions from the first ecm:CanvasLayout (auto-grid fallback); ecm:relations -> Edge<RelationEdgeData> with source/target from ecm:subjectIri/ecm:objectIri. Component is read-only (all interaction props false). C5 creates the canonical-form-compliant canvas-3i-2r.jsonld fixture (3 instances, 2 relations, 1 layout with explicit positions). C6 creates the AC1 Playwright test scoped inside gw-canvas-view, asserting 3 .react-flow__node and 2 .react-flow__edge elements. Chain B/C/D follow-ups and AC5 plan are captured in open_questions.",
        "self_assessment": "uncertain"
      },
      "depends_on": [
