      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:187-rat-canvas",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change introduces a new npm devDependency (@xyflow/react ^12), a new UI component (CanvasView.tsx), a new Playwright test suite (canvas.spec.ts), a new fixture (canvas-3i-2r.jsonld), and edits to App.tsx and package.json \u00e2\u20ac\u201d none of these are typo fixes, formatting corrections, or terminology tightening; they constitute a new canvas surface with a new dependency chain.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance (urn:fnsr:task:185-recon-canvas) is present in UPSTREAM and covers all structural questions the proposed changes depend on. All eight review focus areas from INPUTS are satisfied:\n\n1. RECONCILIATION WITH RECONNAISSANCE: The developer changes reconcile cleanly against the reconnaissance evidence. C4 derives nodes from ecm:instances using ecm:CanvasNode positions from the first valid ecm:CanvasLayout (reconnaissance F2/F4/F18), falls back to an auto-grid when no layout entry exists for an instance (reconnaissance F7), and derives edges from ecm:relations using ecm:subjectIri/ecm:objectIri directly as source/target (reconnaissance F17 join requirement). The edge-derivation path bypasses ecm:CanvasEdge entries \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a deliberate Chain A simplification that reconnaissance F20 (read-only scope, no create/move/edit) permits. ecm:sourceHandle and ecm:targetHandle from ecm:CanvasEdge are not consumed in Chain A; this is consistent with the read-only contract and deferred to Chain C. AC5 semantic-export test is explicitly deferred per F14; the developer's Chain D stand-in plan is consistent with reconnaissance open question 3.\n\n2. AC1 PLAYWRIGHT TEST CREDIBILITY: C6 uses .react-flow__node and .react-flow__edge CSS class selectors scoped to the gw-canvas-view data-testid container, with toHaveCount retry semantics and a 10s timeout accommodating ResizeObserver + fitView initialization in headless Chromium. @xyflow/react v12 uses these class names consistently for node and edge DOM elements. The fixture C5 supplies explicit ecm:CanvasNode positions (ecm:x/ecm:y for all three instances), removing layout-engine non-determinism from the AC1 assertion. The test structure follows the established term-crud.spec.ts pattern (setInputFiles, toBeEnabled guard before node assertions). AC1 is credible as written.\n\n3. @XYFLOW/REACT IN DEVDEPENDENCIES: C1 places @xyflow/react ^12.0.0 in the devDependencies block, inserted alphabetically after @vitejs/plugin-react. This is correct per OPERATOR-MEDIATION-LOG Event 3 (browser-app bundle convention: frontend libraries go in devDependencies since the bundle is the deployed artifact; no separate npm install at consumer side). React and react-dom are already in devDependencies in this project, establishing the pattern. Placement confirmed correct.\n\n4. CANVASVIEW AS DERIVED VIEW: C4 implements CanvasView as a pure derived view with no canonical state ownership: (a) all interaction props set false (nodesDraggable={false}, nodesConnectable={false}, elementsSelectable={false}); (b) no useState for canonical data \u00e2\u20ac\u201d only useMemo for derivation; (c) no setProject callback threaded through; (d) project is a read-only prop (Record<string, unknown> | null). This satisfies SPEC \u00c2\u00a74.2 ('rendered canvas state' and 'React component state' are explicitly not source of truth) and SPEC \u00c2\u00a715.3 ('React Flow state must be derived from / synchronized with the canonical Editor Layer'). The pattern is consistent with App.tsx's established state propagation via prop callbacks (reconnaissance F9) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Chain A deliberately does not pass setProject to CanvasView, enforcing read-only scope at the prop boundary.\n\n5. LAYER BOUNDARIES: CanvasView.tsx lives at src/ui/ (UI layer). Its import list is: useMemo from react (external); ReactFlow, Background, Controls, Node, Edge from @xyflow/react (external). No imports from src/kernel/, src/composition/, or src/adapters/. Layer 0 purity is unaffected. The CSS import for @xyflow/react/dist/style.css in App.tsx is a stylesheet reference, not a module dependency. No layer violations.\n\n6. TYPESCRIPT GAP-13: InstanceNodeData and RelationEdgeData both declare `extends Record<string, unknown>`, satisfying @xyflow/react v12's Node<TData>/Edge<TData> generic constraint that TData must be index-compatible. The typed aliases InstanceNode = Node<InstanceNodeData> and RelationEdge = Edge<RelationEdgeData> are then used consistently throughout C4. The developer flagged flatMap<InstanceNode> generic inference as a potential build-time ambiguity; this is advisory \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the semantic intent is correct; if tsc rejects the generic parameter, replacing flatMap with a typed for-of loop is a non-semantic fix. The operator must run npm run build after applying to confirm.\n\n7. FIXTURE CANONICAL-FORM COMPLIANCE: C5 (canvas-3i-2r.jsonld) contains 3 ecm:Instance entries with all required fields (id, type, ecm:classIris, ecm:createdAt, ecm:updatedAt); 2 ecm:RelationAssertion entries with all required fields (id, type, ecm:subjectIri, ecm:predicateIri, ecm:objectIri); and 1 ecm:CanvasLayout (id, type, ecm:name, ecm:nodes[3], ecm:edges[2]). Each ecm:CanvasNode carries type/ecm:instanceIri/ecm:x/ecm:y/ecm:width/ecm:height per SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.11. Each ecm:CanvasEdge carries type/ecm:relationId/ecm:sourceHandle/ecm:targetHandle per SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.11. The two ecm:relationId values (c3000000-\u00e2\u20ac\u00a6-0011, c3000000-\u00e2\u20ac\u00a6-0012) match the two ecm:relations[].id values exactly \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the join is internally consistent. The @context follows the alphabetical-key ordering of existing fixtures. No BOM declared; LF endings declared. Editor Layer fields (ecm:instanceIri, ecm:x, ecm:y, etc.) are correctly absent from @context since they are not semantically projected. Canonical-form compliant.\n\n8. EDITORIAL VS SUBSTANTIVE: Substantive, as classified. No editorial exemption applies.\n\nNo blocking or major issues. Two advisory forward-track notes for operator awareness: (a) Edge derivation bypass \u00e2\u20ac\u201d reading ecm:relations directly (source=ecm:subjectIri, target=ecm:objectIri) rather than joining through ecm:CanvasEdge means all semantically-defined relations render as edges regardless of whether they appear in the active layout's ecm:edges array; this simplification is correct for Chain A but must be revisited in Chain C when layout write-back is introduced, as per-layout edge visibility and sourceHandle/targetHandle routing will require the join; (b) Build validation \u00e2\u20ac\u201d operator must run `npm run build` and `npm test` after applying C1-C6 before considering Chain A complete; the developer's self_assessment 'uncertain' correctly flags TypeScript flatMap inference and @xyflow/react CSS import path as advisory build-time checks.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
