        "summary": "Chain A's CanvasView.tsx is a read-only component: its props interface carries only `project` (no setter), all three React Flow interactivity flags are locked false, and no write-back path to `ecm:CanvasLayout` exists. Chain B requires adding an `onProjectChange` callback prop (mirroring TermSidebar's `onTermsChange` pattern) and wiring it in App.tsx. For event handling, `@xyflow/react` v12 provides `onPaneClick` (fires on pane background single-click; double-click detectable via `event.detail === 2`) but has no dedicated `onPaneDoubleClick`; `onDoubleClick` (inherited from `HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement>`) fires on any double-click in the container. Converting click coordinates to flow coordinates requires `useReactFlow().screenToFlowPosition`, which requires a `ReactFlowProvider` wrapper not currently present in CanvasView. The minimum-valid ecm:Instance for AC2 consists of: `id` (urn:uuid:... via `crypto.randomUUID()`), `type: 'ecm:Instance'`, `ecm:classIris: []` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `rdfs:label` is optional per both the type guard and the MALFORMED_INSTANCE validator, and the existing fixture confirms label-less instances are valid. No default label string is defined in the codebase or SPEC. The create operation must also produce a paired ecm:CanvasNode entry (per IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.4); the type guard minimum for that is `type`, `ecm:instanceIri`, `ecm:x`, `ecm:y` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d but the fixture and SPEC schema both include `ecm:width: 220` and `ecm:height: 120` as de-facto field companions. A gap exists: there is no helper for creating or upsetting an ecm:CanvasLayout when none exists yet in the project document. IRI generation follows AddTermDialog.tsx's established browser pattern: `crypto.randomUUID()` (Web Crypto API; `src/iri/index.ts` is node:crypto-only and not importable in the browser bundle).",
