        "open_questions": [
          "What default label, if any, should a newly-created instance receive? SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.8 shows 'instance1' as an illustrative value; the fixture uses no label; the MALFORMED_INSTANCE validator does not require it. The operator or architect must decide: empty string, 'New Instance', or some other default.",
          "Should an ecm:CanvasNode created via double-click include `ecm:width` and `ecm:height` (as in fixture and SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.11 example) or only the type-guard-required `ecm:instanceIri`, `ecm:x`, `ecm:y`?",
          "When the project document has no existing ecm:CanvasLayout (e.g., a brand-new project), should creating an instance also create a new ecm:CanvasLayout entry? CanvasView reads `ecm:layouts[0]` but there is no create-layout helper; Chain B must either create the layout inline or assume one always exists.",
          "Double-click detection approach: `event.detail === 2` within `onPaneClick` (pane-specific, fires only on background) vs. `onDoubleClick` HTML div handler (fires anywhere in ReactFlow container including nodes)? The pane-specific variant is more precise for 'create on empty background click'; the native handler is simpler but fires on nodes too.",
          "Coordinate conversion: to obtain flow-space (x, y) for the new ecm:CanvasNode from the double-click event, `useReactFlow().screenToFlowPosition` is required \u00e2\u20ac\u201d but this hook requires a `ReactFlowProvider` wrapper not currently in CanvasView. Should CanvasView add a ReactFlowProvider wrapper, or should a sibling inner component call the hook and pass the handler down?"
        ],
        "scope_assessment": "Investigated CanvasView.tsx (Chain A structure, props, interactivity flags, derivation/position logic), App.tsx (prop wiring), TermSidebar.tsx + AddTermDialog.tsx (mutation callback patterns, IRI/timestamp patterns), src/iri/index.ts (node:crypto constraint), tests/playwright/canvas.spec.ts (AC1 pattern, AC2 stub absence), canvas-3i-2r.jsonld fixture (minimum-field evidence), project/SPEC.md \u00c2\u00a75.8 + \u00c2\u00a75.11 (schema and validator requirements), project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a72.4 (FR-U011 spec), and @xyflow/react v12 type declarations (event API surface); did not investigate kernel/transform.ts, normalize/, migrate/, validate/, or other UI components unrelated to canvas create."
