    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:191-dev-canvas-create",
      "agent": "developer",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "changes": [
          {
            "id": "C1",
            "file": "src/ui/CanvasView.tsx",
            "rationale": "Add useCallback (for memoised handler) and the MouseEvent type alias (for onPaneClick handler typing) from react; add ReactFlowProvider and useReactFlow from @xyflow/react to enable the provider-split pattern required for screenToFlowPosition (recon F7).",
            "before": "import { useMemo } from \"react\";\nimport {\n  ReactFlow,\n  Background,\n  Controls,\n  type Node,\n  type Edge,\n} from \"@xyflow/react\";",
            "after": "import { useMemo, useCallback, type MouseEvent as ReactMouseEvent } from \"react\";\nimport {\n  ReactFlow,\n  ReactFlowProvider,\n  Background,\n  Controls,\n  useReactFlow,\n  type Node,\n  type Edge,\n} from \"@xyflow/react\";",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C2",
            "file": "src/ui/CanvasView.tsx",
            "rationale": "Add optional onProjectChange callback prop to CanvasViewProps, mirroring TermSidebar's onTermsChange pattern (recon F3). Optional keeps Chain A callers compatible; App.tsx will supply it in C4.",
            "before": "interface CanvasViewProps {\n  project: Record<string, unknown> | null;\n}",
            "after": "interface CanvasViewProps {\n  project: Record<string, unknown> | null;\n  /**\n   * Called with the updated project document after an instance is created.\n   * When undefined the double-click create gesture is disabled (read-only mode).\n   */\n  onProjectChange?: (project: Record<string, unknown>) => void;\n}",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C3",
            "file": "src/ui/CanvasView.tsx",
            "rationale": "Split CanvasView into outer (ReactFlowProvider wrapper) + inner (CanvasViewInner, calls useReactFlow). Inner handles onPaneClick: event.detail===2 detects double-click within the pane-click stream (recon F5/F6); screenToFlowPosition converts clientX/Y to flow coords (recon F7). Creates minimum-valid ecm:Instance (SPEC 5.8/isEcmInstance: id, type, ecm:classIris; adds rdfs:label per directions) + ecm:CanvasNode with fixture-canonical dimensions 220x120 (recon F12/F13). Finds or creates first ecm:CanvasLayout (recon F21 gap). IRI via crypto.randomUUID() per AddTermDialog.tsx browser pattern (recon F14).",
            "before": "/**\n * Chain A read-only canvas: derives React Flow nodes from ecm:instances and\n * edges from ecm:relations. No create/move/edit -- those are Chains B/C/D.\n * SPEC section 15.3 / section 4.2 / section 5.11.\n */\nexport function CanvasView({ project }: CanvasViewProps) {\n  const nodes = useMemo<InstanceNode[]>(\n    () => (project !== null ? deriveNodes(project) : []),\n    [project],\n  );\n  const edges = useMemo<RelationEdge[]>(\n    () => (project !== null ? deriveEdges(project) : []),\n    [project],\n  );\n\n  if (project === null) {\n    return (\n      <p className=\"gw-placeholder\" data-testid=\"gw-canvas-view\">\n        Open a project to view the canvas.\n      </p>\n    );\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div\n      style={{ width: \"100%\", height: \"100%\" }}\n      data-testid=\"gw-canvas-view\"\n    >\n      <ReactFlow\n        nodes={nodes}\n        edges={edges}\n        nodesDraggable={false}\n        nodesConnectable={false}\n        elementsSelectable={false}\n        fitView={nodes.length > 0}\n      >\n        <Background />\n        <Controls />\n      </ReactFlow>\n    </div>\n  );\n}",
            "after": "// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Inner canvas: must be a child of ReactFlowProvider to call useReactFlow\n// (screenToFlowPosition for coordinate conversion; SPEC section 5.11).\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ninterface CanvasViewInnerProps {\n  nodes: InstanceNode[];\n  edges: RelationEdge[];\n  project: Record<string, unknown>;\n  onProjectChange?: (updated: Record<string, unknown>) => void;\n}\n\nfunction CanvasViewInner({\n  nodes,\n  edges,\n  project,\n  onProjectChange,\n}: CanvasViewInnerProps) {\n  const { screenToFlowPosition } = useReactFlow();\n\n  /**\n   * onPaneClick fires on every click to the pane background (not on nodes).\n   * event.detail === 2 distinguishes the second click of a double-click from\n   * single clicks. One double-click => one ecm:Instance + ecm:CanvasNode.\n   */\n  const handlePaneClick = useCallback(\n    (event: ReactMouseEvent) => {\n      if (event.detail !== 2) return;\n      if (onProjectChange === undefined) return;\n\n      const pos = screenToFlowPosition({\n        x: event.clientX,\n        y: event.clientY,\n      });\n      const newIri = `urn:uuid:${crypto.randomUUID()}`;\n      const now = new Date().toISOString();\n\n      // Minimum-valid ecm:Instance (SPEC section 5.8 + isEcmInstance guard).\n      const newInstance: Record<string, unknown> = {\n        id: newIri,\n        type: \"ecm:Instance\",\n        \"rdfs:label\": \"New Instance\",\n        \"ecm:classIris\": [],\n        \"ecm:createdAt\": now,\n        \"ecm:updatedAt\": now,\n      };\n\n      // ecm:CanvasNode with default dimensions matching fixture canon (SPEC 5.11).\n      const newCanvasNode: Record<string, unknown> = {\n        type: \"ecm:CanvasNode\",\n        \"ecm:instanceIri\": newIri,\n        \"ecm:x\": pos.x,\n        \"ecm:y\": pos.y,\n        \"ecm:width\": 220,\n        \"ecm:height\": 120,\n      };\n\n      // Append to ecm:instances.\n      const existingInstances = Array.isArray(project[\"ecm:instances\"])\n        ? (project[\"ecm:instances\"] as unknown[])\n        : [];\n\n      // Find or create the first ecm:CanvasLayout; append the new canvas node.\n      const existingLayouts = Array.isArray(project[\"ecm:layouts\"])\n        ? (project[\"ecm:layouts\"] as unknown[])\n        : [];\n      const layoutIdx = existingLayouts.findIndex(\n        (l): l is Record<string, unknown> =>\n          l !== null &&\n          typeof l === \"object\" &&\n          (l as Record<string, unknown>)[\"type\"] === \"ecm:CanvasLayout\",\n      );\n      let updatedLayouts: unknown[];\n      if (layoutIdx >= 0) {\n        const existing = existingLayouts[layoutIdx] as Record<string, unknown>;\n        const existingNodes = Array.isArray(existing[\"ecm:nodes\"])\n          ? (existing[\"ecm:nodes\"] as unknown[])\n          : [];\n        updatedLayouts = [\n          ...existingLayouts.slice(0, layoutIdx),\n          { ...existing, \"ecm:nodes\": [...existingNodes, newCanvasNode] },\n          ...existingLayouts.slice(layoutIdx + 1),\n        ];\n      } else {\n        updatedLayouts = [\n          ...existingLayouts,\n          {\n            id: `urn:uuid:${crypto.randomUUID()}`,\n            type: \"ecm:CanvasLayout\",\n            \"ecm:name\": \"Default Layout\",\n            \"ecm:nodes\": [newCanvasNode],\n            \"ecm:edges\": [],\n          },\n        ];\n      }\n\n      onProjectChange({\n        ...project,\n        \"ecm:instances\": [...existingInstances, newInstance],\n        \"ecm:layouts\": updatedLayouts,\n      });\n    },\n    [onProjectChange, project, screenToFlowPosition],\n  );\n\n  return (\n    <ReactFlow\n      nodes={nodes}\n      edges={edges}\n      nodesDraggable={false}\n      nodesConnectable={false}\n      elementsSelectable={false}\n      fitView={nodes.length > 0}\n      onPaneClick={handlePaneClick}\n    >\n      <Background />\n      <Controls />\n    </ReactFlow>\n  );\n}\n\n/**\n * Chain A/B canvas: derives React Flow nodes from ecm:instances and edges\n * from ecm:relations. Chain B wires onProjectChange for double-click create.\n * SPEC section 15.3 / section 4.2 / section 5.11.\n */\nexport function CanvasView({ project, onProjectChange }: CanvasViewProps) {\n  const nodes = useMemo<InstanceNode[]>(\n    () => (project !== null ? deriveNodes(project) : []),\n    [project],\n  );\n  const edges = useMemo<RelationEdge[]>(\n    () => (project !== null ? deriveEdges(project) : []),\n    [project],\n  );\n\n  if (project === null) {\n    return (\n      <p className=\"gw-placeholder\" data-testid=\"gw-canvas-view\">\n        Open a project to view the canvas.\n      </p>\n    );\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div\n      style={{ width: \"100%\", height: \"100%\" }}\n      data-testid=\"gw-canvas-view\"\n    >\n      <ReactFlowProvider>\n        <CanvasViewInner\n          nodes={nodes}\n          edges={edges}\n          project={project}\n          onProjectChange={onProjectChange}\n        />\n      </ReactFlowProvider>\n    </div>\n  );\n}",
            "scope": "moderate"
          },
          {
            "id": "C4",
            "file": "src/ui/App.tsx",
            "rationale": "Wire setProject into CanvasView via onProjectChange callback, mirroring the TermSidebar onTermsChange pattern (recon F2/F3). The inline arrow function passes the full updated project document to setProject.",
            "before": "          <CanvasView project={project} />",
            "after": "          <CanvasView\n            project={project}\n            onProjectChange={(updated) => { setProject(updated); }}\n          />",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C5",
            "file": "tests/playwright/canvas.spec.ts",
            "rationale": "canvas.spec.ts currently imports only test/expect/path; the AC2 test reads the saved download file via fs.readFileSync following the same pattern as new-open-save.spec.ts AC2.",
            "before": "import { test, expect } from \"@playwright/test\";\nimport path from \"path\";",
            "after": "import { test, expect } from \"@playwright/test\";\nimport path from \"path\";\nimport fs from \"fs\";",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C6",
            "file": "tests/playwright/canvas.spec.ts",
            "rationale": "Add AC2 test: Chain B acceptance test for FR-U011. Uses New project (empty canvas, no nodes to accidentally click), dblclick on .react-flow__pane (pane-specific; no node interference), waits for .react-flow__node count=1, saves, reads download, asserts ecm:instances has exactly one entry with type=ecm:Instance and a urn:uuid IRI. Download pattern follows new-open-save.spec.ts.",
            "before": "      await expect(canvasView.locator(\".react-flow__edge\")).toHaveCount(2);\n    },\n  );\n});",
            "after": "      await expect(canvasView.locator(\".react-flow__edge\")).toHaveCount(2);\n    },\n  );\n});\n\ntest.describe(\"Canvas view (task 2.4 Chain B)\", () => {\n  test(\n    \"AC2: double-click on canvas pane creates a new ecm:Instance with valid IRI\",\n    async ({ page }) => {\n      await page.goto(\"/\");\n\n      // Create a new empty project (no existing nodes to interfere).\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-new\").click();\n      await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\")).toBeEnabled();\n\n      const canvasView = page.getByTestId(\"gw-canvas-view\");\n      await expect(canvasView).toBeVisible();\n\n      // Wait for React Flow to initialise the pane.\n      const pane = canvasView.locator(\".react-flow__pane\");\n      await expect(pane).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });\n\n      // Double-click the pane background; Playwright emits click(detail=1)\n      // then click(detail=2). The handler fires on detail===2 only.\n      await pane.dblclick();\n\n      // Wait for the new node to render before saving.\n      await expect(canvasView.locator(\".react-flow__node\")).toHaveCount(1, {\n        timeout: 5_000,\n      });\n\n      // Save and capture the download.\n      const [download] = await Promise.all([\n        page.waitForEvent(\"download\"),\n        page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\").click(),\n      ]);\n\n      const downloadPath = await download.path();\n      expect(downloadPath, \"download must be saved to disk\").not.toBeNull();\n\n      const content = fs.readFileSync(downloadPath!, \"utf-8\");\n      const saved = JSON.parse(content) as Record<string, unknown>;\n\n      // Assert: ecm:instances must contain exactly one new ecm:Instance.\n      const instances = saved[\"ecm:instances\"] as unknown[];\n      expect(Array.isArray(instances)).toBe(true);\n      expect(instances).toHaveLength(1);\n\n      const inst = instances[0] as Record<string, unknown>;\n      expect(inst[\"type\"]).toBe(\"ecm:Instance\");\n      expect(typeof inst[\"id\"]).toBe(\"string\");\n\n      // IRI must match the canonical urn:uuid pattern.\n      expect(inst[\"id\"] as string).toMatch(\n        /^urn:uuid:[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-9a-f]{12}$/,\n      );\n    },\n  );\n});",
            "scope": "minimal"
          }
        ],
        "tests_recommended": [
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/canvas.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC2 test added in C6. Additional coverage to consider: (a) double-click on existing node should NOT create a second instance (verify onPaneClick does not fire when the click target is a node); (b) multiple sequential double-clicks should each produce exactly one new instance (test idempotency of the IRI generation); (c) double-click with no onProjectChange (read-only mode) should not throw or mutate state."
          },
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/canvas.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC2 variant: load canvas-3i-2r.jsonld (fixture with existing ecm:CanvasLayout), double-click on empty pane area, assert ecm:instances length goes from 3 to 4 and the existing layout's ecm:nodes length goes from 3 to 4 (verifies the layoutIdx>=0 branch in handlePaneClick)."
          }
        ],
        "open_questions": [
          "fitView behaviour after first create: when an empty project gains its first node via double-click, fitView={nodes.length > 0} flips from false to true on that render, causing React Flow to centre the canvas on the single new node rather than leaving the viewport at the click position. If Chain C (move node / layout persistence) requires predictable initial node placement, Chain C may need to manage fitView more explicitly (e.g. fitView={false} after the first create, or a fitViewOptions.duration:0 approach). No change made here; surfacing for Chain C planning.",
          "onPaneClick + detail===2 fires the handler TWICE per double-click (detail=1 ignored, detail=2 creates). If React Flow ever batches or suppresses the detail=1 call internally, detail=2 would remain the only call and behaviour would be identical. This is an implementation assumption; confirmed via xyflow v12 type inspection but not a documented guarantee. If a future xyflow upgrade changes pane-click event semantics, this handler may need revisiting.",
          "New ecm:CanvasLayout (created when project has no existing layout) receives a generated urn:uuid IRI, type=ecm:CanvasLayout, ecm:name=Default Layout, ecm:nodes=[newCanvasNode], ecm:edges=[]. SPEC section 5.11 fields not validated here (no ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder, no ecm:createdAt on the layout). If Chain C requires full SPEC 5.11 compliance on newly-created layouts, the layout creation path should be reviewed against SPEC 5.11 mandatory fields."
        ],
        "summary": "Six changes across three files implement FR-U011 (double-click canvas create) + the AC2 Playwright test. CanvasView.tsx is split into an outer shell (ReactFlowProvider wrapper) and CanvasViewInner (useReactFlow consumer) to enable screenToFlowPosition. The onPaneClick handler uses event.detail===2 to detect double-clicks on the pane background. Each double-click creates one ecm:Instance (id, type, rdfs:label, ecm:classIris:[], timestamps) and one ecm:CanvasNode (instanceIri, x, y, width:220, height:120) appended to the first ecm:CanvasLayout (created if absent). App.tsx is updated to pass onProjectChange. The AC2 Playwright test uses a fresh New project, dblclick on .react-flow__pane, waits for node render, saves, and asserts the instance IRI pattern.",
        "self_assessment": "confident"
      },
      "depends_on": [
        "urn:fnsr:task:190-recon-canvas-create"
