    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:192-rat-canvas-create",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change implements a new interactive feature (FR-U011 double-click canvas create) by introducing a provider-split component architecture, new callback prop, new event-handling logic, layout find-or-create logic, and a new Playwright acceptance test \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all of which alter behavioral spec content and add new runtime paths well outside the editorial-correction scope of typo/formatting/terminology fixes.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance from urn:fnsr:task:190-recon-canvas-create is present in UPSTREAM. All five open questions surfaced by reconnaissance are addressed by the proposal:\n\n(1) rdfs:label default (recon Q1/F11): Developer chose 'New Instance'. No spec constraint violated; SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.8 treats the label as optional; the MALFORMED_INSTANCE validator does not require it; the AC2 test asserts only IRI shape, not label value. The choice is product-sensible and does not constitute a spec violation.\n\n(2) ecm:width / ecm:height (recon Q2/F12/F13): C3 includes ecm:width: 220 and ecm:height: 120, matching both the canvas-3i-2r fixture and the SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.11 example. Correct.\n\n(3) CanvasLayout creation gap (recon Q3/F21): C3 implements an inline find-or-create pattern \u00e2\u20ac\u201d locates the first ecm:CanvasLayout in ecm:layouts or creates one with a generated IRI, type: ecm:CanvasLayout, ecm:name: 'Default Layout', ecm:nodes: [newCanvasNode], ecm:edges: []. The new layout omits ecm:createdAt/ecm:updatedAt, which is consistent with SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.11 not showing those fields on layouts. The gap is resolved.\n\n(4) Double-click detection (recon Q4/F5/F6): C3 uses onPaneClick (fires on pane background only, not on nodes) plus event.detail === 2 to filter for the second click of a double-click. This is the more precise of the two options surfaced by recon. The pane-background-only scope means existing nodes will not accidentally trigger a create.\n\n(5) ReactFlowProvider requirement (recon Q5/F7): Resolved by the outer/inner component split in C3. CanvasView becomes a ReactFlowProvider wrapper; CanvasViewInner is always rendered as a child of that provider and safely calls useReactFlow(). The hook-scope requirement is satisfied.\n\nIRI GENERATION (review focus): The proposal uses `crypto.randomUUID()` inline, matching the pattern established in AddTermDialog.tsx (recon F14). src/iri/index.ts uses node:crypto and is explicitly non-importable in a browser bundle; AddTermDialog.tsx documents this directly in its module comment. Inline `crypto.randomUUID()` IS the canonical UI-layer IRI generation pattern in this codebase \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the proposal reuses it, it does not reinvent it. No new reimplementation.\n\nATOMIC CREATE: Both ecm:instances and ecm:layouts are updated in a single onProjectChange({...project, ...}) call. From React's perspective this is a single state transition \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the Canvas is re-rendered once with both the new instance and its CanvasNode.\n\nCALLBACK PROP PATTERN: `onProjectChange?: (project: Record<string, unknown>) => void` mirrors TermSidebar.onTermsChange exactly (recon F3). The optional qualifier preserves backwards compatibility for Chain A read-only callers. C4 wires setProject via the same inline arrow pattern used for TermSidebar in App.tsx.\n\nAC2 TEST CREDIBILITY: C6 uses a fresh New project (gw-btn-new) to ensure no pre-existing nodes; targets .react-flow__pane via pane.dblclick() (pane-specific selector, node-safe); waits 5s for .react-flow__node count = 1 before saving; captures download via Promise.all(waitForEvent + click); reads via fs.readFileSync; asserts instances array length = 1, type = ecm:Instance, and IRI match against /^urn:uuid:[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-...$/ (correct for crypto.randomUUID() lowercase hex output). The pattern is identical to new-open-save.spec.ts AC2 download-parse idiom \u00e2\u20ac\u201d credible and consistent.\n\nLAYER BOUNDARIES: All changes are in src/ui/ (CanvasView.tsx, App.tsx) and tests/playwright/ (canvas.spec.ts). No imports from src/adapters/ or src/composition/ into src/kernel/. Layer contract is respected.\n\nNO BLOCKING ISSUES IDENTIFIED. Three advisory items are surfaced in bankings but none rise to denial or deferral level.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
