        ],
        "summary": "Chain C (move-node persistence) builds on a CanvasView.tsx (src/ui/CanvasView.tsx) where drag is currently blocked by nodesDraggable={false} at line 294 and no onNodeDragStop/onNodesChange handler exists. The @xyflow/react v12 API provides onNodeDragStop as the dedicated single-callback for 'drag released' with signature (event, node, nodes) where node.position gives the final {x,y}; onNodesChange with NodePositionChange+dragging===false is an alternative but fires on every mid-drag step as well. The ecm:CanvasNode in \u00c2\u00a75.11 and the canonical fixture (canvas-3i-2r.jsonld) define no updatedAt field; only ecm:x and ecm:y need updating on move. Individual ecm:CanvasNode entries have no id field and must be matched by ecm:instanceIri, which equals the React Flow node.id (set to inst.id at CanvasView.tsx:142). Chain B's mutation pattern (spread-replace the layout object with a new ecm:nodes array) is the established precedent for ecm:CanvasLayout updates. No drag-interaction test pattern (dragTo or page.mouse) exists in the Playwright suite; the Chain C test must be written from scratch. The EcmCanvasNode TypeScript interface is narrower than the fixture/write path (missing ecm:width/ecm:height), which is an incidental observation but not a blocker for x/y-only updates.",
