        "open_questions": [
          "Should the move handler also bump the project root's ecm:updatedAt (\u00c2\u00a79.2 wall-clock) when a canvas node is repositioned? The SPEC only mandates ecm:updatedAt at the project root for 'last-write-wins' conflict detection (\u00c2\u00a79.2, line 925), but moving a node is an editor-layer-only change (\u00c2\u00a75.11: 'Canvas layout is Editor Layer metadata'). This is unspecified.",
          "For the Chain C Playwright test: should it use locator.dragTo() or page.mouse.down/move/up? React Flow v12 drag relies on native mouse events; locator.dragTo() dispatches them but does not guarantee the same sequence as a real drag on a controlled flow component. No precedent exists in the test suite.",
          "Should the onNodeDragStop handler update only ecm:x and ecm:y on the matching ecm:CanvasNode entry (preserving ecm:width and ecm:height), or replace the whole ecm:nodes array atomically? Both are consistent with Chain B's spread-replace pattern, but the in-place map is more surgical.",
          "The EcmCanvasNode TypeScript interface is missing ecm:width and ecm:height fields (present in the fixture and written by handlePaneClick). Should Chain C expand the interface to include these fields, or treat them as pass-through unknown fields in the spread?"
        ],
