    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:196-dev-canvas-layout",
      "agent": "developer",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "changes": [
          {
            "id": "C1",
            "file": "src/ui/CanvasView.tsx",
            "rationale": "Recon F15: EcmCanvasNode interface declares only ecm:instanceIri / ecm:x / ecm:y but the fixture and handlePaneClick write path both carry ecm:width and ecm:height. Adding them as optional fields closes the gap without breaking the existing isEcmCanvasNode guard (which does not check those fields) and without requiring a guard update. The handler in C2 spreads the raw Record<string,unknown> node object so the interface narrowness is not a blocker, but leaving the interface incomplete creates a long-term maintenance hazard.",
            "before": "/** ecm:CanvasNode entry from a layout's ecm:nodes array (SPEC section 5.11). */\ninterface EcmCanvasNode {\n  \"ecm:instanceIri\": string;\n  \"ecm:x\": number;\n  \"ecm:y\": number;\n}",
            "after": "/** ecm:CanvasNode entry from a layout's ecm:nodes array (SPEC section 5.11). */\ninterface EcmCanvasNode {\n  \"ecm:instanceIri\": string;\n  \"ecm:x\": number;\n  \"ecm:y\": number;\n  \"ecm:width\"?: number;\n  \"ecm:height\"?: number;\n}",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C2",
            "file": "src/ui/CanvasView.tsx",
            "rationale": "Implements move-node persistence (AC3). Adds handleNodeDragStop using onNodeDragStop (recon F2: preferred over onNodesChange because it fires exactly once at drag-release, not on every mid-drag step). Handler locates the active ecm:CanvasLayout, guards that the dragged node exists in ecm:nodes (by ecm:instanceIri === node.id per recon F7), then immutably maps over ecm:nodes to spread-update ecm:x and ecm:y from node.position (recon F3) on the matching entry \u00e2\u20ac\u201d preserving all other fields (type, ecm:instanceIri, ecm:width, ecm:height) via spread. This mirrors Chain B's spread-replace layout pattern exactly (recon F8). nodesDraggable is changed from the hardcoded false to onProjectChange !== undefined so drag is enabled only when the write path is wired; in read-only mode (onProjectChange undefined) nodes remain non-draggable. elementsSelectable is left false (no selection UX was planned for Chain C).",
            "before": "    [onProjectChange, project, screenToFlowPosition],\n  );\n\n  return (\n    <ReactFlow\n      nodes={nodes}\n      edges={edges}\n      nodesDraggable={false}\n      nodesConnectable={false}\n      elementsSelectable={false}\n      fitView={nodes.length > 0}\n      onPaneClick={handlePaneClick}\n    >\n      <Background />\n      <Controls />\n    </ReactFlow>\n  );\n}",
            "after": "    [onProjectChange, project, screenToFlowPosition],\n  );\n\n  /**\n   * onNodeDragStop fires once when the user releases a dragged node.\n   * Updates ecm:x / ecm:y on the matching ecm:CanvasNode (matched by\n   * ecm:instanceIri === node.id) inside the active ecm:CanvasLayout.\n   * Uses the same spread-replace pattern as handlePaneClick (Chain B).\n   */\n  const handleNodeDragStop = useCallback(\n    (_event: ReactMouseEvent, node: InstanceNode) => {\n      if (onProjectChange === undefined) return;\n\n      const existingLayouts = Array.isArray(project[\"ecm:layouts\"])\n        ? (project[\"ecm:layouts\"] as unknown[])\n        : [];\n      const layoutIdx = existingLayouts.findIndex(\n        (l): l is Record<string, unknown> =>\n          l !== null &&\n          typeof l === \"object\" &&\n          (l as Record<string, unknown>)[\"type\"] === \"ecm:CanvasLayout\",\n      );\n      if (layoutIdx < 0) return;\n\n      const existing = existingLayouts[layoutIdx] as Record<string, unknown>;\n      const existingNodes = Array.isArray(existing[\"ecm:nodes\"])\n        ? (existing[\"ecm:nodes\"] as unknown[])\n        : [];\n\n      // Guard: only update if the dragged node is actually in the layout.\n      const hasMatch = existingNodes.some(\n        (cn) =>\n          cn !== null &&\n          typeof cn === \"object\" &&\n          (cn as Record<string, unknown>)[\"ecm:instanceIri\"] === node.id,\n      );\n      if (!hasMatch) return;\n\n      const updatedNodes = existingNodes.map((cn) => {\n        if (\n          cn !== null &&\n          typeof cn === \"object\" &&\n          (cn as Record<string, unknown>)[\"ecm:instanceIri\"] === node.id\n        ) {\n          return {\n            ...(cn as Record<string, unknown>),\n            \"ecm:x\": node.position.x,\n            \"ecm:y\": node.position.y,\n          };\n        }\n        return cn;\n      });\n\n      const updatedLayouts = [\n        ...existingLayouts.slice(0, layoutIdx),\n        { ...existing, \"ecm:nodes\": updatedNodes },\n        ...existingLayouts.slice(layoutIdx + 1),\n      ];\n\n      onProjectChange({\n        ...project,\n        \"ecm:layouts\": updatedLayouts,\n      });\n    },\n    [onProjectChange, project],\n  );\n\n  return (\n    <ReactFlow\n      nodes={nodes}\n      edges={edges}\n      nodesDraggable={onProjectChange !== undefined}\n      nodesConnectable={false}\n      elementsSelectable={false}\n      fitView={nodes.length > 0}\n      onPaneClick={handlePaneClick}\n      onNodeDragStop={handleNodeDragStop}\n    >\n      <Background />\n      <Controls />\n    </ReactFlow>\n  );\n}",
            "scope": "moderate"
          },
          {
            "id": "C3",
            "file": "tests/playwright/canvas.spec.ts",
            "rationale": "Adds the Chain C / AC3 Playwright test. Opens canvas-3i-2r.jsonld (which has 3 nodes at known flow positions 100,100 / 400,100 / 700,100), waits for nodes to render, drags the first DOM node 150 screen-px right and 100 screen-px down using page.mouse (mousedown + incremental mousemove with steps:10 + mouseup) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the steps option is critical for React Flow to register the drag gesture. Saves, downloads, parses the JSON, finds the ecm:CanvasLayout, and asserts that at least one ecm:CanvasNode now has a position that differs from every original fixture position by more than 1 unit (robust to viewport-scale variance from fitView). Asserts updated ecm:x and ecm:y are valid numbers. page.mouse is preferred over locator.dragTo() per recon open question 2: it gives explicit control over the mousedown/mousemove/mouseup sequence that React Flow's drag handler requires.",
            "before": "      // IRI must match the canonical urn:uuid pattern.\n      expect(inst[\"id\"] as string).toMatch(\n        /^urn:uuid:[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-9a-f]{12}$/,\n      );\n    },\n  );\n});",
            "after": "      // IRI must match the canonical urn:uuid pattern.\n      expect(inst[\"id\"] as string).toMatch(\n        /^urn:uuid:[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-9a-f]{12}$/,\n      );\n    },\n  );\n});\n\ntest.describe(\"Canvas view (task 2.4 Chain C)\", () => {\n  test(\n    \"AC3: dragging a node and saving persists updated ecm:x / ecm:y in ecm:CanvasLayout\",\n    async ({ page }) => {\n      await page.goto(\"/\");\n\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-file-input\").setInputFiles(CANVAS_FIXTURE);\n      await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\")).toBeEnabled();\n\n      const canvasView = page.getByTestId(\"gw-canvas-view\");\n      await expect(canvasView).toBeVisible();\n\n      // Wait for all 3 fixture nodes to render before attempting drag.\n      const nodeLocators = canvasView.locator(\".react-flow__node\");\n      await expect(nodeLocators).toHaveCount(3, { timeout: 10_000 });\n\n      // Canonical flow-coordinate positions for the three fixture nodes.\n      const originalPositions = [\n        { x: 100, y: 100 },\n        { x: 400, y: 100 },\n        { x: 700, y: 100 },\n      ];\n\n      // Drag the first rendered node 150 screen-px right and 100 screen-px down.\n      // page.mouse is used in place of locator.dragTo() to guarantee the\n      // mousedown + incremental mousemove + mouseup sequence React Flow expects.\n      const firstNode = nodeLocators.first();\n      const box = await firstNode.boundingBox();\n      expect(box, \"first node must have a bounding box\").not.toBeNull();\n\n      const cx = box!.x + box!.width / 2;\n      const cy = box!.y + box!.height / 2;\n      await page.mouse.move(cx, cy);\n      await page.mouse.down();\n      await page.mouse.move(cx + 150, cy + 100, { steps: 10 });\n      await page.mouse.up();\n\n      // Save and capture the download.\n      const [download] = await Promise.all([\n        page.waitForEvent(\"download\"),\n        page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\").click(),\n      ]);\n\n      const downloadPath = await download.path();\n      expect(downloadPath, \"download must be saved to disk\").not.toBeNull();\n\n      const content = fs.readFileSync(downloadPath!, \"utf-8\");\n      const saved = JSON.parse(content) as Record<string, unknown>;\n\n      // Locate the active ecm:CanvasLayout.\n      const layouts = saved[\"ecm:layouts\"] as unknown[];\n      expect(Array.isArray(layouts)).toBe(true);\n\n      const layout = (layouts as Record<string, unknown>[]).find(\n        (l) => l[\"type\"] === \"ecm:CanvasLayout\",\n      );\n      expect(layout, \"saved file must contain an ecm:CanvasLayout\").toBeDefined();\n\n      const canvasNodes = layout![\"ecm:nodes\"] as Record<string, unknown>[];\n      expect(Array.isArray(canvasNodes)).toBe(true);\n      expect(canvasNodes).toHaveLength(3);\n\n      // At least one node must have a position differing from every original\n      // fixture position: the dragged node's new coordinates were persisted.\n      const movedNode = canvasNodes.find((cn) => {\n        const x = cn[\"ecm:x\"] as number;\n        const y = cn[\"ecm:y\"] as number;\n        return originalPositions.every(\n          (orig) => Math.abs(x - orig.x) > 1 || Math.abs(y - orig.y) > 1,\n        );\n      });\n      expect(\n        movedNode,\n        \"at least one ecm:CanvasNode must have an updated position after drag\",\n      ).toBeDefined();\n\n      // Updated coordinates must be valid numbers.\n      expect(typeof movedNode![\"ecm:x\"]).toBe(\"number\");\n      expect(typeof movedNode![\"ecm:y\"]).toBe(\"number\");\n    },\n  );\n});",
            "scope": "moderate"
          }
        ],
        "tests_recommended": [
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/canvas.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC3 Chain C test added as C3 above; no additional tests recommended beyond what is proposed. Once the Playwright suite runs, confirm the drag test passes in headed mode (npx playwright test --headed) to visually verify React Flow registers the mouse gesture correctly before promoting to CI."
          }
        ],
        "open_questions": [
          "elementsSelectable={false} + nodesDraggable={true}: React Flow v12 treats these as independent props, but this combination was not verified in the installed build. If the AC3 test fails with nodes not dragging, try setting elementsSelectable={onProjectChange !== undefined} as well (enabling selection for the drag gesture); the recon did not investigate whether React Flow v12 internally gates drag behind selectability.",
          "ecm:updatedAt on project root: recon open question 1. The SPEC \u00c2\u00a79.2 mandates ecm:updatedAt on the project root for last-write-wins conflict detection. Moving a canvas node is editor-layer-only metadata (SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.11), but it is a user-initiated mutation. Chain C does NOT bump ecm:updatedAt in this proposal (it is not in the SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.11 schema for ecm:CanvasNode and the fixture has no such field). Operator should confirm whether project-root ecm:updatedAt should be bumped on canvas-node moves.",
          "page.mouse drag step count: steps:10 is used in the AC3 test to ensure React Flow receives enough intermediate mousemove events to register the drag gesture. If the test is flaky in CI (drag not detected), increase to steps:20 or add an explicit waitForTimeout(50) after page.mouse.up() before clicking save. This is a known React Flow drag-test fragility in headless environments.",
          "EcmCanvasNode interface fields added as optional (ecm:width?: number, ecm:height?: number). If downstream code ever narrows via the EcmCanvasNode type and expects width/height to be present, the optional typing will cause undefined-checks. The guard (isEcmCanvasNode) does not check these fields, so nodes without them still pass. Making them required would require updating the guard to also check typeof obj['ecm:width'] === 'number'. Left optional for now as the minimal safe change."
        ],
        "summary": "Three changes across two files. C1 (minimal): expands the EcmCanvasNode TypeScript interface to include the ecm:width and ecm:height optional fields that the fixture and write path already carry (recon F15 gap). C2 (moderate): adds handleNodeDragStop to CanvasViewInner using onNodeDragStop (React Flow v12 single-fire drag-release callback per recon F2/F3); handler locates the active ecm:CanvasLayout, maps over ecm:nodes to spread-update ecm:x/ecm:y on the matching entry (matched by ecm:instanceIri === node.id per recon F7), calls onProjectChange with an immutably rebuilt layout following Chain B's spread-replace pattern exactly (recon F8); also changes nodesDraggable from hardcoded false to onProjectChange !== undefined so drag is disabled in read-only mode. C3 (moderate): adds the AC3 Playwright test using page.mouse.down/move/up with steps:10, loads canvas-3i-2r.jsonld, drags first node 150x100 screen-px, saves, asserts at least one ecm:CanvasNode position differs from all three original fixture positions by more than 1 unit.",
        "self_assessment": "uncertain"
      },
      "depends_on": [
        "urn:fnsr:task:195-recon-canvas-layout"
      ],
      "inputs": {
        "task_context": "Phase 2 task 2.4 Chain C: Move-node layout persistence",
        "output_envelope_constraint": "Output wrapped: outputs.changes[] (mode=create or edit), outputs.summary, outputs.self_assessment.",
        "goal": "Propose changes[] implementing move-node persistence + AC3.",
        "implementation_directions": [
          "CanvasView.tsx edit: add onNodeDragStop handler (or equivalent per recon findings). Handler updates the ecm:CanvasNode entry matching the dragged node's id with the new x/y position; calls setProject with the updated document.",
