    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:197-rat-canvas-layout",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal adds new behavioral logic (handleNodeDragStop, conditional nodesDraggable), mutates the ReactFlow component's prop surface, and introduces a new Playwright test \u00e2\u20ac\u201d none of this is typo/formatting/terminology-tightening; it is new capability.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance (task 195) is present in UPSTREAM and is sufficient. All three changes are evaluated below.\n\n**C1 (EcmCanvasNode interface expansion):** Recon F15 identified the interface as narrower than the write path (ecm:width/ecm:height present in the fixture and in handlePaneClick but absent from the TypeScript declaration). Adding them as optional fields is the minimal correct fix; it does not break the isEcmCanvasNode guard (which does not check those fields per recon F14), and the handler in C2 spreads the raw Record<string,unknown> so the interface narrowness was not blocking C2. The change is structurally sound and closes a maintenance hazard correctly identified by recon.\n\n**C2 (handleNodeDragStop + nodesDraggable gate):** The handler follows the Chain B spread-replace pattern exactly (recon F8): it locates the active ecm:CanvasLayout by findIndex, guards for layout presence and for the dragged node's membership in ecm:nodes (matched by ecm:instanceIri === node.id per recon F7), then maps over ecm:nodes to produce a new array where only the matching entry has its ecm:x/ecm:y updated via spread ({...cn, ecm:x, ecm:y}) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all other fields (type, ecm:instanceIri, ecm:width, ecm:height) are preserved. No in-place mutation occurs; the layout object itself is rebuilt via { ...existing, ecm:nodes: updatedNodes }. This is immutable by construction. The choice of onNodeDragStop over onNodesChange is well-grounded (recon F2/F4: onNodeDragStop fires exactly once on drag-release; onNodesChange fires on every mid-drag step requiring dragging===false filtering). The nodesDraggable gating on `onProjectChange !== undefined` correctly disables drag in read-only mode (onProjectChange undefined). The _event prefix convention on the unused event parameter is correct. No ecm:updatedAt is added to ecm:CanvasNode, consistent with recon F5/F13 (SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.11 schema defines no such field; the fixture carries none). Layer boundaries are respected: all changes are in src/ui/CanvasView.tsx (UI layer); no kernel imports or mutations.\n\n**C3 (AC3 Playwright test):** The test uses page.mouse.down/move(steps:10)/up rather than locator.dragTo(), which is the correct approach per recon open question 2 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d it gives explicit control over the mousedown/mousemove/mouseup sequence that React Flow's drag handler requires. The fixture has 3 nodes at known flow positions (100,100), (400,100), (700,100). The test drags the first DOM node 150 screen-px right and 100 screen-px down. Given Playwright Desktop Chrome's default 1280\u00c3\u2014720 viewport and fitView scaling to fit the node spread (~820 px of content), the scale factor \u00e2\u2030\u02c6 1.4, meaning 150 screen-px translates to ~107 flow units \u00e2\u20ac\u201d well above the >1-unit threshold. The position assertion strategy (at least one node differs from every original fixture position by >1 unit in x OR y) is robust to viewport-scale variance from fitView and does not over-specify exact coordinates. The download/parse/layout-find chain mirrors the Chain B test pattern exactly. The before-snippet for C3 matches the terminal lines of canvas.spec.ts (lines 97-102) and the after correctly appends the new describe block after the existing Chain B close.\n\n**Open questions acknowledged but not blocking:** (1) elementsSelectable={false} + nodesDraggable={true} combination in React Flow v12 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d developer documented mitigation (try setting elementsSelectable={onProjectChange !== undefined} if drag fails); (2) project-root ecm:updatedAt on canvas-node moves \u00e2\u20ac\u201d correctly deferred to operator since SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.11 scopes canvas layout as editor-layer-only metadata and \u00c2\u00a79.2 updatedAt mandate is unspecified for this case; (3) step count fragility in headless drag \u00e2\u20ac\u201d developer documented increase path. These are all correctly identified, documented, and non-blocking for ratification.\n\n**Before-snippet match verification:** C1 before matches lines 30-35 of src/ui/CanvasView.tsx exactly. C2 before matches lines 287-304 (closing useCallback dependency array through closing brace of CanvasViewInner) exactly. C3 before matches lines 97-102 (closing of Chain B test) exactly. The applier's before-snippet matching will succeed on unmodified disk content.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
            "type": "upstream_task",
            "id": "urn:fnsr:task:195-recon-canvas-layout",
