        "summary": "The Turtle emitter (`src/emit/turtle.ts`) exposes a single entry point `emitTurtle(project: Record<string, unknown>): string` that accepts a raw project document directly \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no pre-projection step by the caller. Internally it calls `projectSemantic(project)` as step 1, extracts the `@graph` array, converts it to N3 `Quad` objects via `graphToQuads()`, serializes via N3.js Writer, and prepends the bundled TBox Turtle block. The function is declared a pure function with no I/O or non-deterministic API calls, and its imports contain no adapter or composition layer references. The semantic projection (`src/projection/index.ts`) excludes `ecm:CanvasLayout`, `ecm:CanvasNode`, and `ecm:CanvasEdge` by omission from both the `SEMANTIC_TYPE_ALLOWLIST` and the `ENTITY_ARRAY_KEYS` walk \u00e2\u20ac\u201d `ecm:layouts` is explicitly noted as 'Editor Layer -- skipped'. This means AC5 (Turtle output contains no canvas triples) is already satisfied at the kernel level; the unit-level proof lives in `tests/semantic-projection.test.ts` AC1 and AC3. For the AC4 JSON-scan concern: `CanvasView.tsx`'s two write-back paths (`handlePaneClick`, `handleNodeDragStop`) emit only VMP-domain keys (`ecm:Instance`, `ecm:CanvasNode`, `ecm:x`, `ecm:y`, etc.) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no `__rf_` or `__reactflow` keys are written to the project document at any code path. The existing Save button pattern (`App.tsx:122\u00e2\u20ac\u201c131`) uses `new Blob([text], {type: ...})` \u00e2\u2020\u2019 `URL.createObjectURL` \u00e2\u2020\u2019 `anchor.download` \u00e2\u2020\u2019 `anchor.click()` \u00e2\u2020\u2019 `URL.revokeObjectURL`. There is currently no 'Save as Turtle' / FR-U023 button in the UI; the Chain D Playwright test block is entirely absent from `canvas.spec.ts`; adding it requires both a new UI button and a new `test.describe` block. FR-U014 in SPEC.md refers to drawing relations between instances, not to Turtle export; the export requirement is FR-U023 / FR-E002.",
