        "open_questions": [
          "AC4 double-click lands on the .react-flow__pane element center. On the canvas-3i-2r fixture the three nodes sit at flow-coordinates (100,100), (400,100), (700,100). If the viewport maps any of those positions to the pane's center, the dblclick may hit a node instead of the background and not fire handlePaneClick (which guards on detail===2). If this flakes in CI, a mitigaton is to call pane.dblclick({ position: { x: 20, y: 20 } }) to target a viewport corner away from the fixture nodes.",
