        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change introduces a new UI export action (FR-U023 Save-as-Turtle button with handler), a new import in a UI component, and two new Playwright test cases with a recursive helper function \u00e2\u20ac\u201d collectively a behavioral addition that extends user-facing functionality, not a formatting, terminology, or citation correction.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance task 200 is present in UPSTREAM and covers all eighteen findings material to Chain D. The proposed changes (C1\u00e2\u20ac\u201cC4) reconcile cleanly with that evidence on every structural axis examined:\n\n1. CORRECT EMITTER INVOCATION. C2 calls emitTurtle(project) with a single raw-project argument, matching the API signature confirmed by recon F1. No pre-projection step is performed by the caller, consistent with recon F2 confirming projectSemantic is called internally. The import path ../emit/turtle.js uses the ESM .js convention already established in App.tsx (line 9, canonical serializeVmp import).\n\n2. PATTERN FIDELITY (FR-U003 mirror). C2's handleSaveTurtle handler is a structurally identical mirror of the existing handleSave handler documented by recon F7 (Blob \u00e2\u2020\u2019 URL.createObjectURL \u00e2\u2020\u2019 anchor.download \u00e2\u2020\u2019 anchor.click \u00e2\u2020\u2019 URL.revokeObjectURL). The only semantically meaningful differences are the MIME type (text/turtle vs application/ld+json) and filename (project.ttl vs project.jsonld) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d both correct for FR-U023 Turtle export. C3 places the new button inside the existing gw-btn-group with the same disabled={project === null} guard, consistent with the Save button's guard confirmed by recon F8.\n\n3. LAYER BOUNDARY COMPLIANCE. The App.tsx import of ../emit/turtle.js is not a prohibited cross-layer import. The CLAUDE.md layer prohibition (src/kernel/ MUST NOT import from src/adapters/ or src/composition/) flows from kernel outward, not from UI to emit. App.tsx already imports from src/kernel/ (line 9); importing from src/emit/ is structurally parallel. Recon F3 independently confirms the Turtle emitter carries no adapter or composition layer imports itself, satisfying the emitter's own boundary constraint. The purity checker (npm run test:purity) enforces src/kernel/ isolation and will not flag a ui\u00e2\u2020\u2019emit import.\n\n4. AC4 COMPREHENSIVENESS. C4 defines collectAllKeys as a recursive tree-walk (array items + object keys at every depth) before asserting against the /__rf_|__reactflow/i pattern. This satisfies the review focus requirement that the assertion 'walks all keys, not just top-level.' A naive Object.keys call on the top-level document would miss canvas-layer items nested inside ecm:layouts[*].ecm:nodes[*] or ecm:relations[*]. The recursive descent eliminates that gap. The AC4 assertion is expected to pass without any additional code changes because recon F10 and F11 confirm CanvasView's two write-back paths (handlePaneClick, handleNodeDragStop) emit only VMP-domain keys to the project document \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no __rf_ or __reactflow keys are written at any code path.\n\n5. AC5 CORRECTNESS AS TURTLE STAND-IN. C4's AC5 triggers gw-btn-save-turtle \u00e2\u2020\u2019 handleSaveTurtle \u00e2\u2020\u2019 emitTurtle(project) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 projectSemantic(project) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 ENTITY_ARRAY_KEYS walk (which omits ecm:layouts, per recon F4) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 SEMANTIC_TYPE_ALLOWLIST filter (which omits ecm:CanvasLayout, ecm:CanvasNode, ecm:CanvasEdge, per recon F4). The Turtle serialization therefore cannot contain canvas vocabulary; the substring assertions on ecm:CanvasLayout, ecm:CanvasNode, ecm:CanvasEdge are sound by construction (recon F6). The canvas-3i-2r fixture (recon F14) is suitable without modification: it contains a fully-populated ecm:CanvasLayout with three CanvasNode and two CanvasEdge entries, and its iao:isAbout value is a real subject IRI (not ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter), so the MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR check will not block export (developer open question 3, confirmed).\n\n6. SPEC REFERENCE ACCURACY. C3 cites FR-U023 as the normative basis, consistent with recon F9 which clarifies FR-U014 is a canvas-interaction requirement (draw relation between instances), not an export requirement. The export requirement is FR-U023 (Generate and download Turtle) and FR-E002 (Turtle export).\n\n7. SCOPE CONTAINMENT. No kernel, emit, or projection files are modified. The change set is exactly the two files (src/ui/App.tsx and tests/playwright/canvas.spec.ts) indicated by the developer's summary. This is the minimum footprint consistent with adding a production FR-U023 button and the two Chain D acceptance tests.\n\n8. OPEN QUESTIONS DISPOSITION. Developer open questions are advisory and do not require pre-ratification resolution. OQ1 (AC4 pane-dblclick position may hit a node): the mitigation path (positional offset to a corner) is identified and actionable if CI flakiness surfaces. OQ2 (no try/catch in handleSaveTurtle): consistent with handleSave's existing behavior; error-surface scope is task 2.8 per developer and recon context. OQ3 (fixture suitability): confirmed by recon F14 and F18.\n\nAll five review focus items are satisfied. Reconnaissance is present and comprehensive. No contract violations, layer boundary violations, or unresolved blocking conflicts were identified.",
