        "summary": "After task 2.3 close, AddTermDialog has both auto-generate (crypto.randomUUID()) and manual IRI override inputs, plus on-submit duplicate detection against ecm:terms \u00e2\u02c6\u00aa ecm:instances; EditTermDialog has a direct IRI text input that triggers the two-phase confirm-refactor flow (showing referenceCount and affectedEntityTypes) when the value changes. Neither dialog implements task 2.5's remaining requirements: (a) inline duplicate-IRI warning on keypress (AC2 gap \u00e2\u20ac\u201d both dialogs clear errors on onChange and only check at submit), (b) IRI preview showing the auto-generated value before submission (FR-U013 gap \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no preview element in AddTermDialog), and (c) 'Regenerate IRI' button in EditTermDialog (AC3 gap \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no such button exists; user must manually type a new IRI to trigger the confirm-refactor flow). The confirm-refactor phase in EditTermDialog (data-testid='gw-dialog-confirm-refactor') is structurally identical in information content to what a Regenerate-IRI confirmation would require. Task 2.5 has no Playwright test file. Task 2.3 AC1 Playwright test already covers the 'new term \u00e2\u2020\u2019 urn:uuid: IRI' verification that task 2.5 AC1 also requires. The collectSemanticEntityIds helper in src/refactor/index.ts is not exported, forcing AddTermDialog to maintain a parallel implementation (collectExistingIris); this is documented in the source file via a code comment. The SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.8 'Create New Term/Instance' alternative path is unimplemented in EditTermDialog.",
