        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change adds new UI behavior (inline duplicate-IRI warning with Save-button enforcement, Regenerate IRI button with confirm-refactor flow reuse) and a new Playwright test file \u00e2\u20ac\u201d these are behavioral additions to production UI components, not formatting or terminology corrections.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:205-recon-iri-affordances). All three task 2.5 acceptance criteria are satisfied:\n\nAC1 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d The IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.5 AC1 requirement ('new term without custom IRI has IRI matching generation policy pattern; unit test + Playwright test') is already covered by task 2.3 Chain A. Recon F13 confirms term-crud.spec.ts lines 41-108 verifies urn:uuid: generation; recon F18 confirms the test passes. The developer's C5 correctly documents this cross-task coverage and does not duplicate the test.\n\nAC2 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d C1 derives isDuplicate as a render-level computed value (trimmedIriOverride.length > 0 && collectExistingIris(project).has(trimmedIriOverride)), which fires on every onChange keystroke. C2 adds gw-iri-duplicate-warning (role='alert', data-testid='gw-iri-duplicate-warning') and disabled={isDuplicate} on the Save button. This is structurally enforced \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the browser prevents submission while the button is disabled \u00e2\u20ac\u201d not merely a visual hint. The fixture term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld is confirmed to contain https://example.org/ontology/Person, making the AC2 Playwright test's duplicate assumption correct. The existing submit-time check in handleSubmit remains as defence-in-depth.\n\nAC3 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d C3 adds handleRegenerateIri() using crypto.randomUUID() (Web Crypto API; lib:DOM \u00e2\u20ac\u201d same browser-compat rationale as AddTermDialog, grounded in recon F12) and calls the already-imported refactorIri() to compute the cascade before entering setPhase('confirm-refactor'). This correctly reuses the existing gw-dialog-confirm-refactor primitive from task 2.3 Chain B (recon F6). C4 adds gw-btn-regenerate-iri outside the IRI label element (correct \u00e2\u20ac\u201d avoids focus delegation). The fixture term-sidebar-cross-refs.jsonld is confirmed to contain Person (ecm:source: project-created, editable) plus one ecm:Instance with ecm:classIris: ['https://example.org/ontology/Person']. src/refactor/index.ts lines 183-202 traverse ecm:classIris entries and increment referenceCount per match; this fixture will yield referenceCount=1>0, satisfying the AC3 Playwright assertion.\n\nLayer boundaries: all changes are in src/ui/ (AddTermDialog.tsx, EditTermDialog.tsx) and tests/playwright/. No src/kernel/, src/composition/, or src/refactor/ stable-module lines are touched. refactorIri() was already imported in EditTermDialog; no new cross-layer imports.\n\nFR-U013 PARTIAL COVERAGE NOTE: The operator's review_focus asks for FR-U013 fully covered including 'preview.' The IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.5 sub-tasks list 'IRI preview: show full IRI before committing' (line 383), but no AC corresponds to it \u00e2\u20ac\u201d AC1/AC2/AC3 are the only enumerated acceptance criteria and none require a preview element. The developer proposal does not implement preview and does not flag this omission in open_questions. The three explicit ACs are satisfied; the preview sub-task is an orphaned FR-U013 sub-requirement with no AC gate. The ratification is granted on AC satisfaction; the operator should track the preview gap as a forward-track item (see bankings).\n\nOpen question residuals from developer proposal: (a) Cancel-after-Regenerate IRI leaves iri state set to the generated UUID rather than originalIri \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this is not an AC requirement; the developer correctly notes it is structurally consistent with manual-type-then-cancel behavior and flags it for operator decision. (b) collectSemanticEntityIds export: acknowledged as a separate refactor concern, correctly deferred. (c) SPEC \u00c2\u00a713.8 'Create New Term/Instance' path: absent from task 2.5 ACs and IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.5 sub-tasks; correctly left out of scope.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
