        "bankings": [
          {
            "id": "B1",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN sub-tasks and acceptance criteria can diverge: \u00c2\u00a72.5 lists 'IRI preview' as a sub-task at line 383 but no AC is written for it, creating an orphaned FR requirement that survives task close undetected. Ratification surfaced this gap via the review_focus checklist. Pattern: when the architect's review_focus explicitly enumerates FR sub-requirements, sub-tasks without corresponding ACs should be flagged as forward-track items rather than silently passing. The operator should decide at ratification time whether to add an AC (blocking), defer to a new task (forward-track), or formally descope the sub-requirement."
          },
          {
            "id": "B2",
            "category": "methodology-refinement-candidate",
            "content": "Developer open_questions that surface UX edge cases (Cancel-after-Regenerate IRI leaves iri state at generated UUID rather than originalIri) are structurally correct to defer when no AC governs them, but the ratification chain is the correct place to make the deferral explicit and traceable. The developer's open_questions field discharged this responsibility adequately; the pattern should be formalized: any edge case without an AC that the developer defers should be accompanied by a recommended forward-track target (task ID or phase) so it does not vanish into the audit trail."
          },
          {
            "id": "B3",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "Cross-task AC satisfaction (AC1 for task 2.5 already covered by task 2.3 term-crud.spec.ts) requires explicit cross-task citation in both the developer proposal and the test file header to remain auditable. C5's file header correctly documents 'AC1: Already covered by term-crud.spec.ts AC1 (task 2.3 Chain A)' and cites the task URN. This pattern \u00e2\u20ac\u201d where a prior task's artifact satisfies a later task's AC \u00e2\u20ac\u201d should be consistently documented at the test-file level and confirmed via referenced_evidence in ratification, not left implicit."
          }
        ]
      },
