        "summary": "The GraphWrite codebase is in a state where canvas rendering of relations is complete (task 2.4 Chain A: deriveEdges() maps ecm:relations to React Flow edges) but all four FR-U014\u00e2\u20ac\u201cFR-U017 relation-CRUD behaviors are unimplemented. The two blocking flags in CanvasView.tsx\u00e2\u20ac\u201dnodesConnectable={false} (line 361) and elementsSelectable={false} (line 362)\u00e2\u20ac\u201ddisable both the draw gesture and edge selection. No onConnect, onEdgeClick, or onSelectionChange handlers exist. The right-sidebar Inspector is a bare placeholder paragraph (App.tsx:226) with no component file; the CSS layout slot (.gw-inspector, 280px wide) is already defined. The @xyflow/react v12 onConnect API delivers Connection={source, target, sourceHandle, targetHandle}, from which a new ecm:RelationAssertion can be constructed using the same inline crypto.randomUUID() pattern used for instances. The ecm:RelationAssertion schema requires ecm:predicateIri with no spec-defined default or placeholder; a newly drawn relation without a predicate triggers MALFORMED_RELATION (\u00c2\u00a717.2). No combined fixture exists with both instances and owl:ObjectProperty terms, making a new fixture necessary for AC2\u00e2\u20ac\u201cAC4 tests. The work naturally splits into two clusters: Chain A (FR-U014 draw, CanvasView-only) and Chain B (FR-U015/U016/U017, Inspector component + edge selection).",
