        "open_questions": [
          "What predicate value (if any) should a newly drawn relation carry at creation time before the user selects a predicate? The SPEC defines no ecm:UnassignedPredicate placeholder; MALFORMED_RELATION fires immediately if ecm:predicateIri is absent. Options include: (a) block edge creation until predicate is chosen via a modal; (b) use a transient in-memory sentinel that is not persisted until predicate is selected; (c) define a new placeholder IRI (requires SPEC addition). The architect must rule on the approach.",
          "Should FR-U014 draw-only ship as Chain A before FR-U015/U016/U017, or must all four ACs ship in a single chain? The IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN groups them as one task; the recon gap (no combined fixture, no Inspector component) suggests two chains are more practical, but that is a scheduling judgment for the architect/operator.",
          "Do the AC2\u00e2\u20ac\u201cAC4 Playwright tests need a new combined fixture (instances + owl:ObjectProperty terms) or can an existing fixture be extended? The canvas-3i-2r.jsonld fixture is used by multiple existing tests; adding terms to it could affect test expectations.",
          "Is ecm:predicateIri required to reference a term already present in ecm:terms, or is a free-form IRI acceptable for the draw-relation MVP? SPEC \u00c2\u00a717.2 DANGLING_RELATION_PREDICATE_REF treats a missing term reference as a hard error, but task 2.6 AC1 only checks that ecm:subjectIri and ecm:objectIri are correct\u00e2\u20ac\u201dpredicate correctness may be deferred.",
          "The SPEC \u00c2\u00a726 Inspector is described as covering both relation details and node details (literal assertions). Should the task 2.6 Inspector be minimal-viable (relations only), or must it also scaffold the node-detail path for task 2.7 (literal assertions)?"
        ],
