            "rationale": "Wire onEdgeSelect on CanvasView so edge clicks update selectedRelationId in App state.",
            "before": "          <CanvasView\n            project={project}\n            onProjectChange={(updated) => { setProject(updated); }}\n          />",
            "after": "          <CanvasView\n            project={project}\n            onProjectChange={(updated) => { setProject(updated); }}\n            onEdgeSelect={(id) => { setSelectedRelationId(id); }}\n          />",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C12",
            "file": "src/ui/App.tsx",
            "rationale": "Replace inspector placeholder paragraph with the Inspector component, passing selectedRelationId, project, and onProjectChange.",
            "before": "        <aside className=\"gw-inspector\" data-testid=\"gw-inspector\">\n          <p className=\"gw-placeholder\">Inspector -- task 2.5</p>\n        </aside>",
            "after": "        <aside className=\"gw-inspector\" data-testid=\"gw-inspector\">\n          <Inspector\n            selectedRelationId={selectedRelationId}\n            project={project}\n            onProjectChange={(updated) => { setProject(updated); }}\n          />\n        </aside>",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C13",
            "file": "tests/playwright/relation-crud.spec.ts",
            "rationale": "New Playwright test file for task 2.6 Chain A. AC1 only: drag gesture from node handle to target node creates a new ecm:RelationAssertion; save and parse to verify. AC2/AC3/AC4 land in Chain B with the full Inspector and a combined fixture (instances + owl:ObjectProperty terms).",
            "before": null,
            "after": "import { test, expect } from \"@playwright/test\";\nimport path from \"path\";\nimport fs from \"fs\";\n\n/**\n * Task 2.6 Chain A -- Object-Property Relation CRUD acceptance tests.\n *\n * AC1: Drag from one node's source handle to a second node; save; parse:\n *      a new ecm:RelationAssertion appears in ecm:relations with\n *      ecm:subjectIri and ecm:objectIri pointing to distinct fixture instances.\n *\n * Chain B (task 2.6): AC2 (select predicate via dropdown; FR-U015),\n *                     AC3 (reverse; FR-U016), AC4 (delete; FR-U017).\n *\n * Event 8 lesson applied: when positioning within the canvas, use\n * explicitly-empty regions to avoid React Flow element occlusion.\n */\n\nconst CANVAS_FIXTURE = path.join(\n  process.cwd(),\n  \"tests\",\n  \"playwright\",\n  \"fixtures\",\n  \"canvas-3i-2r.jsonld\",\n);\n\n/** Instance IRIs present in the canvas-3i-2r.jsonld fixture. */\nconst FIXTURE_INSTANCE_IRIS = new Set([\n  \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001\",\n  \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002\",\n  \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003\",\n]);\n\n/** Relation ids already in the fixture (used to identify the newly created entry). */\nconst ORIGINAL_REL_IDS = new Set([\n  \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011\",\n  \"urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012\",\n]);\n\ntest.describe(\"Relation CRUD (task 2.6 Chain A)\", () => {\n  test(\n    \"AC1: drag from node source handle to second node; save; parse: new ecm:RelationAssertion with valid subject/object IRIs\",\n    async ({ page }) => {\n      await page.goto(\"/\");\n\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-file-input\").setInputFiles(CANVAS_FIXTURE);\n      await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\")).toBeEnabled();\n\n      const canvasView = page.getByTestId(\"gw-canvas-view\");\n      await expect(canvasView).toBeVisible();\n\n      // Wait for all 3 fixture nodes and 2 fixture edges.\n      const nodeLocators = canvasView.locator(\".react-flow__node\");\n      await expect(nodeLocators).toHaveCount(3, { timeout: 10_000 });\n      await expect(canvasView.locator(\".react-flow__edge\")).toHaveCount(2, {\n        timeout: 5_000,\n      });\n\n      // Hover over the first node to reveal connection handles.\n      // React Flow renders handles only when nodesConnectable is true and the\n      // node is hovered. The source handle carries class `.source` in addition\n      // to `.react-flow__handle`; see open_questions for selector verification.\n      const firstNode = nodeLocators.first();\n      await firstNode.hover();\n\n      const srcHandle = firstNode.locator(\".react-flow__handle.source\").first();\n      await expect(srcHandle).toBeVisible({ timeout: 5_000 });\n      const srcBox = await srcHandle.boundingBox();\n      expect(srcBox, \"source handle must have a bounding box\").not.toBeNull();\n\n      // Target: center of the second node.\n      const secondNode = nodeLocators.nth(1);\n      const tgtBox = await secondNode.boundingBox();\n      expect(tgtBox, \"second node must have a bounding box\").not.toBeNull();\n\n      // Drag from source handle center to target node center.\n      await page.mouse.move(\n        srcBox!.x + srcBox!.width / 2,\n        srcBox!.y + srcBox!.height / 2,\n      );\n      await page.mouse.down();\n      await page.mouse.move(\n        tgtBox!.x + tgtBox!.width / 2,\n        tgtBox!.y + tgtBox!.height / 2,\n        { steps: 15 },\n      );\n      await page.mouse.up();\n\n      // A third edge must appear (2 original + 1 newly drawn).\n      await expect(canvasView.locator(\".react-flow__edge\")).toHaveCount(3, {\n        timeout: 5_000,\n      });\n\n      // Save and capture the download.\n      const [download] = await Promise.all([\n        page.waitForEvent(\"download\"),\n        page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\").click(),\n      ]);\n\n      const downloadPath = await download.path();\n      expect(downloadPath, \"download must be saved to disk\").not.toBeNull();\n\n      const content = fs.readFileSync(downloadPath!, \"utf-8\");\n      const saved = JSON.parse(content) as Record<string, unknown>;\n\n      const relations = saved[\"ecm:relations\"] as unknown[];\n      expect(Array.isArray(relations)).toBe(true);\n      expect(relations).toHaveLength(3);\n\n      // Locate the newly created relation (id not present in the original fixture).\n      const newRel = (relations as Record<string, unknown>[]).find(\n        (r) => !ORIGINAL_REL_IDS.has(r[\"id\"] as string),\n      );\n      expect(newRel, \"a new ecm:RelationAssertion must be present\").toBeDefined();\n      expect(newRel![\"type\"]).toBe(\"ecm:RelationAssertion\");\n\n      // subjectIri and objectIri must both be known fixture instance IRIs.\n      const subjectIri = newRel![\"ecm:subjectIri\"] as string;\n      const objectIri = newRel![\"ecm:objectIri\"] as string;\n      expect(\n        FIXTURE_INSTANCE_IRIS.has(subjectIri),\n        `ecm:subjectIri \"${subjectIri}\" must be a fixture instance IRI`,\n      ).toBe(true);\n      expect(\n        FIXTURE_INSTANCE_IRIS.has(objectIri),\n        `ecm:objectIri \"${objectIri}\" must be a fixture instance IRI`,\n      ).toBe(true);\n\n      // The relation must not be a self-loop.\n      expect(\n        subjectIri,\n        \"ecm:subjectIri and ecm:objectIri must be distinct instances\",\n      ).not.toBe(objectIri);\n    },\n  );\n});\n",
            "scope": "moderate"
          }
        ],
        "tests_recommended": [
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/relation-crud.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC2: load relation-crud-2i-1op.jsonld fixture (2 instances + 1 owl:ObjectProperty + 1 existing relation); click an existing edge to select it; Inspector appears with gw-inspector-relation; select the ObjectProperty from the predicate dropdown; save; parse; assert ecm:predicateIri updated (FR-U015). Chain B."
          },
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/relation-crud.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC3: same fixture; select edge; click Reverse button; save; parse; assert ecm:subjectIri and ecm:objectIri swapped (FR-U016). Chain B."
          },
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/relation-crud.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC4: same fixture; select edge; click Delete button; save; parse; assert relation absent from ecm:relations (FR-U017). Use Event 8 lesson: target deliberately-empty region for any dblclick that might conflict with React Flow edge geometry. Chain B."
          },
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/relation-crud.spec.ts",
            "describe": "Pane-click deselect: after selecting an edge, single-click the pane background; assert gw-inspector-empty appears again (requires handlePaneClick to call onEdgeSelect(null) on event.detail !== 2). Chain B."
          }
        ],
        "open_questions": [
          "Handle CSS selector verification: C5 test (AC1) uses `.react-flow__handle.source` to target the source handle. React Flow v12 default nodes assign class `source` to source handles alongside positional classes. If the selector finds zero elements (e.g., the class is `nodrag nopan source connectable` but filtered differently), the fallback is `firstNode.locator('[data-handletype=\"source\"]')` or bounding-box approximation targeting the right edge of the node. The test must be run once against the dev server to confirm handle discovery before CI gates are added.",
          "ecm:UnassignedPredicate sentinel lifecycle: newly drawn relations carry `ecm:predicateIri: \"ecm:UnassignedPredicate\"`. This satisfies the isEcmRelation type guard but will trigger DANGLING_RELATION_PREDICATE_REF and/or MISSING_PREDICATE validation errors (SPEC \u00c2\u00a717.2). Chain B's predicate assignment (FR-U015) replaces it. Until then, projects with unassigned-predicate relations will show validation errors in task 2.8. Operator should confirm this temporary state is acceptable for the MVP, or direct Chain B to require predicate selection before the relation is committed (modal-gate approach from recon open question OQ-1).",
          "Pane-click deselect (Chain B): handlePaneClick currently does `if (event.detail !== 2) return` without calling `onEdgeSelect?.(null)`. After Chain A lands, clicking the pane background will NOT clear the Inspector selection. Chain B should add `onEdgeSelect?.(null)` on the single-click branch and add `onEdgeSelect` to handlePaneClick's useCallback dependency array.",
          "selectedRelationId staleness on project switch: if the user opens a second project, selectedRelationId from the previous project persists. The Inspector's rel-lookup fails gracefully (falls through to the 'Select a relation to inspect' placeholder), so there is no data corruption, but it is a UX inconsistency. Chain B (or a dedicated cleanup task) should reset selectedRelationId in handleNew and handleFileChange.",
          "Chain B fixture: AC2/AC3/AC4 require a fixture combining 2+ instances on canvas, at least 1 existing ecm:RelationAssertion, and 1+ owl:ObjectProperty in ecm:terms. The canvas-3i-2r.jsonld has no terms and term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld has no instances. A new fixture `tests/playwright/fixtures/relation-crud-2i-1op-1rel.jsonld` must be created in Chain B. It should NOT modify canvas-3i-2r.jsonld since multiple existing tests depend on that fixture's exact ecm:terms: [] shape.",
          "React Flow DOM ordering assumption: AC1 test asserts subjectIri/objectIri are valid FIXTURE_INSTANCE_IRIS without asserting which specific instance is source vs target. This is intentional \u00e2\u20ac\u201d React Flow's node DOM ordering is not formally guaranteed to match the ecm:instances array order. If a future test needs strict source=001/target=002 ordering, it should read the relation's subjectIri, cross-reference to the DOM node via data attribute, and verify visually which node was dragged-from."
        ],
        "summary": "Chain A only. 7 edits to CanvasView.tsx (Connection import, two interface extensions, destructure update, handleConnect + handleEdgeClick addition, ReactFlow prop changes, CanvasView pass-through) + 1 new Inspector.tsx skeleton + 3 edits to App.tsx (import, selectedRelationId state, CanvasView onEdgeSelect wiring, inspector aside replacement) + 1 new relation-crud.spec.ts with AC1. The draw gesture (FR-U014) uses onConnect with a placeholder ecm:UnassignedPredicate IRI to satisfy the isEcmRelation type guard while deferring predicate assignment to Chain B. Edge selection is wired end-to-end (handleEdgeClick -> onEdgeSelect -> App state -> Inspector) so Chain B only needs to expand Inspector internals and add the pane-click deselect. No new fixture needed for AC1 (uses existing canvas-3i-2r.jsonld). Chain B task should deliver: predicate dropdown (FR-U015), Reverse (FR-U016), Delete (FR-U017), pane-click deselect, a new 2i-1op-1rel combined fixture, and AC2/AC3/AC4 tests.",
        "self_assessment": "uncertain"
      },
      "depends_on": [
        "urn:fnsr:task:210-recon-relation-crud"
      ],
      "inputs": {
        "task_context": "Phase 2 task 2.6: Object-Property Relation CRUD",
