        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change implements new functional requirements (FR-U015/U016/U017) by adding UI event handlers, a controlled <select> element, two action buttons, a new test fixture, and three new Playwright acceptance tests \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this is behavioral and structural feature addition, not a typo fix or terminology tightening.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:215-recon-relation-crud-b). All six review-focus criteria have been evaluated against the developer proposal (urn:fnsr:task:216-dev-relation-crud-b) and the source files read directly.\n\n**1. Reconciliation with recon (task 215)**\nAll material recon findings are addressed or acknowledged: F1 (onProjectChange omitted from destructure) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 fixed by C2; F2 (App.tsx passes it unconditionally) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 confirmed, no App.tsx change needed; F5 (Chain B stub comments) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 replaced by C3; F7 (partitionTerms pattern in TermSidebar) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 replicated faithfully by C1's getObjectPropertyOptions; F11 (AC2/AC3/AC4 absent) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 added by C6; F12 (canvas-3i-2r.jsonld has ecm:terms: []) \u00e2\u2020\u2019 addressed by C4 new fixture. F14 (EcmRelation duplication) is acknowledged as intentional chain-isolation; not changed.\n\n**2. FR-U015 \u00e2\u20ac\u201c derived view, not duplicated state**\ngetObjectPropertyOptions(project) reads project['ecm:terms'] from the prop passed by App.tsx. The <select> is a controlled element: value={rel['ecm:predicateIri']} is derived from project['ecm:relations'], not a separate useState. No state duplication. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**3. FR-U016 \u00e2\u20ac\u201c reverse is atomic**\nhandleReverse computes the full updated relations array via .map() and calls onProjectChange exactly once. One setProject call in App.tsx = one React commit = atomic from the state machine's perspective. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**4. FR-U017 \u00e2\u20ac\u201c delete filters by id; selectedRelationId behavior**\nThe filter correctly uses r.id === selectedRelationId. However, handleDelete does NOT call any prop to reset selectedRelationId to null in App.tsx. The review-focus criterion says 'clears selectedRelationId'. The implementation instead relies on the rel === undefined guard to show the empty-state placeholder. This approach is functionally correct: after deletion, project['ecm:relations'] no longer contains the relation, rawRelations.find returns undefined, the guard fires, and gw-inspector-empty is visible. AC4 verifies exactly this path and will pass. The SPEC's FR-U017 says only 'Delete a relation' with no normative statement about selection state management. The dangling selectedRelationId is benign in the current codebase (Inspector is the only consumer); a dedicated onRelationDelete callback would be cleaner state hygiene but is not required by the SPEC or AC4. This is an advisory observation (banked below) not a blocking concern. \u00e2\u0153\u201c (with caveat)\n\n**5. AC2/AC3/AC4 Playwright tests \u00e2\u20ac\u201c credibility**\nAC2: loads canvas-3i-2r-with-ops.jsonld (which has two owl:ObjectProperty terms including the current relation predicate 'relatesTo' and 'HasRole'), clicks first edge via bounding-box center, selects HasRole from gw-select-predicate, saves, verifies predicateIri updated. Credible. AC3: same edge-click strategy, clicks gw-btn-reverse, verifies Inspector immediately reflects the swap (via React re-render driven by onProjectChange \u00e2\u2020\u2019 setProject), then verifies saved file. Credible. AC4: same edge-click, clicks gw-btn-delete-relation, verifies gw-inspector-empty visible (via rel===undefined guard), edge count drops to 1, saved file has 1 relation. Credible. Edge-click risk (bezier centroid miss) is acknowledged by the developer with a fallback strategy; this is an acceptable known risk for a first landing, not a ratification blocker. Bounding-box strategy is the same approach used by AC1 and has an established pattern in this codebase.\n\n**6. Layer boundaries**\nAll changes are in src/ui/Inspector.tsx and tests/playwright/. No imports from src/kernel/, src/adapters/, or src/composition/ are added. No non-deterministic APIs (Date.now, Math.random, fetch, etc.) introduced. The helpers in C1 are pure computations over props. tsconfig.ui.json uses 'jsx': 'react-jsx' (confirmed); the <select> onChange event type is inferred via JSX.IntrinsicElements without requiring an explicit React import \u00e2\u20ac\u201d developer's claim in open_questions is correct. \u00e2\u0153\u201c\n\n**7. Fixture correctness**\nC4 (canvas-3i-2r-with-ops.jsonld) is a new file (before: null). ecm:terms is populated with two owl:ObjectProperty entries sorted ascending by id ('HasRole' < 'relatesTo' in Unicode lexicographic order). The fixture includes 'relatesTo' as both an ecm:terms entry and as the existing predicateIri on both relations, enabling meaningful pre-selection in the dropdown. Shape matches the term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld canonical example from recon F13. \u00e2\u0153\u201c",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
            "type": "upstream_task",
            "id": "urn:fnsr:task:215-recon-relation-crud-b",
            "field": "outputs.findings"
          },
