            "claim": "IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md task 2.7 defines three acceptance criteria: (AC1) Add+Save+parse has correct ecm:subjectIri/ecm:predicateIri/ecm:value/ecm:datatype; (AC2) ecm:language: 'en' is saved correctly; (AC3) Delete+Save+parse: entry absent from ecm:literalAssertions.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md",
                "lines": "412-423",
                "excerpt": "### 2.7 Literal-Property Assertion CRUD (P1)\n\n**SPEC refs:** \u00c2\u00a75.10, FR-U018\u00e2\u20ac\u201cFR-U019\n...\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Add \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Save \u00e2\u2020\u2019 parse: entry in ecm:literalAssertions with correct ecm:subjectIri, ecm:predicateIri, ecm:value, ecm:datatype.\n- Entry with ecm:language: \"en\" saved correctly.\n- Delete \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Save \u00e2\u2020\u2019 parse: entry absent from ecm:literalAssertions."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F14",
            "claim": "SPEC \u00c2\u00a726 describes the Inspector as handling both 'selected node details (including literal assertions)' and 'selected relation details' in the same right panel, but the reference UI is explicitly non-normative; no tab/mode mechanism is specified.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "1620",
                "excerpt": "The reference UI is non-normative guidance."
              },
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "1628",
                "excerpt": "**Right panel \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Inspector / Explanation:** selected node details (including literal assertions), selected relation details, triple preview, RDF-like assertion preview, contextual explanation, validation findings for the selection."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F15",
            "claim": "ecm:language interaction with datatype is already implemented in the core emit layer: turtle.ts applies a language tag when lang is non-null and datatype is xsd:string or rdf:langString.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/emit/turtle.ts",
                "lines": "83-88",
                "excerpt": "function makeLiteralTerm(value: string, datatype: string, lang: string | null) {\n  if (lang !== null && (datatype === \"xsd:string\" || datatype === \"rdf:langString\")) {\n    return literal(value, lang);\n  }\n  return literal(value, namedNode(expandIri(datatype)));\n}"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F16",
            "claim": "The ROADMAP Phase 2 scoping confirms that FR-U018 and FR-U019 (literal-property assertion create, edit, delete) are in-scope for Phase 2 with no Phase 2-specific datatype restriction stated.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/ROADMAP.md",
                "lines": "83-84",
                "excerpt": "- Directed object-property relation create, predicate select, reverse, delete (FR-U014\u00e2\u20ac\u201cFR-U017).\n- Literal-property assertion create, edit, delete with optional language tag (FR-U018\u00e2\u20ac\u201cFR-U019)."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F17",
            "claim": "selectedRelationId and the selection of a relation are mutually managed (single state variable in App.tsx with no mutual-exclusion logic for a hypothetical selectedInstanceId); no 'deselect relation when instance selected' pattern exists yet.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/ui/App.tsx",
                "lines": "52-53",
                "excerpt": "const [selectedRelationId, setSelectedRelationId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const fileInputRef = useRef<HTMLInputElement>(null);"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "inference"
          }
        ],
        "summary": "Post-task-2.6 state: Inspector.tsx is relation-only. Its InspectorProps interface declares only selectedRelationId (string | null), the empty state reads 'Select a relation to inspect.', and no getDatatypePropertyOptions function exists. App.tsx holds a single selectedRelationId state variable and passes no onNodeSelect/onNodeClick callback to CanvasView. CanvasView.tsx wires onEdgeClick to propagate edge.id upstream but has no onNodeClick wiring to ReactFlow's props, so single-click node selection is entirely absent from the current component tree. For task 2.7, the ecm:LiteralAssertion schema is fully defined in SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.10: top-level project array (not nested under instance), fields subjectIri/predicateIri/value/datatype (required)/language (optional)/createdAt/updatedAt, nine allowed datatypes with no Phase 2 stub restriction to xsd:string-only. No existing fixture contains populated literal assertions; the closest reusable base is canvas-3i-2r-with-ops.jsonld (3 instances, 0 DatatypeProperty terms) combined with the AgeProperty DatatypeProperty from term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld. The Playwright relation-crud.spec.ts pattern (setInputFiles, raw mouse bounding-box click to select, data-testid assertions, download+parse verification) is the established template for Inspector interaction tests. SPEC \u00c2\u00a726 mentions literal assertions under 'selected node details' in the same Inspector panel as relation details but explicitly marks the reference UI as non-normative; no tab/mode mechanism is prescribed.",
