        "open_questions": [
          "Should selectedInstanceId and selectedRelationId be mutually exclusive (clearing the other when one is set), or can both be independently non-null? The current single-state design implies mutual exclusion is implicit, but this is not encoded anywhere.",
          "Should the Inspector auto-switch its display based on selection type (edge click \u00e2\u2020\u2019 relation view, node click \u00e2\u2020\u2019 instance/literal view), or should it present a tabbed mode selector? SPEC \u00c2\u00a726 is non-normative on this point.",
          "What datatype subset should the Phase 2 UI dropdown offer? SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.10 lists nine types for round-trip fidelity but does not restrict the UI; the operator must decide if task 2.7 should offer all nine or a subset (e.g., xsd:string, xsd:integer, xsd:boolean only) for initial implementation.",
          "Should ReactFlow's onNodeClick be used to detect single-click node selection, or should a different interaction (e.g., a separate button/icon on the node card) be used? React Flow's nodesConnectable and elementsSelectable flags interact with click handling in ways that may require testing.",
          "A new fixture combining instances (from canvas-3i-2r-with-ops.jsonld) with at least one owl:DatatypeProperty term is needed for task 2.7 Playwright tests. Should this be a standalone new fixture or an extension of an existing one?"
