        "open_questions": [
          "Applier adds UTF-8 BOM to all new files by contract; the fixture instructions require no BOM on literal-crud-1i-1dp.jsonld. Operator should verify whether the applier's BOM behavior applies to .jsonld files and strip BOM post-apply if needed.",
          "React Flow routes onNodeClick only when elementsSelectable={true}, which is gated on onProjectChange !== undefined. This means node selection is disabled in any read-only CanvasView instance. Confirm this is acceptable or add an independent elementsSelectable prop.",
          "Double-click (via onPaneClick event.detail===2) creates a new instance; single-click (via onNodeClick) selects. If both fire in sequence on a rapid double-click on an existing node, the create gesture may also trigger. This is an edge case to watch in E2E \u00e2\u20ac\u201d may need event.stopPropagation() in handleNodeClick if it surfaces.",
          "Inspector empty-state text changed from 'Select a relation to inspect.' to 'Select a node or relation to inspect.' Existing relation-crud tests only check data-testid visibility, not text content, so they are unaffected \u00e2\u20ac\u201d but any screenshot snapshots comparing text content would need updating.",
          "EditLiteralDialog (FR-U019 edit half) is deferred to follow-up Chain B per task scope. The Inspector instance-mode branch has no edit affordance; the 'gw-literal-value' display is read-only."
        ],
        "summary": "10 changes across 6 files implement Chain A of task 2.7 literal CRUD. CanvasView gains onNodeSelect prop wired to ReactFlow onNodeClick (C1-C4). App.tsx adds selectedInstanceId state with mutual-exclusion against selectedRelationId (C5-C6). Inspector.tsx is replaced with a dual-mode component: instance mode shows literal assertions with Add/Delete controls; relation mode preserves all existing Chain B behavior (C7). AddLiteralDialog.tsx is a new component modeled on AddTermDialog with datatype-property dropdown, value input, optional language tag, and urn:uuid IRI generation (C8). A new fixture provides 1 instance + 1 CanvasLayout node + 1 owl:DatatypeProperty for isolated testing (C9). Three Playwright tests cover AC1/AC2/AC3 using the Event 8 bounding-box click pattern (C10).",
