    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:226-rat-literal-crud-a",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal introduces two new source files (AddLiteralDialog.tsx, literal-crud.spec.ts), one new fixture, and significant modifications to three existing components (Inspector.tsx, App.tsx, CanvasView.tsx) implementing FR-U018 Add and FR-U019 Delete \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this is new feature functionality, not a typo, formatting, or terminology fix.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance (task 220) is present in UPSTREAM and is sufficient. All 17 recon findings and all 5 open questions are addressed by the 10 proposed changes:\n\n**Recon reconciliation:**\n- F4/F5/F6 (Inspector relation-only, App single-state, CanvasView no onNodeClick): addressed by C1\u00e2\u20ac\u201cC6 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d CanvasView gains onNodeSelect wired to ReactFlow onNodeClick, App gains selectedInstanceId with mutual-exclusion callbacks.\n- F7 (no getDatatypePropertyOptions): addressed by C7 (Inspector) and C8 (AddLiteralDialog) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d both define the function independently, with an acknowledged shared-extraction future-refactor note.\n- F10/F11/F12 (no fixture with instances + DatatypeProperty): addressed by C9 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d standalone new fixture with 1 ecm:Instance, 1 ecm:CanvasLayout node, 1 owl:DatatypeProperty (NameProperty), empty ecm:literalAssertions.\n- F13 (AC1/AC2/AC3): addressed by C10 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d three Playwright tests covering each AC.\n- OQ1 (mutual exclusion): addressed \u00e2\u20ac\u201d App.tsx C6 clears the other state variable on each selection event.\n- OQ2 (auto-switch vs tabs): addressed \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Inspector auto-switches based on which of selectedInstanceId/selectedRelationId is non-null.\n- OQ3 (datatype subset): addressed \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all 9 Phase 2 datatypes from SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.10 included in DATATYPE_OPTIONS.\n- OQ4 (ReactFlow onNodeClick): addressed \u00e2\u20ac\u201d C3 wires handleNodeClick to ReactFlow's onNodeClick.\n- OQ5 (new fixture): addressed \u00e2\u20ac\u201d standalone new fixture chosen (not an extension of an existing one).\n\n**FR coverage:**\n- FR-U018 Add: fully covered \u00e2\u20ac\u201d AddLiteralDialog (C8) + Inspector instance-mode 'Add literal' button (C7). All fields per SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.10 schema populated (id, type, ecm:subjectIri, ecm:predicateIri, ecm:value, ecm:datatype, ecm:language).\n- FR-U019 Delete half: covered \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Inspector instance-mode handleDeleteLiteral + gw-btn-delete-literal (C7).\n- FR-U019 Edit half: deferred to follow-up Chain B \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no AC in IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md task 2.7 for edit; deferral is within task scope.\n\n**AC1/AC2/AC3 Playwright credibility:**\n- All three tests use the bounding-box center click pattern (Event 8 lesson) via firstNode.boundingBox() + page.mouse.click. The fixture has exactly 1 react-flow__node so the locator is unambiguous.\n- The fixture instance IRI (e7000000-\u00e2\u20ac\u00a6-0001) and DatatypeProperty IRI (https://example.org/ontology/NameProperty) are constants matched by AC1 assertions \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no ambiguity.\n- AC1 verifies ecm:subjectIri, ecm:predicateIri, ecm:value, ecm:datatype all match the IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.7 criterion exactly.\n- AC2 fills the language field and verifies ecm:language === 'en'.\n- AC3 adds then deletes, verifies ecm:literalAssertions has length 0.\n- The save+download+parse pattern is identical to the established relation-crud.spec.ts pattern.\n- ReactFlow routes onNodeClick only when elementsSelectable={true}; in the AC tests, App passes onProjectChange which gates elementsSelectable=true \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no dead code path.\n\n**Inspector instance-mode / relation-mode separation:**\n- Structural mutual exclusion is enforced at App level (C6): edge click \u00e2\u2020\u2019 setSelectedRelationId(id), setSelectedInstanceId(null); node click \u00e2\u2020\u2019 setSelectedInstanceId(id), setSelectedRelationId(null). Both cannot be non-null simultaneously by construction.\n- Inspector's render logic (C7) checks selectedInstanceId !== null first (instance mode), then falls through to relation mode. The modes share no UI elements; data-testid gw-inspector-instance and gw-inspector-relation are disjoint. Empty-state text updated to 'Select a node or relation to inspect.' reflects dual-mode capability.\n- Existing relation-crud tests check data-testid visibility (gw-inspector-relation), not text content, so they are unaffected by the empty-state text change.\n\n**Fixture canonical-form compliance (gap-15):**\n- Top-level key order verified: @context, id, type, ecm:specVersion, then remaining alphabetically (ecm:createdAt, ecm:instances, ecm:layouts, ecm:literalAssertions, ecm:name, ecm:ontologies, ecm:relations, ecm:serializations, ecm:snapshots, ecm:terms, ecm:updatedAt, iao:isAbout). All alphabetical steps confirmed against serializeVmp rules.\n- @context keys verified alphabetical: cco, ecm, ecm:classIris, ecm:instances, ecm:isSerializationOf, ecm:layouts, ecm:literalAssertions, ecm:objectIri, ecm:ontologies, ecm:predicateIri, ecm:relations, ecm:serializations, ecm:snapshots, ecm:subjectIri, ecm:terms, iao, iao:isAbout, id, owl, rdf, rdfs, rdfs:subClassOf, rdfs:subPropertyOf, type, xsd \u00e2\u20ac\u201d matches canvas-3i-2r-with-ops.jsonld reference ordering exactly.\n- Nested object keys verified alphabetical at every level (ecm:instances[0], ecm:layouts[0], ecm:nodes[0], ecm:terms[0]).\n\n**Layer boundaries:**\n- AddLiteralDialog.tsx imports from Dialog.js (src/ui/) and react \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no kernel or adapter imports. Layer 2 only.\n- Inspector.tsx imports AddLiteralDialog from src/ui/ \u00e2\u20ac\u201d no layer violation.\n- crypto.randomUUID() in AddLiteralDialog mirrors the established pattern in CanvasView.tsx handlePaneClick; the CLAUDE.md constraint (no crypto.getRandomValues()) applies to the kernel, not the UI layer.\n\n**Minor advisories (not blocking):**\n1. ecm:createdAt/ecm:updatedAt absent from newly-created LiteralAssertion objects. SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.10 example includes them, but the AC1 assertion list does not require them, the recon's F2 enumeration (7 fields) omits them, and the isEcmLiteralAssertion guard does not check them. This is a gap relative to the SPEC example but within task scope.\n2. getDatatypePropertyOptions is defined independently in both Inspector.tsx and AddLiteralDialog.tsx \u00e2\u20ac\u201d acknowledged technical debt with 'future refactor' comment.\n3. elementsSelectable is gated on onProjectChange !== undefined, bundling node-selectability with node-mutability \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a potential constraint for future read-only embed contexts.\n\nAll three advisories are below blocking threshold: the ACs are met, the recon is satisfied, and the developer's self-assessment flags all three.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
