          {
            "id": "F17",
            "claim": "An `iriTail` helper already exists in Inspector.tsx that extracts the fragment or last path segment of an IRI; this is used for predicate label display in the dropdown, not for IRI display fields.",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "src/ui/Inspector.tsx",
                "lines": "51-57",
                "excerpt": "/** Extract the IRI tail (fragment after last '#' or last path segment). */\nfunction iriTail(iri: string): string {\n  const hash = iri.lastIndexOf(\"#\");\n  const slash = iri.lastIndexOf(\"/\");\n  const idx = Math.max(hash, slash);\n  return idx >= 0 ? iri.slice(idx + 1) : iri;\n}"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "observation"
          },
          {
            "id": "F18",
            "claim": "The triple-narration module's own comment declares 'SPEC refs: section 7.1, FR-C008'; SPEC \u00c2\u00a77.1 is titled 'In Scope for v0.3' and covers which ontology element types are in scope \u00e2\u20ac\u201d it does not contain narration template wording; the primary normative narration text is in FR-C008 (SPEC \u00c2\u00a718.1).",
