        "summary": "FR-C008 is a substantive five-slot template \u00e2\u20ac\u201d '{subjectLabel} ({className}) {predicateLabel} {objectLabel} ({objectClassName})' \u00e2\u20ac\u201d already implemented as `narrateTriple()` in `src/emit/triple-narration.ts`. The helper is production-path code used by the Markdown emitter. The Inspector (`src/ui/Inspector.tsx`) currently has no preview section in either relation mode (task 2.6) or instance mode (task 2.7): relation mode displays bare IRI strings for Subject and Object without angle-bracket wrapping and has no narration row; instance mode shows a flat literal list with no per-literal selection mechanism. IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN task 2.8 specifies (1) plain-language narration via FR-C008 in the Inspector when a relation is selected, and (2) an RDF-like triple `<subjectIri> <predicateIri> <objectIri> .` also in the Inspector \u00e2\u20ac\u201d angle-bracket notation per RDF conventions. The literal-assertion preview ('same format adapted for literals') appears as a sub-task of 2.8 but has no corresponding acceptance criterion. The existing relation-crud.spec.ts AC3 asserts raw bare IRI text in `gw-inspector-subject` and `gw-inspector-object`; adding angle-bracket notation to those elements would break that assertion. `src/ui/App.tsx` already imports from `src/emit/turtle.js`, establishing that UI\u00e2\u2020\u2019emit imports are an existing pattern. `narrateProject` returns a flat string array without preserving relation IDs, making it unsuitable for looking up a single selected relation's narration; `narrateTriple` with inline label resolution in the Inspector is the natural call shape. The canvas fixture used by relation-crud tests has no `rdfs:label` on instances, so the fallback in `narrateTriple` would use the full `urn:uuid:...` IRI as the display label.",
