        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal adds a new import, a new label-resolution helper function, a new JSX Preview section in Inspector.tsx (two new testid-bearing elements), and a new Playwright spec file \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all net additions of functional behavior, not editorial cleanup.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance (task 229) is present in UPSTREAM and directly addresses every structural question the changes raise. Findings reconcile cleanly with the four proposed changes:\n\n**C1 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d import narrateTriple**: Recon F11/F12/F15 confirm App.tsx already imports from src/emit/ (establishing the UI-to-emit pattern) and that Inspector.tsx currently has no such import. The new import is the correct incremental step.\n\n**C2 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d resolveRelationNarration helper**: Recon F2 documents that narrateProject returns a flat string[] with no per-relation ID, making it unsuitable for single-relation Inspector lookups. The helper correctly mirrors the label-resolution chain documented in recon F3 with one intentional simplification: the `rel[\"rdfs:label\"]` middle fallback in the predicateLabel chain is dropped. The EcmRelation type (Inspector.tsx lines 8\u00e2\u20ac\u201c14) does not declare rdfs:label, and ecm:RelationAssertion records carry no such field in the fixture or in production data \u00e2\u20ac\u201d so this simplification is safe. The className/objectClassName resolution branches are semantically equivalent to narrateProject (verified against triple-narration.ts lines 109\u00e2\u20ac\u201c120). Recon F1 confirms the five-slot FR-C008 template shape; C2's call to narrateTriple satisfies it.\n\n**C3 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d Preview JSX section**: Adds gw-triple-narration (FR-C008 narration) and gw-triple-iri (angle-bracket triple) after the Object display, before the action-button row. Critically, gw-inspector-subject and gw-inspector-object are left unchanged with raw IRI text \u00e2\u20ac\u201d recon F9 documents that existing relation-crud.spec.ts AC3 asserts bare IRI content in those elements; C3 explicitly preserves that contract. Recon F6 confirms `<subjectIri> <predicateIri> <objectIri> .` is the specified IRI triple format. Recon F8/F16 confirm the Inspector placement is correct (right panel) and non-normative.\n\n**C4 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d triple-preview.spec.ts**: Recon F10 confirms no existing tests cover preview assertions. Recon F13/F14 document the fixture's IRI formats and absence of rdfs:label on instances; C4 correctly sets SUBJECT_IRI/OBJECT_IRI to the full urn:uuid fallback labels and PREDICATE_LABEL to 'Relates To' (resolved from the fixture's ecm:terms rdfs:label for 'https://example.org/ontology/relatesTo' \u00e2\u20ac\u201d verified against fixture lines 184\u00e2\u20ac\u201c186). \n\nAC1 assertions: the rendered narration for relation 1 will be 'urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001 (https://example.org/ontology/Thing) Relates To urn:uuid:c3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002 (https://example.org/ontology/Thing)'. The three toContainText assertions (SUBJECT_IRI, PREDICATE_LABEL, OBJECT_IRI) are all satisfied. \n\nAC2 regex: `/<.*> <.*> <.*> \\./` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d verified by trace that this regex (with backtracking) correctly matches the `<sIri> <pIri> <oIri> .` template-literal output at C3. Playwright toHaveText with a non-anchored regex performs a contains match, so the structural shape is verified without over-constraining the text content. \n\nLayer boundaries: src/ui/ importing src/emit/ is the established pattern (recon F11; App.tsx line 11). triple-narration.ts is a pure function per its own header and has no kernel-layer violations.\n\n**FR-U020 scope**: The literal-assertion sub-task is deferred. Recon F7 documents that task 2.8 has no AC for literal assertions; IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN lines 431\u00e2\u20ac\u201c437 confirm both ACs describe relation selection only. The deferral is correct and both developer and recon document the open question explicitly.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
            "type": "upstream_task",
            "id": "urn:fnsr:task:229-recon-triple-preview",
            "field": "outputs.findings"
          },
