            "source": "project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md"
          },
          {
            "type": "spec_section",
            "id": "\u00c2\u00a726 (UI Layout, non-normative)",
            "source": "project/SPEC.md"
          }
        ],
        "bankings": [
          {
            "id": "B1",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "When a bulk emit helper (narrateProject) returns a flat string[] with no per-item ID index, the correct call shape for a per-item UI interaction (Inspector selecting one relation) is a scoped inline resolver that calls the primitive (narrateTriple) directly with locally-resolved label maps \u00e2\u20ac\u201d not the bulk aggregator. The single-relation resolver is a thin mirror of the bulk function's resolution loop, scoped to the typed EcmRelation shape. This 'primitive-direct with scoped resolution' pattern avoids the O(N) scan + index-rebuild cost that would be incurred by calling the bulk aggregator and discarding all but one result, and keeps the UI component independent of the aggregator's output shape evolution."
          },
          {
            "id": "B2",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "When adding new display sections alongside existing Inspector fields that carry existing Playwright testid assertions, new preview content should use new data-testid values (gw-triple-narration, gw-triple-iri) rather than repurposing or wrapping existing ones (gw-inspector-subject, gw-inspector-object). This preserves the prior test contract without modification and makes the new ACs independently falsifiable. The reconnaissance step surfaced the exact AC3 assertion in relation-crud.spec.ts that would have been broken if angle-bracket notation had been added to the existing IRI elements \u00e2\u20ac\u201d confirming that reconnaissance-before-ratification catches backward-compatibility surface area in test contracts, not just in source code."
          }
        ]
      },
