            "claim": "SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.4.1 states the iao:isAbout placeholder blocks export by default for both new projects (MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR path) and migrated v0.3 projects (LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER path), distinguishing the two only in validation severity (error vs. info).",
            "evidence": [
              {
                "file": "project/SPEC.md",
                "lines": "392",
                "excerpt": "`iao:isAbout` is required and must have at least one entry. If the user has not yet declared a subject, the system fills `iao:isAbout` with the placeholder `[\"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\"]` and emits validation finding `MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR` (an error) or `LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER` (info, after v0.3 migration). The placeholder is treated as an editor-acknowledged \"I will fill this in soon\" marker but blocks export by default."
