        "summary": "Both MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR (\u00c2\u00a717.2 hard error) and LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER (\u00c2\u00a717.4 info) are implemented in src/validate/index.ts as Phase 1 work \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the latter was resolved at task 1.9 via ft-097-test-validator-3 Option A, not deferred at ft-097-test-validator-2 (which covers the remaining 24 codes). The two findings are mutually exclusive by a boolean document marker `ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder: true` set only by the v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4 migration leg; LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER is therefore a validator code driven by this marker, not a direct UI-side IRI detection. The placeholder IRI string is `ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter` across all three sites (migrate, validate, buildNewDocument). iao:isAbout entries are IRI strings (`@type: @id`), not objects. For AC1 (new project indicator), validate() currently produces MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR on a new-project document but the result is discarded and validate() is not called at all from handleNew(). The header layout is a flex row with gw-brand + gw-btn-group (4 buttons: New/Open/Save/Save as Turtle) + conditional migration banner (margin-left: auto); no Project Settings button exists. All three existing dialogs share the Dialog.tsx base component (native `<dialog>`, showModal(), title bar, gw-dialog-body slot) and the gw-term-form / gw-form-* CSS vocabulary.",
