        "open_questions": [
          "The scripts/README.md documents '2 of 26 validation codes' shipped in Phase 1, but src/validate/index.ts implements 4 codes (adding LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER and NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE). The architect/operator should confirm whether the demo script documentation needs updating or whether the '2 of 26' claim is intentionally scoped to CLI-demonstrable error-path codes only.",
          "For AC1 (new project shows MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR indicator): validate() is not called from handleNew() at all in the current App.tsx. The architect must decide whether task 2.9 wires validate() into handleNew() directly, or whether a separate reactive derive-from-document-state path (reading iao:isAbout + ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder without running the full validator) is the intended AC1 trigger mechanism.",
          "IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md task 2.9 names this feature a 'Project-settings UI' but FR-U031 only specifies iao:isAbout declaration/editing \u00e2\u20ac\u201d it does not specify other project settings. The architect should confirm whether the Project Settings button/dialog is scoped to iao:isAbout only, or whether it is intended to expose ecm:settings (IRI generation policy, export defaults, determinism) from SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.5 as well.",
