    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:235-dev-isabout",
      "agent": "developer",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "changes": [
          {
            "id": "C1",
            "file": "src/ui/ProjectSettingsDialog.tsx",
            "rationale": "New dialog component for FR-U031 iao:isAbout declaration. Follows the Dialog base + gw-term-form CSS vocabulary pattern used by AddTermDialog / AddLiteralDialog. Validates Add input (not empty, not ECM_UNSPECIFIED placeholder). Clears ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder from the document (via undefined so JSON.stringify omits it) when at least one real IRI is saved, keeping validate() and deriveIsAboutState consistent post-declaration.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "/**\n * ProjectSettingsDialog -- iao:isAbout declaration UI (FR-U031, task 2.9).\n *\n * Allows the user to view, add, and remove iao:isAbout subject IRIs.\n * Uses the Dialog base component (same pattern as AddTermDialog).\n * Layer boundary: src/ui/ only; SPEC section 5.4.1 for IRI semantics.\n */\n\nimport { useState, type FormEvent } from \"react\";\nimport { Dialog } from \"./Dialog.js\";\n\n/** The placeholder IRI per SPEC section 5.4.1; must not be added as a real subject. */\nconst ECM_UNSPECIFIED = \"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\";\n\ninterface ProjectSettingsDialogProps {\n  project: Record<string, unknown>;\n  /** Called with the updated project document when the user clicks Save. */\n  onSave: (updated: Record<string, unknown>) => void;\n  onClose: () => void;\n}\n\n/** Extract current iao:isAbout entries as a string array from the project document. */\nfunction extractIsAbout(project: Record<string, unknown>): string[] {\n  const raw = project[\"iao:isAbout\"];\n  if (Array.isArray(raw)) {\n    return (raw as unknown[]).filter(\n      (v): v is string => typeof v === \"string\",\n    );\n  }\n  if (typeof raw === \"string\") return [raw];\n  return [];\n}\n\nexport function ProjectSettingsDialog({\n  project,\n  onSave,\n  onClose,\n}: ProjectSettingsDialogProps) {\n  const [isAbout, setIsAbout] = useState<string[]>(() =>\n    extractIsAbout(project),\n  );\n  const [addInput, setAddInput] = useState(\"\");\n  const [addError, setAddError] = useState<string | null>(null);\n\n  function handleAdd() {\n    const trimmed = addInput.trim();\n    if (trimmed.length === 0) {\n      setAddError(\"IRI must not be empty.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if (trimmed === ECM_UNSPECIFIED) {\n      setAddError(\n        \"Cannot add the placeholder IRI. Enter a real subject IRI.\",\n      );\n      return;\n    }\n    if (isAbout.includes(trimmed)) {\n      setAddError(\"This IRI is already in the list.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    setIsAbout((prev) => [...prev, trimmed]);\n    setAddInput(\"\");\n    setAddError(null);\n  }\n\n  function handleRemove(iri: string) {\n    setIsAbout((prev) => prev.filter((v) => v !== iri));\n  }\n\n  function handleSave(e: FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    const hasRealIri = isAbout.some((v) => v !== ECM_UNSPECIFIED);\n    const updated: Record<string, unknown> = {\n      ...project,\n      \"iao:isAbout\": isAbout,\n    };\n    if (hasRealIri) {\n      // Clear the migration marker once a real subject IRI is declared so that\n      // if the user later empties the list, validate() emits\n      // MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR (not LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER).\n      // Setting to undefined causes JSON.stringify (used by serializeVmp) to\n      // omit the field from the saved document.\n      updated[\"ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder\"] = undefined;\n    }\n    onSave(updated);\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <Dialog\n      title=\"Project Settings\"\n      onClose={onClose}\n      testId=\"gw-dialog-project-settings\"\n    >\n      <form\n        className=\"gw-term-form\"\n        onSubmit={handleSave}\n        data-testid=\"gw-form-project-settings\"\n      >\n        <div className=\"gw-form-label\">\n          Subject IRIs (<code>iao:isAbout</code>)\n        </div>\n        {isAbout.length === 0 ? (\n          <p className=\"gw-placeholder\" data-testid=\"gw-isabout-empty\">\n            No subject IRIs declared.\n          </p>\n        ) : (\n          <ul className=\"gw-iri-list\" data-testid=\"gw-isabout-list\">\n            {isAbout.map((iri) => (\n              <li key={iri} className=\"gw-iri-item\">\n                <span\n                  className=\"gw-iri-value\"\n                  title={iri}\n                  data-testid=\"gw-iri-value\"\n                >\n                  {iri}\n                </span>\n                <button\n                  type=\"button\"\n                  className=\"gw-btn gw-btn--secondary gw-btn--sm\"\n                  onClick={() => { handleRemove(iri); }}\n                  aria-label={`Remove ${iri}`}\n                  data-testid=\"gw-btn-remove-iri\"\n                >\n                  Remove\n                </button>\n              </li>\n            ))}\n          </ul>\n        )}\n        <div className=\"gw-iri-add-row\">\n          <input\n            className=\"gw-form-input\"\n            type=\"text\"\n            placeholder=\"https://example.org/MySubject\"\n            value={addInput}\n            onChange={(e) => {\n              setAddInput(e.target.value);\n              setAddError(null);\n            }}\n            data-testid=\"gw-input-isabout-iri\"\n          />\n          <button\n            type=\"button\"\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            onClick={handleAdd}\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-add-iri\"\n          >\n            Add IRI\n          </button>\n        </div>\n        {addError !== null && (\n          <p\n            className=\"gw-form-error\"\n            role=\"alert\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-isabout-add-error\"\n          >\n            {addError}\n          </p>\n        )}\n        <div className=\"gw-form-actions\">\n          <button\n            type=\"button\"\n            className=\"gw-btn gw-btn--secondary\"\n            onClick={onClose}\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-settings-cancel\"\n          >\n            Cancel\n          </button>\n          <button\n            type=\"submit\"\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-settings-save\"\n          >\n            Save\n          </button>\n        </div>\n      </form>\n    </Dialog>\n  );\n}\n",
            "scope": "moderate"
          },
          {
            "id": "C2",
            "file": "src/ui/App.tsx",
            "rationale": "Full replacement to add: (1) ProjectSettingsDialog import, (2) ECM_UNSPECIFIED const + deriveIsAboutState helper (mirrors validator logic; avoids calling validate() for reactive indicator), (3) projectSettingsOpen state, (4) isAboutState derived value, (5) 'Project Settings' header button, (6) anchor banner strip between header and body (data-anchor-state attribute for test selection), (7) conditional ProjectSettingsDialog render. The onSave callback threads setProject + close, ensuring the indicator re-derives from the updated project immediately after dialog save. All pre-existing handler bodies are preserved verbatim.",
            "before": "import { useState, useRef, type ChangeEvent } from \"react\";\nimport \"./App.css\";\nimport \"@xyflow/react/dist/style.css\";\nimport { CanvasView } from \"./CanvasView.js\";\nimport { Inspector } from \"./Inspector.js\";\nimport { TermSidebar } from \"./TermSidebar.js\";\nimport { migrate } from \"../migrate/index.js\";\nimport { normalizeOnLoad } from \"../normalize/index.js\";\nimport { validate } from \"../validate/index.js\";\nimport { serializeVmp } from \"../kernel/canonicalize.js\";\nimport { emitTurtle } from \"../emit/turtle.js\";\n\n/**\n * Minimal v0.4 project document for FR-U001 New.\n * Per SPEC section 5 required fields + section 10.4 type/iao:isAbout shape.\n * ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder is NOT set: validate() emits\n * MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR (error); ecm:error display is FR-U028 scope (task 2.8).\n */\nfunction buildNewDocument(): Record<string, unknown> {\n  return {\n    id: \"urn:ecm:project:new\",\n    type: [\"ecm:Project\", \"iao:OntologyDesignPattern\"],\n    \"ecm:specVersion\": \"0.4\",\n    \"ecm:createdAt\": \"1970-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"ecm:instances\": [],\n    \"ecm:layouts\": [],\n    \"ecm:literalAssertions\": [],\n    \"ecm:name\": \"Untitled Project\",\n    \"ecm:ontologies\": [],\n    \"ecm:relations\": [],\n    \"ecm:serializations\": [],\n    \"ecm:snapshots\": [],\n    \"ecm:terms\": [],\n    \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"1970-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"iao:isAbout\": [\"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\"],\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * GraphWrite App shell -- SPEC section 26 five-panel layout.\n *\n * Panels populated in subsequent tasks:\n *   Left sidebar (Term Manager): task 2.2\n *   Center canvas (Instance Canvas): task 2.4\n *   Right inspector: task 2.5+\n *   Bottom outputs: task 2.10\n * FR-U001 / FR-U002 / FR-U003 / FR-U029 header controls: task 2.1 Chain 2.\n */\nexport function App() {\n  const [project, setProject] = useState<Record<string, unknown> | null>(null);\n  const [migrationBannerText, setMigrationBannerText] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [selectedRelationId, setSelectedRelationId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [selectedInstanceId, setSelectedInstanceId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const fileInputRef = useRef<HTMLInputElement>(null);\n\n  // FR-U001: New project\n  function handleNew() {\n    setProject(buildNewDocument());\n    setMigrationBannerText(null);\n  }\n\n  // FR-U002: Open project -- trigger hidden file input\n  function handleOpen() {\n    fileInputRef.current?.click();\n  }\n\n  // FR-U002: File selected -- read, migrate, normalize, validate, set state\n  function handleFileChange(event: ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) {\n    const file = event.target.files?.[0];\n    if (file === undefined) return;\n\n    const reader = new FileReader();\n    reader.onload = (loadEvent: ProgressEvent<FileReader>) => {\n      const raw = loadEvent.target?.result;\n      if (typeof raw !== \"string\") return;\n\n      let parsed: Record<string, unknown>;\n      try {\n        parsed = JSON.parse(raw) as Record<string, unknown>;\n      } catch {\n        // TODO (task 2.8): surface parse errors to user\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Capture source version BEFORE migrate() for FR-U029 banner text.\n      const fromVersion =\n        typeof parsed[\"ecm:specVersion\"] === \"string\"\n          ? (parsed[\"ecm:specVersion\"] as string)\n          : null;\n\n      const migrateResult = migrate(parsed);\n      if (migrateResult.document === null) {\n        // TODO (task 2.8): surface migration refusal to user\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const { document: migrated, migrationReport } = migrateResult;\n\n      // Detect if migration actually occurred: any report arrays non-empty.\n      const wasMigrated =\n        migrationReport.addedFields.length > 0 ||\n        migrationReport.transformedFields.length > 0 ||\n        migrationReport.removedFields.length > 0 ||\n        migrationReport.info.length > 0;\n\n      const { document: normalized } = normalizeOnLoad(migrated);\n      // Call validate per FR-U002; findings display deferred to task 2.8.\n      void validate(normalized);\n\n      setProject(normalized);\n\n      if (wasMigrated) {\n        const from = fromVersion ?? \"unknown\";\n        setMigrationBannerText(`Project was migrated from v${from} to v0.4.`);\n      } else {\n        setMigrationBannerText(null);\n      }\n    };\n\n    reader.readAsText(file);\n    // Reset input so the same file can be re-opened in the same session.\n    event.target.value = \"\";\n  }\n\n  // FR-U003: Save project -- canonical serialize -> Blob -> browser download\n  function handleSave() {\n    if (project === null) return;\n    const text = serializeVmp(project);\n    const blob = new Blob([text], { type: \"application/ld+json\" });\n    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n    const anchor = document.createElement(\"a\");\n    anchor.href = url;\n    anchor.download = \"project.jsonld\";\n    anchor.click();\n    URL.revokeObjectURL(url);\n  }\n\n  // FR-U023: Save as Turtle -- semantic projection -> Blob -> browser download\n  function handleSaveTurtle() {\n    if (project === null) return;\n    const text = emitTurtle(project);\n    const blob = new Blob([text], { type: \"text/turtle\" });\n    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n    const anchor = document.createElement(\"a\");\n    anchor.href = url;\n    anchor.download = \"project.ttl\";\n    anchor.click();\n    URL.revokeObjectURL(url);\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"gw-shell\">\n      <header className=\"gw-header\" data-testid=\"gw-header\">\n        <span className=\"gw-brand\">GraphWrite</span>\n        <div className=\"gw-btn-group\">\n          <button\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-new\"\n            onClick={handleNew}\n          >\n            New\n          </button>\n          <button\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-open\"\n            onClick={handleOpen}\n          >\n            Open\n          </button>\n          <button\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-save\"\n            onClick={handleSave}\n            disabled={project === null}\n          >\n            Save\n          </button>\n          <button\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-save-turtle\"\n            onClick={handleSaveTurtle}\n            disabled={project === null}\n          >\n            Save as Turtle\n          </button>\n        </div>\n        <input\n          ref={fileInputRef}\n          type=\"file\"\n          accept=\".jsonld,.json\"\n          style={{ display: \"none\" }}\n          data-testid=\"gw-file-input\"\n          onChange={handleFileChange}\n        />\n        {migrationBannerText !== null && (\n          <div\n            className=\"gw-migration-banner\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-migration-banner\"\n          >\n            <span>{migrationBannerText}</span>\n            <button\n              className=\"gw-migration-dismiss\"\n              data-testid=\"gw-migration-dismiss\"\n              onClick={() => { setMigrationBannerText(null); }}\n              aria-label=\"Dismiss migration notice\"\n            >\n              &#x2715;\n            </button>\n          </div>\n        )}\n      </header>\n\n      <div className=\"gw-body\">\n        <aside className=\"gw-sidebar\" data-testid=\"gw-sidebar\">\n          <TermSidebar\n            project={project}\n            onTermsChange={(updated) => { setProject(updated); }}\n          />\n        </aside>\n\n        <main className=\"gw-canvas\" data-testid=\"gw-canvas\">\n          <CanvasView\n            project={project}\n            onProjectChange={(updated) => { setProject(updated); }}\n            onEdgeSelect={(id) => { setSelectedRelationId(id); setSelectedInstanceId(null); }}\n            onNodeSelect={(id) => { setSelectedInstanceId(id); setSelectedRelationId(null); }}\n          />\n        </main>\n\n        <aside className=\"gw-inspector\" data-testid=\"gw-inspector\">\n          <Inspector\n            selectedRelationId={selectedRelationId}\n            selectedInstanceId={selectedInstanceId}\n            project={project}\n            onProjectChange={(updated) => { setProject(updated); }}\n          />\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n\n      <section className=\"gw-outputs\" data-testid=\"gw-outputs\">\n        <p className=\"gw-placeholder\">Outputs -- task 2.10</p>\n      </section>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n",
            "after": "import { useState, useRef, type ChangeEvent } from \"react\";\nimport \"./App.css\";\nimport \"@xyflow/react/dist/style.css\";\nimport { CanvasView } from \"./CanvasView.js\";\nimport { Inspector } from \"./Inspector.js\";\nimport { TermSidebar } from \"./TermSidebar.js\";\nimport { migrate } from \"../migrate/index.js\";\nimport { normalizeOnLoad } from \"../normalize/index.js\";\nimport { validate } from \"../validate/index.js\";\nimport { serializeVmp } from \"../kernel/canonicalize.js\";\nimport { emitTurtle } from \"../emit/turtle.js\";\nimport { ProjectSettingsDialog } from \"./ProjectSettingsDialog.js\";\n\n/**\n * Minimal v0.4 project document for FR-U001 New.\n * Per SPEC section 5 required fields + section 10.4 type/iao:isAbout shape.\n * ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder is NOT set: validate() emits\n * MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR (error); ecm:error display is FR-U028 scope (task 2.8).\n */\nfunction buildNewDocument(): Record<string, unknown> {\n  return {\n    id: \"urn:ecm:project:new\",\n    type: [\"ecm:Project\", \"iao:OntologyDesignPattern\"],\n    \"ecm:specVersion\": \"0.4\",\n    \"ecm:createdAt\": \"1970-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"ecm:instances\": [],\n    \"ecm:layouts\": [],\n    \"ecm:literalAssertions\": [],\n    \"ecm:name\": \"Untitled Project\",\n    \"ecm:ontologies\": [],\n    \"ecm:relations\": [],\n    \"ecm:serializations\": [],\n    \"ecm:snapshots\": [],\n    \"ecm:terms\": [],\n    \"ecm:updatedAt\": \"1970-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"iao:isAbout\": [\"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\"],\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * The placeholder IRI used by migration, buildNewDocument, and the validator.\n * Defined here (src/ui layer) to avoid a cross-layer import from src/validate/\n * just for the constant. Kept in sync with SPEC section 5.4.1.\n */\nconst ECM_UNSPECIFIED = \"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\";\n\n/**\n * Derive the iao:isAbout indicator state from a project document.\n * Mirrors the validator logic in src/validate/index.ts (SPEC sections 17.2, 17.4)\n * without calling validate() -- used for reactive UI indicator display only.\n *\n * \"missing\" -- iao:isAbout absent/empty or contains only ECM_UNSPECIFIED\n *              with no legacy marker; MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR would fire.\n * \"legacy\"  -- ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder is true and iao:isAbout contains\n *              only ECM_UNSPECIFIED; LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER would fire.\n * \"clean\"   -- at least one real (non-placeholder) IRI present; no finding fires.\n */\nfunction deriveIsAboutState(\n  doc: Record<string, unknown>,\n): \"clean\" | \"missing\" | \"legacy\" {\n  const raw = doc[\"iao:isAbout\"];\n  const arr: unknown[] = Array.isArray(raw)\n    ? raw\n    : raw !== undefined\n    ? [raw]\n    : [];\n  const nonPlaceholder = arr.filter(\n    (v): v is string => typeof v === \"string\" && v !== ECM_UNSPECIFIED,\n  );\n  if (nonPlaceholder.length > 0) return \"clean\";\n  const isLegacy = doc[\"ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder\"] === true;\n  if (isLegacy && arr.some((v) => v === ECM_UNSPECIFIED)) return \"legacy\";\n  return \"missing\";\n}\n\n/**\n * GraphWrite App shell -- SPEC section 26 five-panel layout.\n *\n * Panels populated in subsequent tasks:\n *   Left sidebar (Term Manager): task 2.2\n *   Center canvas (Instance Canvas): task 2.4\n *   Right inspector: task 2.5+\n *   Bottom outputs: task 2.10\n * FR-U001 / FR-U002 / FR-U003 / FR-U029 header controls: task 2.1 Chain 2.\n */\nexport function App() {\n  const [project, setProject] = useState<Record<string, unknown> | null>(null);\n  const [migrationBannerText, setMigrationBannerText] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [selectedRelationId, setSelectedRelationId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [selectedInstanceId, setSelectedInstanceId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n  const [projectSettingsOpen, setProjectSettingsOpen] = useState(false);\n  const fileInputRef = useRef<HTMLInputElement>(null);\n\n  // Derived: iao:isAbout indicator state (clean | missing | legacy).\n  // Computed from project document; no validate() call required for indicator.\n  const isAboutState = project !== null ? deriveIsAboutState(project) : \"clean\";\n\n  // FR-U001: New project\n  function handleNew() {\n    setProject(buildNewDocument());\n    setMigrationBannerText(null);\n  }\n\n  // FR-U002: Open project -- trigger hidden file input\n  function handleOpen() {\n    fileInputRef.current?.click();\n  }\n\n  // FR-U002: File selected -- read, migrate, normalize, validate, set state\n  function handleFileChange(event: ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) {\n    const file = event.target.files?.[0];\n    if (file === undefined) return;\n\n    const reader = new FileReader();\n    reader.onload = (loadEvent: ProgressEvent<FileReader>) => {\n      const raw = loadEvent.target?.result;\n      if (typeof raw !== \"string\") return;\n\n      let parsed: Record<string, unknown>;\n      try {\n        parsed = JSON.parse(raw) as Record<string, unknown>;\n      } catch {\n        // TODO (task 2.8): surface parse errors to user\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Capture source version BEFORE migrate() for FR-U029 banner text.\n      const fromVersion =\n        typeof parsed[\"ecm:specVersion\"] === \"string\"\n          ? (parsed[\"ecm:specVersion\"] as string)\n          : null;\n\n      const migrateResult = migrate(parsed);\n      if (migrateResult.document === null) {\n        // TODO (task 2.8): surface migration refusal to user\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const { document: migrated, migrationReport } = migrateResult;\n\n      // Detect if migration actually occurred: any report arrays non-empty.\n      const wasMigrated =\n        migrationReport.addedFields.length > 0 ||\n        migrationReport.transformedFields.length > 0 ||\n        migrationReport.removedFields.length > 0 ||\n        migrationReport.info.length > 0;\n\n      const { document: normalized } = normalizeOnLoad(migrated);\n      // Call validate per FR-U002; findings display deferred to task 2.8.\n      void validate(normalized);\n\n      setProject(normalized);\n\n      if (wasMigrated) {\n        const from = fromVersion ?? \"unknown\";\n        setMigrationBannerText(`Project was migrated from v${from} to v0.4.`);\n      } else {\n        setMigrationBannerText(null);\n      }\n    };\n\n    reader.readAsText(file);\n    // Reset input so the same file can be re-opened in the same session.\n    event.target.value = \"\";\n  }\n\n  // FR-U003: Save project -- canonical serialize -> Blob -> browser download\n  function handleSave() {\n    if (project === null) return;\n    const text = serializeVmp(project);\n    const blob = new Blob([text], { type: \"application/ld+json\" });\n    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n    const anchor = document.createElement(\"a\");\n    anchor.href = url;\n    anchor.download = \"project.jsonld\";\n    anchor.click();\n    URL.revokeObjectURL(url);\n  }\n\n  // FR-U023: Save as Turtle -- semantic projection -> Blob -> browser download\n  function handleSaveTurtle() {\n    if (project === null) return;\n    const text = emitTurtle(project);\n    const blob = new Blob([text], { type: \"text/turtle\" });\n    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n    const anchor = document.createElement(\"a\");\n    anchor.href = url;\n    anchor.download = \"project.ttl\";\n    anchor.click();\n    URL.revokeObjectURL(url);\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"gw-shell\">\n      <header className=\"gw-header\" data-testid=\"gw-header\">\n        <span className=\"gw-brand\">GraphWrite</span>\n        <div className=\"gw-btn-group\">\n          <button\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-new\"\n            onClick={handleNew}\n          >\n            New\n          </button>\n          <button\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-open\"\n            onClick={handleOpen}\n          >\n            Open\n          </button>\n          <button\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-save\"\n            onClick={handleSave}\n            disabled={project === null}\n          >\n            Save\n          </button>\n          <button\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-save-turtle\"\n            onClick={handleSaveTurtle}\n            disabled={project === null}\n          >\n            Save as Turtle\n          </button>\n          <button\n            className=\"gw-btn\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-project-settings\"\n            onClick={() => { setProjectSettingsOpen(true); }}\n            disabled={project === null}\n          >\n            Project Settings\n          </button>\n        </div>\n        <input\n          ref={fileInputRef}\n          type=\"file\"\n          accept=\".jsonld,.json\"\n          style={{ display: \"none\" }}\n          data-testid=\"gw-file-input\"\n          onChange={handleFileChange}\n        />\n        {migrationBannerText !== null && (\n          <div\n            className=\"gw-migration-banner\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-migration-banner\"\n          >\n            <span>{migrationBannerText}</span>\n            <button\n              className=\"gw-migration-dismiss\"\n              data-testid=\"gw-migration-dismiss\"\n              onClick={() => { setMigrationBannerText(null); }}\n              aria-label=\"Dismiss migration notice\"\n            >\n              &#x2715;\n            </button>\n          </div>\n        )}\n      </header>\n\n      {project !== null && isAboutState !== \"clean\" && (\n        <div\n          className={`gw-anchor-banner gw-anchor-banner--${isAboutState}`}\n          data-testid=\"gw-anchor-banner\"\n          data-anchor-state={isAboutState}\n        >\n          <span className=\"gw-anchor-banner-text\">\n            {isAboutState === \"missing\"\n              ? \"No subject declared (MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR). Export is blocked until a real subject IRI is added.\"\n              : \"Subject placeholder from v0.3 migration (LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER). Replace with a real subject IRI.\"}\n          </span>\n          <button\n            className=\"gw-btn gw-btn--sm gw-btn--anchor-action\"\n            data-testid=\"gw-btn-anchor-action\"\n            onClick={() => { setProjectSettingsOpen(true); }}\n          >\n            {isAboutState === \"missing\" ? \"Add subject IRI\" : \"Set real subject\"}\n          </button>\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      <div className=\"gw-body\">\n        <aside className=\"gw-sidebar\" data-testid=\"gw-sidebar\">\n          <TermSidebar\n            project={project}\n            onTermsChange={(updated) => { setProject(updated); }}\n          />\n        </aside>\n\n        <main className=\"gw-canvas\" data-testid=\"gw-canvas\">\n          <CanvasView\n            project={project}\n            onProjectChange={(updated) => { setProject(updated); }}\n            onEdgeSelect={(id) => { setSelectedRelationId(id); setSelectedInstanceId(null); }}\n            onNodeSelect={(id) => { setSelectedInstanceId(id); setSelectedRelationId(null); }}\n          />\n        </main>\n\n        <aside className=\"gw-inspector\" data-testid=\"gw-inspector\">\n          <Inspector\n            selectedRelationId={selectedRelationId}\n            selectedInstanceId={selectedInstanceId}\n            project={project}\n            onProjectChange={(updated) => { setProject(updated); }}\n          />\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n\n      <section className=\"gw-outputs\" data-testid=\"gw-outputs\">\n        <p className=\"gw-placeholder\">Outputs -- task 2.10</p>\n      </section>\n\n      {projectSettingsOpen && project !== null && (\n        <ProjectSettingsDialog\n          project={project}\n          onSave={(updated) => {\n            setProject(updated);\n            setProjectSettingsOpen(false);\n          }}\n          onClose={() => { setProjectSettingsOpen(false); }}\n        />\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n",
            "scope": "moderate"
          },
          {
            "id": "C3",
            "file": "src/ui/App.css",
            "rationale": "Append two new CSS sections: (1) anchor banner styles with --missing (red/error) and --legacy (amber/info) variants plus .gw-btn--anchor-action override using doubled-class specificity to reliably beat .gw-btn:hover; (2) project-settings dialog list styles (.gw-iri-list, .gw-iri-item, .gw-iri-value, .gw-iri-add-row) plus .gw-btn--sm small-button variant. All new classes are additive; no existing rules modified.",
            "before": ".gw-btn--secondary:hover:not(:disabled) {\n  background: #f1f5f9;\n  border-color: #64748b;\n}\n",
            "after": ".gw-btn--secondary:hover:not(:disabled) {\n  background: #f1f5f9;\n  border-color: #64748b;\n}\n\n/* -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n * iao:isAbout indicator banner (FR-U031 task 2.9)\n * --------------------------------------------------------------------- */\n\n.gw-anchor-banner {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  gap: 0.75rem;\n  padding: 0.375rem 1rem;\n  font-size: 0.8125rem;\n  flex-shrink: 0;\n}\n\n.gw-anchor-banner--missing {\n  background: #fef2f2;\n  border-bottom: 1px solid #fca5a5;\n  color: #991b1b;\n}\n\n.gw-anchor-banner--legacy {\n  background: #fffbeb;\n  border-bottom: 1px solid #fcd34d;\n  color: #92400e;\n}\n\n.gw-anchor-banner-text {\n  flex: 1;\n}\n\n.gw-btn--sm {\n  padding: 0.125rem 0.5rem;\n  font-size: 0.8125rem;\n}\n\n/* Doubled-class selector beats .gw-btn base specificity (0,2,0 > 0,1,0). */\n.gw-btn.gw-btn--anchor-action {\n  background: transparent;\n  border-color: currentColor;\n  color: inherit;\n}\n\n.gw-btn.gw-btn--anchor-action:hover:not(:disabled) {\n  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);\n}\n\n/* -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n * Project Settings Dialog: iao:isAbout list (FR-U031 task 2.9)\n * --------------------------------------------------------------------- */\n\n.gw-iri-list {\n  list-style: none;\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  gap: 0.375rem;\n  max-height: 10rem;\n  overflow-y: auto;\n  border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\n  border-radius: 4px;\n  padding: 0.375rem;\n}\n\n.gw-iri-item {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  gap: 0.5rem;\n}\n\n.gw-iri-value {\n  flex: 1;\n  overflow: hidden;\n  text-overflow: ellipsis;\n  white-space: nowrap;\n  font-size: 0.8125rem;\n  color: #1e293b;\n  font-family: monospace;\n}\n\n.gw-iri-add-row {\n  display: flex;\n  gap: 0.5rem;\n  align-items: center;\n}\n\n.gw-iri-add-row .gw-form-input {\n  flex: 1;\n}\n",
            "scope": "minimal"
          },
          {
            "id": "C4",
            "file": "tests/playwright/isabout-ui.spec.ts",
            "rationale": "Four Playwright tests covering the 4 ACs. AC1 asserts gw-anchor-banner visible with data-anchor-state='missing' after New. AC2 opens settings, adds a real IRI, saves dialog, downloads file, parses JSON-LD, asserts iao:isAbout contains the IRI. AC3 asserts banner disappears after IRI declaration (not.toBeVisible() passes even when element not in DOM). AC4 opens minimal-v0.3.jsonld fixture (which migrate() will annotate with ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder:true), asserts banner shows data-anchor-state='legacy' and gw-btn-anchor-action reads 'Set real subject'. Fixture path matches the pattern used in new-open-save.spec.ts.",
            "before": null,
            "after": "import { test, expect } from \"@playwright/test\";\nimport path from \"path\";\nimport fs from \"fs\";\n\n/**\n * Task 2.9 -- FR-U031 iao:isAbout Declaration UI.\n *\n * AC1: New project shows MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR indicator banner.\n * AC2: Open settings, add IRI, Save dialog, download file, parse:\n *      iao:isAbout contains the added IRI.\n * AC3: After IRI declaration via settings, indicator banner not visible.\n * AC4: Open v0.3 fixture: LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER indicator +\n *      \"Set real subject\" affordance visible.\n */\n\nconst V03_FIXTURE = path.join(\n  process.cwd(),\n  \"tests\",\n  \"playwright\",\n  \"fixtures\",\n  \"minimal-v0.3.jsonld\",\n);\n\ntest.describe(\"iao:isAbout Declaration UI (FR-U031 task 2.9)\", () => {\n  test(\"AC1: New project shows MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR indicator\", async ({\n    page,\n  }) => {\n    await page.goto(\"/\");\n    await page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-new\").click();\n    // Wait for React state update -- Save becomes enabled once project != null\n    await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\")).toBeEnabled();\n\n    const banner = page.getByTestId(\"gw-anchor-banner\");\n    await expect(banner).toBeVisible();\n    await expect(banner).toHaveAttribute(\"data-anchor-state\", \"missing\");\n  });\n\n  test(\n    \"AC2: Add subject IRI via settings dialog; saved file contains the IRI\",\n    async ({ page }) => {\n      await page.goto(\"/\");\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-new\").click();\n      await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\")).toBeEnabled();\n\n      // Open Project Settings dialog\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-project-settings\").click();\n      await expect(\n        page.getByTestId(\"gw-dialog-project-settings\"),\n      ).toBeVisible();\n\n      // Add a real subject IRI\n      await page\n        .getByTestId(\"gw-input-isabout-iri\")\n        .fill(\"https://example.org/MySubject\");\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-add-iri\").click();\n\n      // Save dialog -- updates in-memory project\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-settings-save\").click();\n      await expect(\n        page.getByTestId(\"gw-dialog-project-settings\"),\n      ).not.toBeVisible();\n\n      // Download project JSON-LD\n      const [download] = await Promise.all([\n        page.waitForEvent(\"download\"),\n        page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\").click(),\n      ]);\n      const downloadPath = await download.path();\n      expect(downloadPath, \"download must be saved to disk\").not.toBeNull();\n\n      const content = fs.readFileSync(downloadPath!, \"utf-8\");\n      const parsed = JSON.parse(content) as Record<string, unknown>;\n      const isAbout = parsed[\"iao:isAbout\"];\n      expect(\n        Array.isArray(isAbout),\n        \"iao:isAbout must be an array\",\n      ).toBe(true);\n      expect(\n        isAbout as string[],\n        \"iao:isAbout must contain the added IRI\",\n      ).toContain(\"https://example.org/MySubject\");\n    },\n  );\n\n  test(\n    \"AC3: After IRI declaration via settings, indicator banner not visible\",\n    async ({ page }) => {\n      await page.goto(\"/\");\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-new\").click();\n      await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\")).toBeEnabled();\n\n      // Confirm indicator is shown before declaration\n      await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-anchor-banner\")).toBeVisible();\n\n      // Open settings, add a real IRI, save dialog\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-project-settings\").click();\n      await page\n        .getByTestId(\"gw-input-isabout-iri\")\n        .fill(\"https://example.org/DeclaredSubject\");\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-add-iri\").click();\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-settings-save\").click();\n\n      // Indicator must not be visible after declaration\n      // (passes whether element is hidden or absent from DOM)\n      await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-anchor-banner\")).not.toBeVisible();\n    },\n  );\n\n  test(\n    \"AC4: Open v0.3 fixture shows LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER indicator\",\n    async ({ page }) => {\n      await page.goto(\"/\");\n      // FR-U002: load v0.3 fixture via hidden file input\n      await page.getByTestId(\"gw-file-input\").setInputFiles(V03_FIXTURE);\n      // Wait for async FileReader + React state update\n      await expect(page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-save\")).toBeEnabled();\n\n      const banner = page.getByTestId(\"gw-anchor-banner\");\n      await expect(banner).toBeVisible();\n      await expect(banner).toHaveAttribute(\"data-anchor-state\", \"legacy\");\n\n      // \"Set real subject\" affordance must be present and visible\n      const actionBtn = page.getByTestId(\"gw-btn-anchor-action\");\n      await expect(actionBtn).toBeVisible();\n      await expect(actionBtn).toContainText(\"Set real subject\");\n    },\n  );\n});\n",
            "scope": "moderate"
          }
        ],
        "tests_recommended": [
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/isabout-ui.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC5 (gap): Test that the placeholder IRI (ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter) is rejected by the Add IRI input in the dialog -- currently not covered by the 4 mandated ACs."
          },
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/isabout-ui.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC6 (gap): Test that after adding a real IRI via settings and re-opening the dialog, the IRI is listed with a Remove button; clicking Remove and saving returns to the indicator state."
          },
          {
            "file": "tests/playwright/isabout-ui.spec.ts",
            "describe": "AC7 (gap): Test that opening a v0.3 fixture, using Set real subject to add a real IRI, and saving causes the downloaded file to NOT contain ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder (verifying the marker-clear path in handleSave)."
          }
        ],
        "open_questions": [
          "Recon OQ4 resolved by design: deriveIsAboutState reads ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder directly from the project document (no validate() call). This is consistent with recon F6 which confirms the marker is the discriminant for LEGACY vs MISSING state. Architect should confirm this is the intended AC1 trigger mechanism (resolving recon OQ2).",
          "Recon OQ3 resolution assumed: ProjectSettingsDialog is scoped to iao:isAbout only (not ecm:settings from SPEC section 5.5). If the architect intends the dialog to also expose IRI generation policy / export defaults / determinism settings, the dialog body must be extended in a follow-up chain.",
          "ECM_UNSPECIFIED constant is defined independently in both src/ui/App.tsx and src/ui/ProjectSettingsDialog.tsx (string literal 'ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter'). It is NOT exported from src/validate/index.ts (where it is also a local const). If the operator wants a single canonical export of this string, it should be added to src/validate/codes.ts as a named export -- but that requires modifying a stable file outside this task's scope.",
          "serializeVmp (src/kernel/canonicalize.ts) must call JSON.stringify with no replacer that re-introduces undefined-keyed properties. The marker-clear mechanism in ProjectSettingsDialog.handleSave relies on JSON.stringify omitting keys with undefined values (standard behavior). If serializeVmp uses a custom replacer that converts undefined to null, the ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder field would re-appear in the saved file as null rather than being omitted.",
          "shell.spec.ts AC1 checks for zero JS console errors on load. The new ProjectSettingsDialog import is a new module; if it fails to resolve at bundle time, it would emit console errors. Operator should confirm npm run build passes before running e2e suite.",
          "The anchor banner is placed as a sibling between <header> and <div class='gw-body'> inside gw-shell (flex-direction: column). If normalizeOnLoad mutates the document in a way that removes ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder from a v0.3-opened document, AC4 would fail (deriveIsAboutState would return 'missing' not 'legacy'). Recon did not investigate normalizeOnLoad internals -- operator should verify."
        ],
        "summary": "Four changes implement FR-U031 task 2.9: (C1) new ProjectSettingsDialog.tsx dialog for iao:isAbout list management (view / add / remove IRIs; validates against ECM_UNSPECIFIED placeholder; clears legacy migration marker on real-IRI save); (C2) App.tsx full replacement adding the deriveIsAboutState helper, projectSettingsOpen state, 'Project Settings' header button, and an anchor banner strip (rendered between header and body) that reactively shows MISSING or LEGACY state with an affordance button; (C3) App.css append with banner and dialog list styles; (C4) four Playwright tests for the mandated ACs. Detection derives from project document state directly (no validate() call) matching the validator's ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder discriminant logic per recon findings F5 and F6.",
        "self_assessment": "uncertain"
      },
