    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:236-rat-isabout",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change introduces a new React component (ProjectSettingsDialog.tsx), replaces App.tsx with new state, helpers, and JSX, appends CSS, and adds Playwright tests \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all of which alter behavioral and structural content of the subject codebase, not merely typography or citation formatting.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:234-recon-isabout) and grounds every material claim in the developer's proposal. The change is ratified on the following verified bases:\n\n1. RECONNAISSANCE RECONCILIATION. All developer design decisions trace to recon findings. The `deriveIsAboutState` helper in C2 mirrors the discriminant logic in `src/validate/index.ts` (lines 128\u00e2\u20ac\u201c171) exactly: `nonPlaceholder.length > 0` \u00e2\u2020\u2019 clean; `ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder === true && arr.some(v => v === ECM_UNSPECIFIED)` \u00e2\u2020\u2019 legacy; otherwise \u00e2\u2020\u2019 missing. This matches recon F6 to the character. The placeholder string `ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter` matches recon F5 (all three sites). Recon OQ2 (AC1 trigger mechanism) is resolved by the document-state derive approach rather than a validate() call; recon OQ3 (settings scope) is resolved by scoping to iao:isAbout only; recon OQ4 (UI reads marker directly) is resolved by deriveIsAboutState reading `ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder` from the document.\n\n2. FR-U031 COVERAGE. SPEC \u00c2\u00a718.2 FR-U031 requires: display of declared iao:isAbout IRIs, add affordance, edit/remove affordance, prominent display of MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR, prominent display of LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER, and obvious affordance to resolve. C1 (ProjectSettingsDialog) covers display + add + remove. C2 (App.tsx anchor banner) covers both MISSING and LEGACY indicator display with a prominently rendered banner strip and affordance button. All six FR-U031 sub-requirements are addressed.\n\n3. DETECTION LOGIC STRUCTURAL CORRECTNESS. Verified by reading src/validate/index.ts on disk: the `ECM_UNSPECIFIED` local constant, the `isAboutArr` array construction, the `nonPlaceholder` filter, and the `isLegacyAnchorPlaceholder` boolean check in validate() are structurally identical to the corresponding logic in `deriveIsAboutState`. The two-path discrimination is mutually exclusive by the ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder marker, exactly as described in recon F6.\n\n4. SERIALIZATION SAFETY (developer OQ5). Verified by reading src/kernel/canonicalize.ts: `serializeVmp` calls `JSON.stringify(canonical, null, 2)` with no custom replacer \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the second argument is `null`. JavaScript's `JSON.stringify` omits keys whose values are `undefined` by standard specification. The `updated[\"ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder\"] = undefined` marker-clear mechanism in ProjectSettingsDialog.handleSave is therefore structurally sound: the key will be absent from the saved file output.\n\n5. normalizeOnLoad MARKER SURVIVAL (developer OQ6). Verified by reading src/normalize/index.ts: normalizeOnLoad strips only `ecm:_wasNormalizedOnLoad` before comparison (line 68: `delete docForComparison[NORMALIZED_ON_LOAD_MARKER]`). It does not strip `ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder`. When a v0.3 file is opened, migrate() sets the marker, normalizeOnLoad preserves it through serialize\u00e2\u2020\u2019parse, and the marker reaches setProject intact. AC4 fixture test is structurally sound.\n\n6. PLAYWRIGHT FIXTURE EXISTS. `tests/playwright/fixtures/minimal-v0.3.jsonld` is present on disk (confirmed by Glob). AC4's fixture path reference in C4 is valid.\n\n7. LAYER BOUNDARIES. C1 and C2 reside in `src/ui/`. C2 imports from `../migrate/`, `../normalize/`, `../validate/`, `../kernel/`, `../emit/` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all downward imports from the UI layer to lower layers. No import from `src/adapters/` or `src/composition/` into `src/kernel/`. No kernel purity violation. The `before` content of C2 matches the current App.tsx on disk precisely.\n\n8. DIALOG PATTERN CONFORMANCE. C1 uses Dialog.tsx base component, `gw-term-form` CSS class, `gw-form-label`, `gw-form-input`, `gw-form-actions`, `gw-btn`, `gw-btn--secondary` \u00e2\u20ac\u201d exactly the pattern documented in recon F11 for AddTermDialog and AddLiteralDialog.\n\n9. ALL 4 ACS PLAYWRIGHT-CREDIBLE. AC1 (banner visible with data-anchor-state='missing' after New), AC2 (add IRI via dialog \u00e2\u2020\u2019 download \u00e2\u2020\u2019 parse \u00e2\u2020\u2019 assert iao:isAbout contains IRI), AC3 (banner not.toBeVisible after declaration), AC4 (open v0.3 fixture \u00e2\u2020\u2019 legacy banner \u00e2\u2020\u2019 'Set real subject' action) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d all four use stable data-testid selectors and realistic user-flow sequences.\n\nRESIDUAL ADVISORY CONCERNS (not blocking):\n- ECM_UNSPECIFIED is independently defined in src/validate/index.ts, src/ui/App.tsx, and src/ui/ProjectSettingsDialog.tsx. Consolidation into src/validate/codes.ts as a named export is the correct follow-up; acceptable for this task's scope boundary.\n- deriveIsAboutState duplicates validator discrimination logic. A unit test comparing deriveIsAboutState outputs against validate() outputs for the three document states would guard against future drift; recommended for a follow-up chain.\n- No inline 'edit' affordance for individual IRIs; remove + add is the interaction model. Within FR-U031 scope for Phase 2.",
