        ],
        "summary": "The Phase 1 validator (`src/validate/index.ts`) is a pure function returning a `ValidationReport` with a `ecm:findings: ValidationFinding[]` array per SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.13. Each finding carries the five required fields (`ecm:severity`, `ecm:code`, `ecm:message`, `ecm:target`, `ecm:acknowledged`) plus a `type` discriminator, with `ecm:acknowledged` always initialized to `false`. Four of the 26 SPEC-declared codes are implemented: two errors (`MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR`, `INVALID_SPEC_VERSION`) and two info findings (`LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER`, `NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE`). No warning-severity code is implemented and no `makeWarning` factory exists, making the three-severity fixture required by AC1 of task 2.10 impossible to construct against the current validator without adding at least one warning-emitting code path. The bottom panel (`gw-outputs`) is a styled but unimplemented placeholder with `height: 180px`; no `ValidationPanel` component exists, and `App.tsx` discards the `validate()` return value entirely (via `void validate(normalized)`). The comment on line 149 of App.tsx incorrectly attributes the deferred display to \"task 2.8\" (which is Triple Previews); the correct task number is 2.10. The `ecm:validationReports` array is part of the SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.1 project document shape, indicating reports are intended to be persisted in the canonical document, but `buildNewDocument()` and `test/fixtures/canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld` both omit this field. OED-303 (retention policy: latest-only vs. one-per-save) is Open and is a Phase 1 exit gate; its resolution directly governs whether acknowledging a finding and saving will survive a subsequent validate-on-open cycle. IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a72.10 explicitly instructs that this interaction must be documented in code comments even though the resolution is deferred to Phase 3.",
