        "open_questions": [
          "AC1 warning-severity gap: IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a72.10 AC1 specifies '1 error + 1 warning + 1 info' simultaneously. No warning code is implemented in src/validate/index.ts (no makeWarning factory; \u00c2\u00a717.3 warning codes are TODO chain C). The task scope constraint forbids modifying src/validate/*. This proposal adapts AC1 to assert 1 error (MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR) + 1 info (NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE). Operator decision required: (A) permit a follow-up task to add makeWarning + at least one \u00c2\u00a717.3 warning code to src/validate/index.ts and re-verify AC1 with all three severities, or (B) formally re-scope AC1 in IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md to '1 error + 1 info + no warning until chain C'.",
          "OED-303 / ecm:validationReports persistence path: handleAcknowledge writes the updated ValidationReport into project['ecm:validationReports'] as a single-element array (latest-only Phase 2 stub). This means the marker survives Save/parse (AC2) but is discarded on the next file Open when validate() runs fresh (ecm:acknowledged always false on creation per validate() contract). IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a72.10 defers OED-303 resolution to Phase 3. The code comment in handleAcknowledge documents this. Operator should confirm no Phase 2 AC requires acknowledgement to survive a close-and-reopen cycle (which would require pre-merging stored acknowledged state with fresh findings \u00e2\u20ac\u201d an architectural change gated on OED-303).",
          "gap-15 fixture canonical-form compliance: The validation-3-findings.jsonld fixture deliberately omits @context to trigger normalizeOnLoad() normalization (which sets ecm:_wasNormalizedOnLoad=true, enabling NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE to fire). The scope constraint references 'Fixture canonical-form-compliant per gap-15'. If gap-15 requires @context in all playwright fixtures, the fixture needs to be restructured: include @context in exact serializeVmp canonical key order AND pre-set 'ecm:_wasNormalizedOnLoad': true \u00e2\u20ac\u201d normalizeOnLoad() strips the marker from the comparison copy, so a canonical document with the marker pre-set still passes the canonical check and returns the original doc (with marker) to validate(). Operator should confirm gap-15 requirement and whether the pre-set-marker approach satisfies it.",
          "buildNewDocument() is missing 'ecm:validationReports': [] per SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.1 document shape: reconnaissance finding F11. Not addressed in this task (task scope is FR-U028 panel rendering). A follow-up task should add the field to buildNewDocument() once OED-303 resolves (its presence/absence in new documents is a retention-policy question).",
          "App.tsx comment on line 18 (buildNewDocument docstring) still references 'task 2.8' for error display: this is a separate stale comment from the one fixed in C5. The buildNewDocument comment says 'ecm:error display is FR-U028 scope (task 2.8)' \u00e2\u20ac\u201d should be 'task 2.10'. A follow-up editorial fix is recommended."
        ],
        "summary": "Implements FR-U028 (ValidationPanel) across 5 files: (1) new src/ui/ValidationPanel.tsx \u00e2\u20ac\u201d controlled component rendering findings list with severity badges, code/message/target display, and Acknowledge button for non-error findings; (2) src/ui/App.tsx \u00e2\u20ac\u201d validationReport state added (separate from project state to prevent reset on project mutations), handleNew wired to validate, handleFileChange void-validate replaced with setValidationReport, handleAcknowledge writes updated report to both validationReport state and project['ecm:validationReports'] for Save persistence, bottom panel placeholder replaced with ValidationPanel; (3) src/ui/App.css \u00e2\u20ac\u201d ValidationPanel CSS including gw-finding-acknowledged dimming, gw-severity-badge color variants, and gw-btn-acknowledge states; (4) new test fixture validation-3-findings.jsonld producing MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR (error) + NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE (info); (5) new validation-panel.spec.ts with 4 Playwright tests covering AC1-AC4 (AC1/AC2 adapted from warning severity to info severity due to absence of \u00c2\u00a717.3 warning codes in current validator \u00e2\u20ac\u201d see open_questions). OED-303 persistence interaction documented in code comments per IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a72.10 instruction.",
