        "implementation_directions": [
          "ValidationPanel.tsx: new component rendered in bottom panel. Subscribes to current project state, runs validator, renders findings as a list. Each entry: severity badge (error/warning/info colored), ecm:code (e.g., 'MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR'), ecm:message, ecm:target IRI link/text. For warning + info: Acknowledge button. Acknowledged findings: visually distinct (CSS class, e.g., gw-finding-acknowledged) + button shown as 'Acknowledged' or hidden.",
          "Acknowledge handler: marks the finding's ecm:acknowledged=true. Per IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN note: persistence interaction with OED-303 is unresolved \u2014 document the open question via a code comment. For Phase 2 stub: store ecm:acknowledged as a separate UI-state map keyed by finding-id+target, OR persist in ecm:validationReports if the schema supports it. Developer chooses based on recon findings.",
          "App.tsx: replace bottom panel placeholder with <ValidationPanel project={project} setProject={setProject?} />.",
          "Tests: tests/playwright/validation-panel.spec.ts with 4 tests. AC1: fixture with 1 error + 1 warning + 1 info; assert 3 finding entries visible (by severity-badge counts). AC2: click acknowledge on warning; save; parse; assert that finding's ecm:acknowledged=true (or check the documented Phase-2-stub-storage location). AC3: acknowledge a warning; assert the entry has gw-finding-acknowledged class. AC4: assert error finding has no acknowledge button (button absent or disabled).",
          "Fixture for AC1: create tests/playwright/fixtures/validation-3-findings.jsonld with deliberate violations triggering 3 different-severity codes (probably INVALID_SPEC_VERSION + MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR + LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER per Phase 1 + ft-097-test-validator-3 implementations; OR developer adapts based on what codes are actually present)."
