    {
      "@id": "urn:fnsr:task:241-rat-validation-panel",
      "agent": "architect",
      "status": "done",
      "attempts": 1,
      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change introduces a net-new React component (ValidationPanel.tsx), new React state variables (validationReport, handleAcknowledge), new Playwright test infrastructure, a new test fixture, and CSS additions \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this is new behavioral code and new test coverage, not a typo fix, formatting change, or terminology tightening.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance (task 239) is present in UPSTREAM and its twenty-one findings are reconciled by the developer's ten-change proposal (task 240). Ratification proceeds on the following structural grounds:\n\n**FR-U028 coverage:** The ValidationPanel (C1) renders all four display fields \u00e2\u20ac\u201d severity badge, code (gw-finding-code), message (gw-finding-message), and target (gw-finding-target) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d as required by FR-U028 and \u00c2\u00a717.5.\n\n**Error acknowledge affordance (AC4):** C1 enforces `canAck = sev !== 'ecm:error'`, rendering the Acknowledge button only for warning and info findings per \u00c2\u00a717.1. Error findings have no button element in the DOM, satisfying AC4 and the test in C10.\n\n**Visual suppression (AC3):** Acknowledged findings receive the `gw-finding-acknowledged` CSS class (C1, C8 opacity:0.45). The finding is NOT removed from the list \u00e2\u20ac\u201d it is dimmed. This correctly implements SPEC \u00c2\u00a717.5 'acknowledged finding remains in the validation report but is visually suppressed'.\n\n**OED-303 documentation:** C6 (handleAcknowledge) includes an explicit code comment naming OED-303, the Phase 2 latest-only stub semantics, and the Phase 3 deferral, per IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md \u00c2\u00a72.10 direct instruction: 'implement \u00c2\u00a717.5 as specified and document the open question in code comments.'\n\n**Recon reconciliation:** Findings F8/F9/F10 (placeholder, void validate discard, stale task-2.8 comment) are corrected by C5/C7. F17 (no ValidationPanel, no Playwright test) is resolved by C1/C10. F21 (AC2 round-trip persistence path) is implemented via C6 writing the updated report to project['ecm:validationReports'] before setProject so that Save serializes it. F4 (ecm:acknowledged always false on fresh validate()) is managed by keeping validationReport in separate state from project (C3), preventing setProject calls from resetting acknowledgement.\n\n**AC1 warning-severity gap:** No makeWarning factory exists in src/validate/index.ts (recon F7). IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md AC1 specifies '1 error + 1 warning + 1 info' simultaneously \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a three-severity fixture that cannot be constructed against the current validator without modifying src/validate/*, which is outside this task's scope. The developer adapts AC1 to assert 1 error (MISSING_REALIST_ANCHOR) + 1 info (NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE), documents the adaptation with a named gap label (`gap-ac1-warning`) in C10, and raises an operator decision question (A: follow-up task adds makeWarning; B: formally re-scope AC1). This is an acceptable adaptation within phase scope \u00e2\u20ac\u201d \u00c2\u00a717.3 warning codes are explicitly deferred to follow-up chain C.\n\n**gap-15 compliance:** The gap-15 discipline (OPERATOR-MEDIATION-LOG.md Event 7) concerns: no BOM in developer 'after' content, LF newlines (enforced repo-wide by .gitattributes `*.jsonld text eol=lf`), canonical key order for canonical fixtures, no trailing whitespace. The developer's open_question #3 conflates @context inclusion with gap-15 requirements \u00e2\u20ac\u201d gap-15 does not require @context; it governs byte-level encoding properties. C9's fixture deliberately omits @context to trigger normalizeOnLoad() normalization (the design mechanism), which is architecturally valid and not a gap-15 violation. The BOM risk is the developer's responsibility in the 'after' payload \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the C9 content begins with `{` with no BOM character. CRLF is mitigated by the .gitattributes already in place from Event 7. gap-15 compliance concerns are not blocking.\n\n**Layer boundaries:** ValidationPanel.tsx imports from `src/validate/index.ts` only; no imports from src/adapters/ or src/composition/. App.tsx imports ValidationPanel from the same UI layer. No kernel layer boundary violations.\n\n**State initialization:** validationReport state starts as null (C3); C7 uses `validationReport?.['ecm:findings'] ?? []` to handle the pre-load null case gracefully. handleNew (C4) seeds the report immediately after creating a new document, consistent with FR-U002 validate-on-open intent. handleFileChange (C5) replaces the void-discarding call with setValidationReport.\n\n**Remaining open questions not blocking ratification:** (a) gap-ac1-warning: deferred to follow-up chain with operator decision required; (b) gap-15 @context clarification: conflation resolved above \u00e2\u20ac\u201d not a blocking concern; (c) buildNewDocument() missing ecm:validationReports: recon F11 acknowledged, deferred per OED-303; (d) stale buildNewDocument docstring referencing task 2.8: follow-up editorial fix recommended. None of these are architectural blockers for this task's scope.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
          {
