        "open_questions": [
          "The selectedAddClassIri state is not reset to '' after a successful Assign click. If the UX spec requires the dropdown to revert to '(select class)' after assignment, handleAddClassAssignment should call setSelectedAddClassIri('') at the end. The current implementation leaves the last-selected value in the dropdown.",
          "isEcmInstance requires Array.isArray(obj['ecm:classIris']). Instances that pre-date the ecm:classIris field (if any exist in the wild) will not match the guard and will silently pass through handleRemoveClassAssignment/handleAddClassAssignment unchanged. If migration cannot guarantee the field exists on every instance, make 'ecm:classIris' optional in the interface and adjust classIris extraction to use selectedInstance?.['ecm:classIris'] ?? []."
        ],
        "summary": "Four targeted edits to src/ui/Inspector.tsx only. C1 adds EcmInstance interface + isEcmInstance guard (after isEcmLiteralAssertion). C2 adds OwlClassOption interface + getOwlClassOptions() helper (mirrors getObjectPropertyOptions pattern, placed before the component comment). C3 adds selectedAddClassIri useState. C4 replaces the instance mode if-block: adds rawInstances lookup, selectedInstance find, classIris extraction, owlClassOptions, classLabelFor helper, handleRemoveClassAssignment, handleAddClassAssignment, and a Class Assignments subsection in JSX between the IRI display and Literal Assertions \u00e2\u20ac\u201d with all five required data-testids (gw-inspector-class-assignments, gw-class-assignment-row, gw-btn-remove-class, gw-select-add-class, gw-btn-assign-class). No other files touched. Literal Assertions section preserved verbatim. All non-ASCII content absent (encoding constraint satisfied).",
