        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposal adds a new UI surface (class-assignment section in Inspector instance mode) including a new TypeScript interface, type guard, component state, two event handlers, and new JSX tree \u00e2\u20ac\u201d none of which existed before; this is not a typo fix, formatting correction, or terminology tightening.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:244-recon-smoke-suite), satisfying the Spec 03 reconnaissance requirement for substantive changes. The reconnaissance findings directly substantiate the proposed change: F1 confirmed ecm:classIris is read-only in instance mode (lines 81-83) and never rendered; F5 confirmed no class-assignment selector or UI exists anywhere in src/ui/. The proposed change (four edits to src/ui/Inspector.tsx only) is structurally sound on all evaluated axes:\n\n1. BEFORE-SNIPPET FIDELITY: All four before-snippets were verified against the live file. C1 matches lines 39-52 exactly. C2 matches lines 147-168 exactly. C3 matches line 196 exactly. C4 matches lines 209-323 exactly. The applier can match all four without conflict.\n\n2. PATTERN CONFORMANCE: C1 (EcmInstance interface + isEcmInstance guard) mirrors the EcmRelation/isEcmRelation and EcmLiteralAssertion/isEcmLiteralAssertion patterns already present in the same file. C2 (OwlClassOption interface + getOwlClassOptions()) mirrors getDatatypePropertyOptions() identically, including label/IRI fallback via iriTail(). Both additions are consistent with the file's existing domain-type conventions.\n\n3. IMMUTABILITY: handleRemoveClassAssignment and handleAddClassAssignment both produce new arrays (filter and spread respectively) and call onProjectChange with a new top-level object spread \u00e2\u20ac\u201d consistent with how handleDeleteLiteral and handlePredicateChange operate elsewhere in the same component.\n\n4. DATA-TESTID CONVENTION: Five new data-testids (gw-inspector-class-assignments, gw-class-assignment-row, gw-btn-remove-class, gw-select-add-class, gw-btn-assign-class) all follow the established gw- kebab-case prefix convention used throughout src/ui/.\n\n5. DERIVED VIEW: getOwlClassOptions() reads ecm:terms filtered by type === 'owl:Class' \u00e2\u20ac\u201d correctly a derived read of the project document, not independent state.\n\n6. IDEMPOTENCY: handleAddClassAssignment guards with classIris.includes(selectedAddClassIri), preventing duplicate assignment.\n\n7. LAYER BOUNDARIES: All four changes are confined to src/ui/Inspector.tsx. The component accepts a project prop and an onProjectChange callback; it does not import from src/kernel/, src/adapters/, or src/composition/.\n\n8. SCOPE: Single file edit confirmed; no test additions in Chain A (deferred to Chain B per developer's tests_recommended). No new file creations.\n\n9. SPEC CONFORMANCE: FR-U012 specifies 'Edit an instance (label, IRI, class assignments, comment)'; the class-assignments portion is the direct target of this change. IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN \u00c2\u00a72.12 smoke flow 1 requires an 'assign class' step; this change provides the selector and operation path that flow requires.\n\nTwo developer-flagged open questions (selectedAddClassIri not reset after assign; isEcmInstance guard requiring ecm:classIris array on older instances) are advisory-class concerns: the first is a UX refinement candidate for Chain B/C, the second is a data-compatibility edge case that the developer has explicitly surfaced. Neither is a structural blocker for Chain A ratification.",
