        "open_questions": [
          "UPSTREAM recon findings F1/F5 reported gw-select-add-class and gw-btn-assign-class absent, but reading src/ui/Inspector.tsx lines 364-384 shows both selectors are already rendered in the instance-mode branch. Chain A appears to have landed before this task. Confirm Chain A is committed before applying this change (if it has not landed, the gw-select-add-class and gw-btn-assign-class selectors in Flow 1 will be missing at test runtime).",
          "gw-select-predicate for the 'knows' OP uses selectOption({ label: 'knows' }). The existing relation-crud.spec.ts Chain B uses exact IRI values. Confirm the predicate <select> renders option text as rdfs:label (not IRI) so { label } matching resolves correctly.",
          "After gw-btn-assign-class click, no explicit wait is inserted before the subsequent hover-and-drag. If the onProjectChange handler triggers a re-render that momentarily unmounts the node, the hover may race. If flakiness is observed, add `await expect(page.getByTestId('gw-class-assignment-row')).toHaveCount(1)` between step 6 and step 7 as a render-completion guard.",
          "The test captures instance1Id as the firstNode locator's first() element. React Flow does not guarantee DOM order matches creation order when two nodes are added in rapid succession. If instance1Id unexpectedly matches the second-created instance in a flaky run, consider using position-based discrimination or a short wait between the two dblclick calls."
        ],
        "summary": "Single new file tests/playwright/smoke.spec.ts with two test.describe blocks. Smoke flow 1 (12 steps) exercises the full authoring path from new project through save-reload round-trip using only confirmed-present selectors from existing UI code. Smoke flow 4 (3 steps) mirrors isabout-ui.spec.ts AC1 scoped as a smoke gate. No production code edits. No new fixture files. All patterns match existing playwright specs (dblclick positions from canvas.spec.ts Chain D, source-handle drag from relation-crud.spec.ts Chain A, term-add dialog flow from term-crud.spec.ts Chain A, banner assertion from isabout-ui.spec.ts AC1). Estimated ~5500 chars; well within scope threshold.",
