      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change creates a new test file (tests/playwright/smoke.spec.ts, ~250 lines) covering two smoke flows not previously exercised by any test \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this adds new behavioral test surface and new test execution paths, placing it firmly outside editorial-correction scope.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:244-recon-smoke-suite) and satisfies the Spec 03 reconnaissance requirement for substantive changes. The proposed change is a single new test file with no production code edits. Independent verification of all selectors referenced in the test confirms each is present in the current codebase:\n\n- gw-btn-new \u00e2\u2020\u2019 App.tsx:226\n- gw-btn-save \u00e2\u2020\u2019 App.tsx:240\n- gw-btn-add-class \u00e2\u2020\u2019 TermSidebar.tsx:249 (via addTestId prop \u00e2\u2020\u2019 data-testid)\n- gw-btn-add-object-property \u00e2\u2020\u2019 TermSidebar.tsx:259\n- gw-dialog-add-term \u00e2\u2020\u2019 AddTermDialog.tsx:106 (Dialog testId prop \u00e2\u2020\u2019 data-testid on <dialog> element, Dialog.tsx:51)\n- gw-input-term-label \u00e2\u2020\u2019 AddTermDialog.tsx:128\n- gw-btn-term-submit \u00e2\u2020\u2019 AddTermDialog.tsx:168\n- gw-canvas-view \u00e2\u2020\u2019 CanvasView.tsx:456\n- gw-inspector-instance-iri \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Inspector.tsx:324\n- gw-select-add-class \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Inspector.tsx:367 (Chain A landed; class assignment UI is present in lines 315\u00e2\u20ac\u201c386 of the instance-mode branch)\n- gw-btn-assign-class \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Inspector.tsx:379\n- gw-class-assignment-row \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Inspector.tsx:340\n- gw-inspector-relation \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Inspector.tsx:524\n- gw-select-predicate \u00e2\u2020\u2019 Inspector.tsx:547 (options rendered as {opt.label}, confirming { label } matching resolves correctly)\n- gw-anchor-banner with data-anchor-state \u00e2\u2020\u2019 App.tsx:292\u00e2\u20ac\u201c293\n- gw-file-input \u00e2\u2020\u2019 App.tsx:268\n\nThe reconnaissance findings F1 and F5 reported class-assignment UI as absent, but independent reading of Inspector.tsx lines 315\u00e2\u20ac\u201c386 shows the UI is present. The discrepancy is explained by Chain A landing between reconnaissance and developer dispatch; the developer correctly identified and disclosed this in open_questions item 1. The architect's direct verification resolves the conflict in favor of the current codebase state.\n\nThe save-then-re-open reload pattern (setInputFiles(downloadPath)) is the correct implementation of 'reload' for a Phase 2 app with no session persistence mechanism, consistent with reconnaissance inference F3/F4.\n\nSmoke flow 4 mirrors isabout-ui.spec.ts AC1 exactly and is anchored to App.tsx:289\u00e2\u20ac\u201c308 behavior confirmed by reconnaissance F7.\n\nEvent 8 position-awareness is applied (bottom-area dblclick positions: x=80/300, y=paneBox.height-80) in a manner consistent with the canvas dblclick pattern.\n\nStructural JSON-LD assertions on the downloaded file are correctly scoped: ecm:terms (Person owl:Class + knows owl:ObjectProperty), ecm:instances length 2 + instance1 classIris contains Person IRI, ecm:relations length 1 with knows IRI as predicateIri.\n\nResidual advisory risks noted but not blocking:\n(a) React Flow edge bounding-box center click may miss the narrow SVG path \u00e2\u20ac\u201d inherent to SVG interaction testing, consistent with existing relation-crud.spec.ts patterns.\n(b) DOM ordering of .first() node may not guarantee creation order \u00e2\u20ac\u201d developer disclosed; acceptable at smoke-test fidelity level.\n(c) Post-assign-class render race between step 6 and 7 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d developer disclosed guard option (gw-class-assignment-row count assertion); can be applied if flakiness is observed.\n\nAll findings support ratification.",
