          "SMOKE FLOW 2 RELOAD ASSERTION ORDER: The assertion on ecm:terms (parsing downloadPath with fs.readFileSync) occurs after the re-upload step (setInputFiles), reading the same downloaded file. The file content is unchanged by the re-upload. If the operator prefers a UI-level assertion after reload (e.g., checking that TermSidebar shows 'Person (Smoke 2)'), that could be added as an additional assertion after step 5.",
          "SMOKE FLOW 3 ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter IN iao:isAbout: After migration from v0.3 and adding a real IRI via ProjectSettingsDialog, the saved iao:isAbout array will contain BOTH 'ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter' AND 'https://example.org/subjects/AlphaTopic' (ProjectSettingsDialog does not remove the placeholder from the list). This proposal only asserts that AlphaTopic is present and ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder is not true. If the operator requires asserting that ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter is absent from iao:isAbout, a Remove step in the settings dialog would be needed first."
        ],
        "summary": "Two changes to tests/playwright/smoke.spec.ts: C1 adds `import path from 'path'` and two fixture-path constants; C2 appends smoke flow 2 (edit-label roundtrip: load v0.4 fixture with Person class -> EditTermDialog -> save -> re-upload -> assert label persisted) and smoke flow 3 (v0.3 migration + isAbout: load v0.3 -> assert migration banner -> set AlphaTopic IRI via ProjectSettingsDialog -> save -> assert iao:isAbout contains AlphaTopic and ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder absent). All selectors verified in source. Migration behavior confirmed via src/migrate/index.ts migrateV3toV4 and src/ui/ProjectSettingsDialog.tsx handleSave. Fixture path for smoke flow 2 deviates from INPUTS spec (minimal.jsonld has no terms); substitution noted in open_questions.",
