      "outputs": {
        "ruling": "ratified",
        "editorial_verdict": "substantive",
        "editorial_verdict_reason": "The proposed change introduces new Playwright test flows (flows 2 and 3) with new fixture references, new download-re-upload reload patterns, new assertions on ecm:terms label persistence and ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder clearance \u00e2\u20ac\u201d this is new test surface, not a typo or terminology correction.",
        "rationale": "Reconnaissance is present in UPSTREAM (urn:fnsr:task:244-recon-smoke-suite). The proposed changes (C1 + C2) are structurally sound; all selectors, fixture paths, and behavioral assertions were verified against source.\n\n**C1 (import block):** `import path from 'path'` and two fixture-path constants are correctly added. The `before` snippet (`import { test, expect } from \"@playwright/test\";\\nimport fs from \"fs\";`) is unique in the file (lines 1\u00e2\u20ac\u201c2 of the existing smoke.spec.ts); the applier's before-snippet match will succeed. The rest of the file (JSDoc comment + existing tests) is unaffected.\n\n**C2 (Smoke flow 2 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d edit-label roundtrip):** The fixture substitution (`term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld` in lieu of INPUTS-specified `test/fixtures/canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld`) is correct. The minimal.jsonld fixture has `ecm:terms: []` (confirmed by direct read) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the TermSidebar would show no classes to click. The substitute fixture has Person (`id: https://example.org/ontology/Person`) as `ecm:project-created` owl:Class, making it a valid edit-label target. The locator chain `gw-term-section-classes` \u00e2\u2020\u2019 `[role=\"button\"]` \u00e2\u2020\u2019 `hasText: \"Person\"` is correct: only `ecm:project-created` terms receive `role=\"button\"` in TermSidebar.tsx (line 163); Organization in the same fixture is `ecm:system-starter-example` and will not match. The IRI-based assertion (`t[\"id\"] === \"https://example.org/ontology/Person\"`) is stable against the fixture. The download+re-upload reload pattern (step 5: `setInputFiles(downloadPath!)`) is new but well-formed per reconnaissance finding F4 (no existing spec exercises this). The label assertion reads the downloaded file directly rather than verifying TermSidebar UI state post-reload \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a minor coverage gap noted in the developer's open_questions, not blocking.\n\n**C2 (Smoke flow 3 \u00e2\u20ac\u201d v0.3 migration + isAbout):** All selectors verified in source: `gw-migration-banner` (App.tsx line 274), `gw-btn-project-settings` (App.tsx line 256), `gw-dialog-project-settings` (ProjectSettingsDialog.tsx line 92), `gw-input-isabout-iri` (line 141), `gw-btn-add-iri` (line 146), `gw-btn-settings-save` (line 173). Migration behavior confirmed: `migrateV3toV4` sets `iao:isAbout = [\"ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter\"]` and `ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder = true`; `App.tsx` sets `migrationBannerText` to a non-null string when `wasMigrated = true`, causing `gw-migration-banner` to render. `ProjectSettingsDialog.handleSave` sets `ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder = undefined` (JSON.stringify-omitted) when `hasRealIri = true` after adding AlphaTopic. The `iao:isAbout` array will contain both `ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter` and the added IRI after save \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the `toContain` assertion is correct. The `ecm:_legacyAnchorPlaceholder` assertion (`not.toBe(true)`) passes since the field will be absent from the saved JSON. The open question about whether `ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter` should be removed from the list is a UX/semantic concern (FR-U031), not a test correctness issue; the test as written is valid.\n\n**C2 before-snippet (applier):** The `before` for C2 is the closing block of smoke flow 4 (the anchor-banner `toHaveAttribute` + closing braces). This block is unique in the file (smoke flow 1's save-reload block uses different test IDs; no other test in the file references `gw-anchor-banner` or `data-anchor-state`). Applier match will succeed.\n\n**No regression risk:** The change is append-only to an existing file; flows 1 and 4 are unmodified. The `C1` import-block replacement leaves the JSDoc comment and all existing test.describe blocks in place.\n\n**Self-assessment calibration:** The developer's `self_assessment: uncertain` is honest and well-scoped \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the uncertainty is limited to the documented open questions (fixture substitution, reload assertion order, placeholder retention), none of which prevent test execution or introduce false positives/negatives in the assertions as written.",
        "referenced_evidence": [
