        "bankings": [
          {
            "id": "B1",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "Developer-corrected fixture substitution grounded in reconnaissance: the INPUTS spec referenced canonical-v0.4/minimal.jsonld for smoke flow 2's edit-label step, but reconnaissance finding F10 and direct fixture inspection established that minimal.jsonld has ecm:terms:[] making the step impossible. The developer independently identified and substituted term-sidebar-2c-1op-1dp.jsonld, documented the deviation in open_questions, and self-assessed as uncertain. This is the first instance of a developer task correcting an imprecise INPUTS fixture reference using reconnaissance findings as grounding \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the pattern of open_questions carrying the deviation rationale rather than silently substituting is the discipline to carry forward."
          },
          {
            "id": "B2",
            "category": "pattern-observation",
            "content": "The download-then-re-upload reload pattern (save \u00e2\u2020\u2019 waitForEvent('download') \u00e2\u2020\u2019 download.path() \u00e2\u2020\u2019 setInputFiles(downloadPath)) establishes a Playwright idiom for testing persistence through the full save-reload cycle in the absence of session-storage primitives. Smoke flow 2 is the first Playwright spec in this project to exercise this complete round-trip. The pattern is technically correct but the post-reload assertion reads the raw file rather than verifying UI state after re-load \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a deliberate tradeoff noted by the developer. Future smoke flows should consider adding a UI-level follow-up assertion (e.g., TermSidebar shows the edited label) to cover the full round-trip through the render layer."
          },
          {
            "id": "B3",
            "category": "methodology-refinement-candidate",
            "content": "Smoke flow 3's ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter retention issue: after v0.3 migration and a single AddIRI action, the saved iao:isAbout array contains both the placeholder and the real IRI. The test asserts presence of the real IRI (via toContain) and absence of the legacy marker flag, but does not assert placeholder removal. The developer surfaced this as an open question. This is a candidate for a FR-U031 refinement (should the ProjectSettingsDialog auto-remove ecm:UnspecifiedSubjectMatter when a real IRI is added?) that the UX-SME should deliberate before smoke flow 3's acceptance criteria are finalized."
          }
        ]
      },
